title: fettuccine salad
directions: Boil fettuccine as directed on package.
Slice carrot, green and red peppers (1 of each or as many as you'd like) thin.
Dice the onion.
Crumble Feta cheese.
Mix all together.
You may also throw in sliced black olives, if you'd like.
About 1/2 hour before serving, mix up dressing and mix with all the ingredients. Chill and serve.

title: delicious salad
directions: Cream the cheese with the juice from the cherries.
Chop all but 4 of the cherries and add to the mixture.
Mix well, but do not stir or beat hard.
To serve, layer lettuce on an individual plate, then a pineapple slice.
In the center, heap the cheese mixture, topping with a cherry.
Can also be served as a dessert by draining crushed pineapple and adding that to the cheese instead of sliced pineapple.
Serve very cold in sherbet glasses with whipped cream and a cherry.

title: ice cream
directions: Beat eggs with sugar.
Blend in milk, half and half and heavy cream.
Add salt and vanilla.
Pour into ice cream maker and process.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown bacon, onion and hamburger.
Pour off excess fat and add remaining ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cream cheese cupcakes
directions: Mix cream cheese, eggs, vanilla and sugar.
Put paper cup in the bottom of cupcake pan.
Put 1 cookie in paper cup.
Pour cream cheese mixture over cookie.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes. Top with cherries or blueberries.

title: mint patties
directions: Melt margarine
and Crisco over hot water and stir all ingredients together.
Knead until smooth.
If entire recipe is to be one color and flavor, both can be added along with other ingredients.
If not, divide to your desire.
Roll into ball size of pea or little larger.
Flatten to desired size.

title: cheeseburger buns
directions: In a mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water. Add next 5 ingredients and 2 cups flour; beat until smooth. Stir in enough remaining flour to form a soft dough. Turn onto floured surface; knead until smooth, about 4 to 6 minutes. Place in a greased bowl. Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled. In a skillet, cook beef and onion until done; drain. Stir in tomato sauce. Set aside. Punch down dough; divide into 16 pieces. On a lightly floured surface, roll out dough into a 5-inch circle. Top each circle with two pieces of cheese and 3 tablespoons beef mixture. Bring dough over filling to center. Pinch edges to seal. Place seam side down on greased baking sheet. Cover and let rise until doubled. Bake at 400° for 8 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: truffle
directions: Arrange the ingredients in order given, with Dream Whip on top.
Refrigerate to set.

title: trenton's famous scrambled eggs
directions: Mix eggs, salt and pepper with fork until all is yellow.
Heat margarine or butter in pan over medium
heat until melted.
Add egg mixture and hot dog.
Stir as often as needed so eggs do not burn onto bottom or side of pan.
When eggs are thickened in pan, add cheese and take off stove.
Makes 1 servings.

title: quick candy
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a heavy boil.
Then add peanut butter and cereal.
Mix well and drop by spoonful on wax paper.

title: egg bread
directions: Place bread in toaster and toast until golden brown.
Heat a skillet to medium heat.
Cut 2-inch circle out of the middle of toast.
Melt butter in pan.
Place toast in the pan.
Break egg over the toast so that egg yolk is in the hold of the toast.
Cook until egg yolk is done or to your liking.

title: dillon's fried apples
directions: Peel and core apples; cut into thin slices.
In a heavy saucepan, bring apples, sugar, cinnamon, cinnamon stick and butter to a boil.
Cook over high heat 5 minutes until sugars dissolve. Reduce heat to low and simmer, uncovered, 15 to 20 minutes or until apples are tender.
Remove cinnamon stick.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Place ingredients in pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inch, in order listed. Sprinkle with cheese (should be sharp or Parmesan) or bacon bits. Refrigerate 24 hours.
Do not mix.
Serve in squares.

title: peanut butter french toast
directions: Blend eggs, salt and milk with a whisk in a shallow plate. Heat griddle to medium/hot.
Dip bread slices into egg mixture and place on griddle.
Brown one side, then flip over.
Coat browned side with peanut butter.
Complete cooking.
Peanut butter will melt into toast.
Serve with favorite jelly, jam or syrup.
Good!

title: stack cake
directions: Pour all ingredients together and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured small cake pans.
Bake at 350° until done.
Stack with cooked apples or applesauce.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Boil milk, margarine, sugar and cocoa together for 1 minute. Remove from heat and add peanut butter, vanilla and oats. Drop on waxed paper.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Saute onion, celery and garlic in oil in large pan for 3 minutes.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, water, cabbage, carrots, bay leaf, oregano, basil, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil; cover and lower heat and simmer for 30 minutes or longer.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate for a few hours. Makes 6 servings.

title: swedish cookies
directions: Blend the shortening, the butter and vanilla together. Mix in the sugar, then the soda, baking powder, ground nuts, flour and coconut. It is a very dry mixture that the butter and shortening hold together.
Form into log rolls and wrap each log in wax paper. Chill overnight.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Layer in baking dish as listed.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Top with Funyun onion rings after baking.

title: gumbo succotash
directions: Put all in pot.
Cover and simmer until tender.
You may need more tomato juice as it cooks.

title: "strawberry" fig jelly
directions: Bring to a boil and let bubble for 10 minutes.
Fill sterilized jars and seal.

title: lemon cheese bars
directions: Mix dry
cake mix with 1 egg, 1/3 cup oil; mix together until crumbly.
Reserve 1
cup.
Put remaining in greased pan. Bake for 15 minutes at
Mix
cheese, juice, sugar and 1 egg until light and
smooth.	Spread	over 1st layer. Sprinkle with reserved mixture.
Bake 15 minutes more.

title: raisin pie
directions: This recipe is for a small pie.
Put water up to raisins in saucepan.
Let come to boil and then simmer 15 to 20 minutes. Remove from heat and add thickening and slice of butter.
Pour into crust and top with crust.
Bake at 450 degrees until crust starts to brown.
When crust begins to brown, turn heat to 325-350 degrees.
Bake approximately 35 minutes.

title: norwegian apple pie
directions: In bowl, with a spoon, mix the ingredients in the order listed.
Fold
the	nuts
and
apples in last, to form a thick batter.
Put
mixture
in
a 10-inch glass pie plate.
Bake at 350°
to
375° for approximately 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve warm or cooled.

title: beef stroganoff with noodles
directions: Dredge steak in flour.
Brown with onion in butter.
Add seasonings and water.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour. Stir occasionally.
Add soup and mushrooms; stir to mix.
Cook 30 minutes longer, until beef is tender.
Turn off heat and stir in sour cream.
Serve over noodles.

title: pickled okra
directions: Wash okra and brush lightly with nylon net or brush to remove "fuzz".
Trim okra stems without cutting too close.
Sterilize 10 pint jars and keep hot until ready to use.
Combine vinegar, water and salt and bring to a boil.
Into each jar, pack okra in two vertical layers.
The first layer should be packed with stems down; the next with stems up.
Also add to each jar 1 clove garlic, 1 hot red pepper, 1 teaspoon dill seed and 1 teaspoon mustard seed.
Pour hot vinegar over okra and seal.
Process in boiling water bath 5 minutes.
Let stand several weeks before opening.

title: meatless chili soup
directions: Drain garbanzo beans and corn. Drain and rinse red kidney beans.
In a large saucepan, stir together beans, corn, kidney beans, broth, tomatoes, onion, chili powder, garlic, red pepper and black pepper.
Bring to a boil, then reduce the heat. Cover and simmer for 20 minutes. To serve, ladle into bowls.
Dollop each serving with 1 tablespoon yogurt.
Makes 4 servings.

title: monkey bread
directions: Take white sugar and cinnamon, make cinnamon mixture.
Take biscuits and cut each one in 4 pieces.
Roll them in cinnamon sugar.

title: oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Add soda to milk and stir into mixture of first 4 ingredients. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Chop up vegetables and mix with:

title: spaghetti carbonara
directions: Place fish in baking dish (if skin is on it, put skin side down in dish).
Sprinkle fish lightly with black pepper, garlic salt, dill weed and Italian bread crumbs.
Slice butter on top (about 4 teaspoons).
Put in middle oven and broil.
Don't turn fish.
Broil 2 to 3 minutes for scallops and sole.
Broil 5 to 7 minutes for perch, cod and haddock.

title: melon sorbet
directions: Puree chopped melon in blender and set aside.
Mix sugar and wine in saucepan and simmer until sugar is dissolved.
Mix in the melon puree.
Pour into loaf pan and freeze 4 hours or until hard. Puree again 30 minutes before serving.
Return to freezer until time to serve.
Garnish serving dishes with mint sprigs.
Makes 4 (1 cup) servings.

title: egg pie
directions: Mix butter, sugar and flour.
Add eggs, milk, vanilla and salt.
Pour in pie shell; bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: crisp potato salad
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill.

title: drumstick torte
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients and put in a 9 x 13 pan and bake in 350° oven for 5 to 10 minutes (first layer). Let cool about 20 minutes before adding the remainder of layers.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Combine flour and sugar; stir in egg, then fruit juices. Cook, stirring, over hot water until thick.
Cool.
Whip the cream; fold in.
Serve over fresh fruit or with jellied fruit salad.

title: orange mandarin cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, eggs and oranges with liquid for 2 minutes. Pour into greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Drain pineapple juice, reserving the juice of 1 can to pour over the baked layers while warm (2 layer cake).

title: microwave savory cabbage rolls
directions: Power Level:
High.
Cut core from cabbage; rinse.
In medium glass bowl, heat, covered, 4 to 5 minutes on High.
Remove 8 leaves; reserve (using remaining cabbage in other recipes).
Into glass bowl, crumble ground beef; stir in onions.
Heat 3 1/2 to 4 1/2 minutes on High until beef is browned, stirring once; drain. Stir in 1/2 tomato sauce, rice, salt and pepper.
To stuff cabbage, place beef-rice filling in cabbage leaf; roll up, folding edges in. Arrange seam side down in square baking dishes.
Pour in remaining tomato sauce blended with brown sugar and vinegar.
Heat, covered, 5 minutes before serving.

title: fat free chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Spray cookie sheets with cooking spray.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Stir in corn syrup and egg whites until blended (dough will be thick and slightly sticky).
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheets.
Bake in 350° oven 7 to 9 minutes or just until set (cookies will be soft when pressed).
Do not overbake.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain and keep hot. Melt 2 tablespoons butter in frying pan. Saut mushrooms until golden brown. Melt 1/4 cup butter in large saucepan; remove from heat. Blend in flour, salt and pepper. Stir in chicken stock slowly. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens and boils 1 minute. Remove from heat. Stir in sherry and cream slowly. Combine sauce, mushrooms, chicken and spaghetti; spoon into greased 2-quart casserole and sprinkle cheese over top. Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes, until bubbly and brown on top. Serves 6 to 8.

title: super pea and pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Rinse and drain. Mix all ingredients and chill several hours or overnight.
Serve in a lettuce cup.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: egg casserole
directions: Baking Temperature: 325°.
Baking Time: 50 to 60 minutes.

title: easy scalloped potatoes
directions: Butter 1 1/2-quart casserole.
For sauce, in heavy saucepan, over medium heat, melt butter.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper until smooth.
Gradually stir in milk; cook until mixture boils, stirring constantly.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken until well done; chop fine.
Cook mixed vegetables until well done.
Mix broth and soup.
Place chicken in bottom of 8 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Add vegetables.
Pour soup and broth over vegetables.
Mix flour, oleo and milk; pour over top.
Bake at 400° until pastry browns.

title: taco fried chicken
directions: In 3-quart bowl, combine taco mix, flour and salt.
In 2-quart bowl, blend egg and milk.
Dip chicken pieces into egg mixture, then coat in flour mixture.
Fry in hot shortening.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In
long, buttered casserole (13 x 9-inches), layer the following:
Place
chicken (deboned).
In saucepan, heat soups and milk.
Pour this mixture over chicken breasts.
In saucepan, heat
broth,
margarine
and
seasoning
mix.
Pour over casserole.
Heat at 325° for 15 minutes or until bubbly.

title: pea salad
directions: Drain peas and	green
beans.
Add
celery,
onion
and pimentos.
Mix Mazola
oil,
vinegar,
sugar, salt and pepper. Bring to boil.
After peas, beans and pimentos drain, add oil, wine vinegar, sugar, salt
and
pepper after it's brought to a boil.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: spinach balls
directions: Melt butter or margarine.
Add spinach (well drained), eggs, onion, cheese and stuffing mix; mix well and chill overnight.
Form into balls (makes approximately 36 balls).
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Very good appetizer.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Sift together flour, salt, cloves and cinnamon; set aside. Mix egg, sugar and shortening with a spoon until light and fluffy. Combine applesauce and baking soda and add to ingredients. Mix well. Stir in nuts and raisins. Drop by teaspoons onto a lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned. Makes approximately 100 cookies.

title: tangy honeyed shrimp
directions: Clean and devein shrimp, keeping tail intact.
Drain on paper towels.
Heat peanut oil in wok or saute on high 1 minute.
Add shrimp, garlic and ginger and cook, stirring constantly, for about 8 minutes, or until shrimp turn pink.
Watch heat carefully to avoid overcooking.
Combine broth and next 7 ingredients, stirring until smooth.
Add to shrimp mixture, stirring constantly.
Bring to boil; cook 1 minute.
Stir in sesame oil, green onions and cilantro.
Cook until heated through.
Serve immediately over rice. Yields 4 servings.

title: tostitos dip(microwave)
directions: Heat eggs, vinegar and sugar in microwave on Medium, stirring often.
Cook until thickened.
Mix with remaining ingredients.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix sugar and eggs first, then add other ingredients. Mix well by hand.
Bake in long baking dish at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In glass baking dish, pour in frozen broccoli. Sprinkle with garlic powder. Pour in rice and milk.
Spoon can of soup over mixture. Top with sliced Velveeta. Microwave on High for 20 minutes, stirring once after 10 minutes.

title: topping for angel food cake
directions: Make pie filling according to directions; cool.
Fold in ice cream.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and Crisco.
Add eggs and spices.
Put soda in berries.
Add berries, then add flour, cocoa and salt, a little at a time until all is mixed thoroughly.
Add vanilla. Bake in layers.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or test with cake tester.
May take a few more minutes.
Ice with your favorite icing.

title: egg cream
directions: In 10-ounce glass, stir chocolate syrup and milk to mix thoroughly.
Slowly stir in enough soda to fill glass.

title: chicken manicotti
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Cook manicotti shells as directed on package; drain.
Mix chicken, carrot, Ricotta cheese, onions, cilantro and garlic.
Fill shells with chicken mixture.

title: gina's famous chili
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Simmer them until tender (2 - 3 hours) and drain.
In melted butter saute onions, shallots, green chilies, and garlic until onions are soft.
Add sirloin and cook over moderate heat until browned.
Add turkey and pepper flakes. Sprinkle with flour, and stir until blended.
Transfer to heavy Dutch oven or 8 qt. kettle.
Add next 8 ingredients.
Bring to boil, then simmer for 30 minutes stirring occasionally.
Stir in spices and continue to simmer for 1 hour or more.
Just before serving, remove from heat, stir in sour cream, and return to low heat to heat through.
May be made ahead and refrigerated or frozen, but do not add sour cream until ready to serve.

title: whole wheat raisin nut bread
directions: Pour the 2 cups boiling water over raisins, sugar and butter. Let stand while preparing other ingredients.
Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt; add to raisin mixture.
Add eggs, nuts and vanilla; beat well.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans (2 large or 4 small ones).
Bake large loaves for 1 hour or small ones for 50 minutes at 375°.
Bread may be frozen and used later.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Wesson oil.
Add sugar.
Add eggs 1 at a time, beating after each addition.
Add coconut flavoring.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add alternately with milk to egg mixture. Add coconut and pecans.
Pour into well-greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: hobo beans
directions: Brown bacon; drain and crumble into pieces.
Brown beef and onion; drain.
Mix all ingredients and bake for 1 hour at 400°.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Melt butter.
Add eggs and sugar; mix well.
Add coconut. Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, or until done.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook until onion, celery and broccoli are tender.
Add one cup of Minute rice.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 35 minutes or until done.

title: fruit salad
directions: Put pudding mix in microwave bowl.
Measure liquid from chunks and oranges (need 1 to 1 1/4 cups).
Pour into pudding.
Cook, uncovered, for 3 to 4 minutes in microwave until boiling.
Add pineapple and oranges to mixture; cool.
Add cherries.
One hour before serving, slice bananas and mix.
Slice and peel kiwi and arrange on top of salad.

title: grandma's peanut butter cookies
directions: Stir together flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
Mix margarine and peanut butter.
Add brown sugar, mixing thoroughly. Add eggs; beat well.
Gradually add flour mixture, beating until thoroughly mixed.
On lightly floured surface, roll out dough to 1/8 inch thickness.
Cut with floured cookie cutter and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes or until done.

title: olive nut spread
directions: Blend cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Stir in nuts and olives and then add juice and pepper.
Chill.
May be used on crackers or as sandwich spread.

title: peanut butter swirl bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine peanut butter, butter, brown sugar and granulated sugar.
Beat until creamy. Gradually beat in eggs and vanilla.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Blend in peanut butter mixture.
Spread into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over surface.
Place in a 350° oven for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven; run knife through mixture to marbleize.
Bake an additional 30 minutes.
Cool; cut into 2 x 1-inch bars.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: peanut butter pound cake
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter and sugar.
Add 1 cup of flour, milk and 3 eggs, ending with 1 cup of flour into which baking powder has been mixed.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 275° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Beat cranberry sauce until smooth and add lemon juice.
Pour into refrigerator trays and combine remaining ingredients and pour over cranberry mixture.
Freeze.
Make day ahead.

title: cake brownies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in bowl.
Mix sugar, egg yolks, butter, milk and vanilla, then add chocolate, dry ingredients and nuts, then add beaten egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Bake in a 9 x 9-inch greased pan.

title: minute fudge frosting
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in saucepan.
Bring slowly to a full rolling boil, stirring constantly, and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Beat until thick enough to spread.
If frosting becomes too thick, add about 1 tablespoon cream.
(This can stand to cool, stirring every so often, if you wish.)

title: mom's artichoke hearts dip
directions: Blend cheeses and mayonnaise; add chilies and artichokes and stir.
Turn into casserole dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Can be prepared ahead of time and warmed up to serve.

title: apple and shrimp salad
directions: Simmer bay leaf and cloves in water until well flavored; strain.
Dissolve Jell-O in hot liquid.
Add tomato sauce and cool. Add rest of ingredients.
Pour into mold; garnish with tomatoes and cukes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugars and oleo until light and fluffy.
Add oil, eggs and vanilla, beating until ingredients are combined.
Add flour, salt, soda and cream of tartar.
Mix until it is combined.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten each ball with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: james river waffles
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat yolks until light, adding 1 cup buttermilk.
Sift together dry ingredients; add to yolk mixture and beat.
Add the remaining cup of buttermilk and beat again, adding melted margarine.
Lastly, fold in the beaten (stiff) egg whites. Bake in hot waffle iron.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat into bite size slices.
Put butter in Dutch oven pan and saute the meat until all of the juice is boiled down.
(Any cooking oil may be used in place of the butter, but the taste is not quite the same.)
Remove meat from the pan and add 1 cup chopped onion to the remaining drippings.
(If necessary, add another spoon of butter.)
Saute onion until transparent.
Add 3 tablespoons flour, dry mustard, catsup and mashed garlic.
When this is well blended, add the sauteed meat.
Add enough boiling water to cover meat and the bouillon.

title: taco salad
directions: Add taco seasoning and chili beans to browned meat.
Simmer uncovered.
If too thick, add water.
Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Add meat mixture.
Crush 1/2 large bag of Doritos and mix well.
Top with large bottle of Western salad dressing.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all together, except crackers and margarine. Pour in casserole dish.
Crush Ritz crackers (about 1 stack).
Melt 1 stick of margarine.
Coat crackers with margarine. Pat on top.
Bake in 350° oven until bubbles and browns lightly.

title: 3-2-1 chili
directions: Brown the meat and drain the fat.
Add canned foods in a large pot; mix and heat approximately 15 minutes.
You may cut recipe in half.

title: shrimp paste
directions: Grind shrimp.
Add butter and spices.
Mix thoroughly.
Place in covered bowl and leave in refrigerator for several hours.
May be sliced or put in mold and used with crackers.

title: glazed baby carrots
directions: In a saucepan, put the carrots.
Add salt, sugar, butter and enough water just to barely cover the carrots.
Cover; cook just until the carrots are tender.
Remove the lid; boil until the water has completely evaporated, leaving a sticky glaze.
Sprinkle with the cinnamon; mix and serve.
Mmm good!

title: blueberry-lemon bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Butter 8-inch loaf pan.
Combine first 3 ingredients; set aside.
With mixer, cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add lemon peel.
Mix dry ingredients, alternating with milk.
End with dry ingredients.
Stir in blueberries.
Bake until golden brown for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: snackers party mix
directions: Combine crackers and peanuts in 4-quart microwave-safe bowl and set aside.

title: baked beans
directions: Look over beans, remove bad ones.

title: alberta (b) ketchup
directions: Cook and drain tomatoes overnight.
Cook tomatoes and rest of ingredients together for 1 hour.
Put into jars and seal.
Good for baked beans and Sloppy Joes.

title: lemon dill twice baked potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes.
Pat dry.
Prick potatoes with a fork.
Bake in 425° oven for 40 to 60 minutes or cook, uncovered, in a microwave oven on 100% power (High) for 14 to 17 minutes.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise.
Gently scoop out each potato half, leaving a thin shell.
Place potato pulp in large bowl.
Add 3 tablespoons melted margarine or butter, sour cream, dill, lemon juice, garlic salt and pepper.
Beat with an electric mixer (low speed) until smooth.
Pile mixture into potatoes.
Bake in 425° oven for about 20 minutes or until light brown.
Makes 8 servings.

title: tomato relish
directions: Mix well and boil for 1 hour.
Put in jars and seal.

title: meat loaf
directions: Soak bread crumbs from dressing in milk for 5 minutes.
Add hamburger, pork, eggs, contents of flavor packet, salt, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Mix well.
Place in a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Cover with chili sauce and bacon, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: Mix all ingredients together in casserole dish. Cook 1 hour at 350°. Do not uncover or stir until cooked 1 hour.

title: soda pop sherbet
directions: Mix.
Freeze as you would ice cream in a small freezer.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve jello as directed on package.
Add sugar to jello mixture while hot.
Add pineapple juice and lemonade, then add limeade as directed on can.
Just before serving, add ginger ale or 7-Up.
Serves 30.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed; drain.
Combine rest of ingredients, except cracker crumbs.
Place in a buttered casserole dish; top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: frozen salad
directions: Whip the cream cheese.
Add the remaining ingredients, except whipping cream.
Whip the whipping cream; fold into the mixture. Pour into mold and freeze.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Just mix and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for about 25 minutes at 350°.

title: banana bread
directions: Oil bottom of 9 x 5-inch glass loaf pan and sprinkle with flour.
Mix all ingredients and pour in prepared pan.
Bake in 325° oven for 50 minutes or until firm in center of loaf.

title: decorator frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients as listed and spread on cake or cookies with wet spatula.

title: sweet dill pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers.
Dissolve lime in water.
Pour over cucumbers and let stand 24 hours.
Take out of lime water and wash.
Let stand in ice water for 3 hours.
Drain 30 minutes.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Save 1 to 2 cups of chicken stock.
Place all ingredients in pot with chicken stock and bring to a boil.
Boil slowly 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pack firmly back into vanilla wafer box and store in refrigerator until ready to eat.

title: baked zucchini squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Put in buttered dish.
Top with grated cheese. Bake about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken stroganoff
directions: In a skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Drain, reserving 2 Tbsp. drippings; set bacon aside.
In the drippings, cook the chicken, onion and mushrooms until the chicken is no longer pink.
Add the broth, garlic, salt, paprika, pepper and bacon.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Combine flour and sour cream until smooth; add to the skillet.
Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened.
Serve over noodles.
Sprinkle with paprika if desired. Serves 4.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let set.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch dish with butter.
Line bottom with graham crackers.
Mix pudding and milk.
Beat 2 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour 1/2 of pudding over graham crackers.
Alternate pudding and graham crackers ending with graham crackers.
Put frosting on top.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: butter cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.	Cream butter and sugar; add egg and vanilla.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Blend thoroughly. Chill.
Can roll
into 1 inch balls and flatten or sliced from roll.
Bake at 350° until edges brown for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: autumn potato gratin
directions: Arrange half of potato slices in deep 10-inch pie plate.
Put onion slices on top.
Sprinkle with chervil, summer savory, pepper, salt, half of the butter and oil.
Arrange remaining sweet potato slices in overlapping pattern around edge of pan.
Arrange remaining white potato slices in overlapping pattern in center. Drizzle remaining oil over top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes more or until golden and tender, basting occasionally with butter.
Serves 6.

title: butterscotch thins
directions: Cream butter, brown sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy; beat in egg.
Sift together dry ingredients and 1/4 teaspoon of salt; mix into creamed mixture.
Divide dough into 4 parts; make 12 balls about 1/2-inch in diameter out of each part.
Place balls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten by crisscrossing with fork tines. Bake at 375° for about 8 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: old-fashioned rolled molasses cookies(65 years)
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs, molasses and milk, then add flour, ginger, cinnamon, cloves, allspice and soda.
Mix well. Chill 2 or 3 hours.
Roll and cut to desired shapes.
Bake on a greased sheet at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: In saucepan, cook pudding and milk over medium heat until thickened and bubbling.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.

title: variations of eggs for a crowd
directions: Spray Pam in 3-quart saucepan.
Beat eggs well and add the next 6 ingredients.
(You can beat them in saucepan to save dishwashing.)
Cook on medium heat and stir occasionally to keep from sticking.
Serves 4.

title: fudge
directions: Cook sugar, butter
and milk until it forms a soft ball in a cup of
cold
water.
Take off burner; add bits, nuts and marshmallows.
Stir until smooth.
Pour onto a greased pan and cool and cut into squares.

title: pie crust, double crust
directions: Cut flour, salt and Crisco together.
Beat egg in cup.
Finish filling cup with cold water.
Add to other ingredients.

title: rice krispy treats
directions: In large bowl, microwave butterscotch morsels for 1 1/2 minutes.
Turn bowl and microwave for 1 more minute.
Stir softened morsels and add peanut butter.
When thoroughly mixed, add Rice Krispies gradually.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate for about an hour.
Cut into 2-inch squares.

title: upside-down fruit pancakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare pancake mix according to package directions.
In 10-inch pie plate, melt butter.
Spoon in fruit.
Pour pancake batter over all.
Bake 18 minutes (or until done in center).
Serve with maple syrup.

title: easy cheesy potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients in large casserole dish.
Top with grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° until brown and bubbly.

title: mud pie
directions: Crush cookies/wafers and add butter.
Mix well and press into 9-inch pie plate.
Cover with coffee ice cream.
(Make sure ice cream is soft but not runny.)
Put pie into freezer until ice cream is firm.
Top with cold fudge sauce.
Store in freezer for approximately 10 hours before serving.
Serve with whipped cream and chocolate shavings, if desired.

title: sweet and sour red cabbage
directions: Melt butter in Dutch oven.
Add onion; saute 5 minutes.
Add cabbage and apple; saute 5 minutes, until cabbage starts to wilt.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package. Saute onion in oleo.
Add broccoli, soup and milk, stirring well.
Add Cheez Whiz, let come to boil, then simmer a few minutes longer.

title: macaroni supreme
directions: Cook macaroni until tender and drain well.
Mix all ingredients with cooked macaroni and put in casserole dish.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Put sugar, eggs and buttermilk into blender. Spin until mixed, then add vanilla and melted butter; mix.
Fill pie shells with coconut.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: 24 hour lettuce salad
directions: Break lettuce into bite-sized pieces and lay in bottom of pan (glass casserole).
Over that sprinkle celery, pepper and onion. Layer frozen peas.
Mix Miracle Whip and sugar; spread over peas. Sprinkle with cheese and top with crumbled bacon.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.

title: lite brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 13 x 9-inch baking pan with nonstick cooking spray; set aside.
In large, heavy saucepan cook 1 cup chips, sugar, applesauce and margarine over low heat, stirring constantly until smooth.
Remove from heat; cool slightly.
Beat in egg whites.
Beat in remaining ingredients and chips.
Spread in prepared pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until set. Cool in pan on wire rack.
Garnish.

title: delicious pork chops
directions: Flour and pan-fry pork chops; drain fat.
Add mushroom soup, water and Mozzarella cheese.
Heat until cheese melts.
Serve.

title: flour tortillas
directions: Sift dry ingredients; add shortening, working it into the flour.
Stir in 1 cup water; knead well and form into balls the size of an egg.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Roll out to size of plate. Cook on hot ungreased griddle or skillet.
Let it cook on one side until bubbly looking.
Flip over and do same.

title: satellites
directions: Mix corn syrup and sugar in pan.
Cook over medium heat. Bring to soft ball stage.
Mix in peanut butter.
Take off heat and quickly mix in Krispies.
Press into greased 8 x 8-inch pan. Let set until cool.
Cut into squares.

title: chocolate-covered tarantulas
directions: Melt both packages of chips in double boiler over low heat. Add peanuts and noodles.
Remove from heat and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper and chill in refrigerator.

title: molasses cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and margarine together to make crumbs. Take out 1 cup for topping.

title: breakfast before
directions: Make a day ahead, refrigerate and pop in oven 45 minutes before breakfast or brunch.

title: dump cake 2
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Dump undrained pineapple into pan. Spread evenly.
Dump in pie filling and spread evenly. Dump dry cake mix onto cherry layer and spread evenly.
Sprinkle pecans over cake mixture.
Put butter over top. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes. Serve warm or cool.

title: honey bread
directions: Combine 1 cup flour and yeast in bowl of electric mixer.
Mix well.
Cut butter into small bits.
Add with salt to bowl.
Slowly pour in very warm water beating at low speed for 1 minute scraping inside of bowl often.
Add milk, honey and 2 cups flour.
Blend well for 2 minutes.
Remove bowl from mixer.
Stir in enough remaining flour to make a soft dough (about 2 1/2 cups).
Use remaining flour for kneading.
Turn dough out onto generously floured board.
Sprinkle top generously with flour.
Knead dough 5 to 10 minutes until smooth and elastic.
Use as little flour as possible.
Put dough in a lightly oiled medium size bowl.
Turn dough over once and cover with clean towel.
Put bowl in a warm place away from drafts.

title: crab cakes
directions: Break bread into small pieces and moisten with milk.
Mix all ingredients.
Shape into cakes.
Chill for at least one hour.
Fry quickly until browned.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Blend with mixer cream cheese, mayo and Good Seasons Italian package (soften cream cheese).
Unroll crescent rolls on cookie sheet and follow directions on package.
(Bake 8 to 9 minutes.) Once cooled, spread cream cheese mixture.
Top with vegetables and place in refrigerator.
Cut into pieces before serving.

title: microwave vegetable-beef soup
directions: In a 5-quart casserole, combine ingredients. Stir and cover. Set microwave to Defrost at High (10) for 60 minutes. Then cook at Medium (5) for 99 minutes.
Turn casserole 1/4 turn twice.

title: souffle casserole(using cooked chicken, turkey, shrimp or tuna.)
directions: Dice 4 slices of bread.
Place in bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix (large) bite size pieces of meat with mayonnaise, pepper, onion and celery. Spread over diced bread. Trim crusts from remaining 6 slices of bread.
Place whole slices of bread over meat mixture. Beat eggs until frothy. Add milk. Pour over bread slices.
Place in refrigerator overnight.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1/2 cup cheese.
Put mixture in dish; sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Then microwave on High for 11 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix instant pudding as directed.
Let chill 5 to 10 minutes. Fold in sour cream and Cool Whip.
Layer bowl with wafers, pudding mixture and bananas.

title: coconut pie
directions: Cook milk, sugar, egg yolks and cornstarch until thick.
Add butter, vanilla and coconut.
Pour into crust.
Whip egg whites and place on top of pie.
Bake until meringue is brown.

title: party punch
directions: Pour ginger ale over frozen punch. Garnish with apples.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Tear tortillas into pieces.
Brown beef.
Add tomatoes, onion, salt, pepper and cheese.
Mix thoroughly.
Add tortillas; mix thoroughly and place in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix together the flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Add eggs, milk and shortening.
Add corn.
Fry as pancakes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix ingredients until creamy.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Mix in cranberry sauce and pineapple; chill until set.
Whip whipping cream and sugar until stiff.
Mix in pecans; spread over salad.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and pour into buttered casserole.
Dot top of casserole with butter.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: cold corned beef sandwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Will keep in refrigerator several days. Good to mix ahead and take to beach or lake for sandwiches.

title: holiday pudding
directions: Melt butter.
Mix in flour in saucepan.
Mix fruit juice, sugar and egg and add to flour mixture.
Stir and cook until thick pudding.
Cool.
Add to fruit mixture (except bananas) .
When ready to serve, whip the cream, cut up the bananas and add to the fruit pudding mix.

title: lazy man pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix all the ingredients well. Cook at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: chinese noodle salad
directions: Shake well to pour on salad just before serving.

title: fruit pie
directions: Melt margarine in pan.
Mix flour, sugar, milk and eggs to form batter.
Pour in pan with melted margarine.
Pour fruit over batter and margarine.
Bake in 350° oven until golden brown for approximately 30 minutes.

title: sugar-free jello congeal salad
directions: Mix jello powder and cottage cheese in a bowl.
Add Cool Whip to this.
Drain juice off the pineapple, then fold in pineapple and nuts.
Put slices of mandarin oranges or strawberries on top and refrigerate.

title: country club squash
directions: Cook squash and onions
in
1/2 cup boiling water until tender.
Drain and mash.
Combine squash, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Pour into a greased 2 quart casserole.
Combine bread crumbs, cheese, butter
and
paprika.
Sprinkle
over
squash. Top with bacon crumbs.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: cheesy taco casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; pour off fat.
Add taco seasoning, kidney beans and tomato sauce and simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Cook macaroni; drain.
Stir in milk and cheese.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Toast the English muffin.
Spread each half with tomato sauce. Top with cheese.
(You can also add ham, pepperoni or your own favorite topping.)
Bake in the oven at 400° until the cheese melts.

title: sauerkraut and kielbasa
directions: Simmer all ingredients, except kielbasa, for several hours. Approximately 1/2 hour before eating, add Polish kielbasa and cook.
Serve with mashed potatoes and applesauce.

title: marcillac dream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine ingredients in mixer.
Beat at medium 4 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured pan(s).
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes in 13 x 9-inch or Bundt pan.

title: mom's ham loaf
directions: Mix well and bake slowly at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. Ham will be salty enough for all. Serves 14 to 15 servings.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain
liquid from fruit cocktail into a saucepan.
Add sugar to liquid and heat until sugar dissolves.
Then add sour cream and
mix well.
Then add fruit cocktail.
Then add food coloring (optional).
Pour into a flat container (9 x 9-inches or 13 x 9-inches) and freeze.
Cut into desired size portions.

title: my mother's noodles
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt and baking powder in large bowl.
Make a well in center of flour. Add eggs and milk.
Work to make a stiff dough. Turn out on floured board.
Knead for 10 minutes. Roll out thin. Cut into narrow strips.

title: cranberry pineapple punch
directions: Stir together first 4 ingredients until sugar dissolves. Cover and chill 8 hours.
When ready to serve, stir in ginger ale.

title: baked custard
directions: Place both milks in medium pan.
Heat over medium heat until small bubbles form around edge.
Mix egg, sugar and extract in a bowl.
Add 1 cup hot milk to egg mixture and blend. Pour this mixture back into pan of hot milk.
Stir well.

title: jojo's potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in wedges.
Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Toss potatoes in mixture until evenly coated.
Place on a baking sheet, skin side down.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: stir-fried chicken
directions: In medium bowl mix wine with 1 tablespoon cornstarch.
Add chicken and stir to coat.
Refrigerate 20 minutes to 4 hours.
Mix soy sauce, water and 1 tablespoon cornstarch.
In wok or large heavy skillet heat 2 teaspoons oil over high heat.
Add ginger and cook 15 seconds, stirring constantly.
Add green pepper and onion and stir fry 2 minutes.
Transfer to a bowl.
Add remaining 2 teaspoons oil to skillet; when hot add chicken and red peppers. Stir fry 2 to 3 minutes until chicken loses its pink color and turns white.
Add peanuts, cooked veggies and soy sauce mixture. Bring to a full rolling boil.
Serve immediately over rice.

title: hot dip bread
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream, chopped dried beef, green onions, Worcestershire sauce and garlic salt.
Thinly slice off top of French bread loaf.
Scoop out inside of bread loaf.
Fill loaf with cheese mixture.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Serve with bread pieces, chips and crackers.

title: frozen strawberry yogurt smash
directions: In a blender, puree the strawberries with the orange juice. Add the yogurt, honey, lemon juice and ice cubes; blend until slushy in consistency.
Pour into 2 stemmed glasses and garnish with a whole strawberry.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Sift the dry ingredients into a large bowl.
Combine the orange juice, shortening, water and egg; stir gradually into the dry ingredients.
Fold the chopped cranberries and walnuts into the batter and pour into a greased and floured 9 x 5 x 2 3/4-inch bread pan.
Bake for 1 hour or until a skewer inserted into the center comes out clean.

title: caramel sauce or dip
directions: Blend together all ingredients until it melts on low heat. Can be served warm over ice cream, cake or with sliced apples.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil and peel potatoes.
Cut into bite size.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir good and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: lorna doones
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Roll out to 1/2 inch thick.
Bake at 375 for 20 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Stir soups, sour cream, etc. together.
Mix in hash browns; put in buttered 8 x 12 x 2-inch casserole.
Add cheese and bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix and pour into a stem pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: veal parmigiana
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In shallow bowl, beat eggs with fork; set aside.
Place bread crumbs on sheet of waxed paper.
Dip veal in eggs; drain off excess.
Coat veal pieces on both sides with bread crumbs.
In large skillet, heat half the olive oil until hot. Over medium heat, cook veal, a few pieces at a time, until golden brown on both sides.
Remove from pan; keep warm.
Repeat with remaining oil and veal.
Place half of veal in shallow baking dish; cover with half of tomato sauce.
Sprinkle with 1/2 Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together the first three ingredients.
Work in the potato chips and flour.
Add pecans last.
Chill in refrigerator. Place small amounts on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press dough together on side of bowl with teaspoon.
Be sure cookie dough is pressed all together.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Mix white and yellow hominy, sour cream and diced chilies. Lightly grease or spray with 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Pour mixture into pan and cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Soak crumbs in hot cream.
Mix ground meat, soaked crumbs, egg yolks, seasonings and onions.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Roll in flour.
Brown in hot fat, turning to brown evenly.
Place meatballs in casserole dish with 1 or 2 tablespoons drippings and 1 tablespoon water.
Cover and bake 60 minutes in 300° oven.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Drain pineapple (save juice) and put the chunks in a casserole dish.
Heat over low flame the sugar, flour, 1/2 stick margarine and pineapple juice until thick.
Pour over the pineapple and mix. Melt 1 stick of margarine and crumble the Ritz crackers in.
Mix well.
Spread evenly over top of pineapple.
Bake at 350° until brown on top (about 20 minutes).

title: potato oven meal
directions: Place the potatoes, celery, hamburger and pepper in layers in a 3-quart casserole. Sprinkle salt and pepper over each layer. Pour tomatoes over the top, then add a layer of sliced onion. Cover casserole and bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 16 servings.

title: punch
directions: Mix and finish filling 1 gallon with water.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil sugar, Karo and water until mixture spins a thread when dripped from spoon.
Add peanuts.
Cook slowly until syrup turns light tan.
Remove from heat and stir in soda and butter. (Mixture will foam.)
Spread on two buttered cookie sheets.
Pull from edges as it cools for thinner brittle.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix all together until consistency of pie dough.
Shape into walnut size balls. Place in baking pan and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Serve warm.
Can be frozen in ball form until ready to bake.

title: rice casserole
directions: Bake in the oven for 1 hour at 350° or use the microwave. Microwave on High for 6 minutes; stir and continue cooking on Medium power for 6 minutes longer or until liquid is absorbed.

title: gingerbread men
directions: Mix all ingredients and add 1 cup flour and mix well; add 3 or 3 1/2 more cups of flour until dough is stiff enough to be rolled out on floured board.
Cut into cookies.
Bake in 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 24 men.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Cool the pudding mix.
Fold the Cool Whip and marshmallows into the pudding until just blended.
Add the fruits, slowly, just enough to blend.
Chill in the refrigerator for 24 hours before serving.

title: apple chip cake
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients.
Add the next 3 ingredients; stir.
Add vanilla and apples; stir.
Pour into large baking dish (9 x 13-inch).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: banana split pie
directions: Melt butter and combine with graham cracker crumbs.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cook in a 350° oven for 5 minutes.
Cool.

title: pink frozen salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in order listed.
May use muffin tins with liners or 8 cup molds.
Freeze.
Yields 14 to 16 servings.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix cornstarch, vinegar, sugar and beet juice together until smooth.
Mix in diced beets.
Add butter and bring to a boil. Cook until thick.

title: venison roast
directions: Soak roast 6 to 8 hours in vinegar or buttermilk.
Rinse well and remove all fat from roast.
Season.
Line a baking pan with salt pork.
Place roast in pan.
Add the juice of 1 lemon, Worcestershire sauce, onion and slices of other lemon.
Cover and cook slowly until tender.
Add a small amount of hot water as needed.
Serves 12.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Mix and beat altogether.
Put in a 9 x 13 x 2 inch pan and bake at 350 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Saute in butter the green pepper and onion.
Add meat and salt; mix well.
Cook until lightly browned.
Wash rice; spread over bottom of casserole.
Place layer of meat mixture; pour over tomato juice and bouillon over.
Bake uncovered at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: spring flowers and greens
directions: Wash greens; pat dry with paper towels.
Place in bowls or on plate.
Sprinkle herbs over and arrange flowers decoratively on greens.
Mix vinaigrette, pour over salad and toss gently.
Serve immediately.
Serves 8.

title: pineapple-coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 325° until lightly brown, about 40 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: Heat oil over medium-high heat in a heavy Dutch oven.
Add rice and next 7 ingredients, and cook, stirring often, until rice is browned.
Stir in water and tomato sauce; bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium; cover and cook 25 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Coat meat strips with flour mixture.
Brown meat in hot fat in a large frypan.
Add onion and cook until clear.
Drain off excess fat.
Add soup and mushrooms. Simmer, covered, 10 to 15 minutes.
Blend in sour cream and remove from heat.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Garnish with paprika and parsley.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pork chops
directions: In
casserole,
mix
all ingredients and pour over pork chops. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with brown rice.

title: fiesta peppers
directions: Slice peppers and onion vertically about 1/8-inch wide. Heat a 12-inch frying
pan,
then put in olive oil and garlic. Saute for a short
time
until
garlic starts to tan.
Add the remaining ingredients and
saute
until onions start to wilt a little.
I prefer it not cooked to death.
This is a tasty and colorful addition to
steaks
or
chops,
better
for you than gravy.

title: ware neck strawberry shortcake
directions: Sprinkle desired amount of sugar over strawberries and mash with a potato masher.
Cook sheet of pie crust and butter crust. When hot from the oven, cut into squares, about 3 or 4 inches. Alternate pie crust, then strawberries, then crust, ending with strawberries.
You may garnish with any whipped topping or vanilla ice cream.
You can use boxed Jiffy pie crust mix or the All-Ready pie crusts.
Just unfold, bake and butter.
Yields about 4 to 6 servings.

title: mom's fruit cobbler
directions: Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish with fruit and pour batter over it.
Sweeten fresh fruit.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Good warm or cold.

title: strawberry angel fluff cake
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water. Let this cool. Break cake into egg-sized pieces. Combine jello mixture, strawberries and whipped topping. Stir well. Add cake and fold well to coat cake. Spoon into a tube pan and chill until firm, about 4 hours. Slice. Add a dollop of whipped cream; top with a strawberry.

title: cajun pastry
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions. Preheat oven to 400°. In a medium skillet, saut next 7 ingredients. Add seasonings and mix until blended. Add crabmeat, shrimp and cooked rice. Stir to combine. Place about 1/2 cup mixture into each pie shell. Bake for 20 minutes.

title: chicken tamale pie
directions: Combine lime juice, garlic, oil, pepper, cilantro and salt; pour over chicken in a recloseable plastic bag or covered nonmetal dish and marinate 1 hour or overnight.
Cook on barbecue grill (over mesquite wood if desired) until done.
Cut chicken into strips.
To serve, place chicken on warm flour tortillas and add desired toppings.
Serve sauteed onion and pepper on the side. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: brown bag baked turkey
directions: You will need a brown grocery bag.
Rinse and dry turkey with paper towels.
Rub cavity with small amount of salt.
Stuff with stuffing.
On outside of turkey, rub with Crisco.
Do not use any shortening with salt.
Bag in brown grocery bag.
Be sure there's not any holes or tears in bag; print side of bag should be on bottom.
Bag should not touch breast of turkey.
Fold over end and seal with paper clips or staple.
Put on roaster rack oven pan. Bake at 325°.
Bake 20 minutes per pound if under 12 pounds; bake 25 minutes per pound if over 12 pounds.
No peeking.

title: stewed squash
directions: Slice squash and onion.
Place on microwaveable dish.
Dot butter on top, add salt and pepper.
Microwave 20 minutes.
Stir before serving.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: In a 9 x 12-inch covered Tupperware container or glass dish, place layers of lettuce, onion, celery, water chestnuts and peas. Mix mayonnaise with sugar and cover layers with mixture.
Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight.
One and one-half hours before serving time, add layers of tomatoes, boiled eggs, bacon and cheese.
Do not toss.
Seal tightly until serving time.
Make sure your guests dig to the bottom of the dish.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix all ingredients, except coconut, together.
Roll into balls; roll in coconut.
Store in airtight can or bag.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Mix peaches and lemon juice.
Stir together sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Mix with peaches.
Turn into a 10-inch pastry lined pie plate.
Dot with butter.
Cover with top crust.
Seal well.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 50 minutes or until brown.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Boil macaroni according to package directions.
Mix all of the ingredients and chill.

title: oven baked cube steak
directions: Sprinkle steak with sauce, pepper and small amount of salt. Roll in flour.
Brown each piece of steak in skillet with olive oil.
Have heat high enough to brown quickly.
Place in baking dish with 1/2 cup of water to cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour. This was one of Mama's old recipes.

title: potato casserole(very good)
directions: Grate potatoes into a greased 9 x 13 pan. Mix together and pour over potatoes the cream of chicken soup, margarine, sour cream, salt and onion.
Put cheese and potato chips on top. Bake 10 more minutes.

title: pineapple cheese salad
directions: Simmer sugar and pineapple until sugar is well dissolved. Cool.
Add boiling water and Jell-O.
Stir until well dissolved. Chill until just beginning to set.
When slightly firm, mix in cheese and whipped cream.
Return to bowl or mold and chill until firm.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Place butter and rice in bottom of 2-quart casserole dish. Add remaining ingredients; cover.
Bake in a moderately hot oven (375°).
Stir lightly after 40 minutes.
Continue to bake, covered, an additional 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Serves 4.
Contains about 122 calories per 1 cup serving.

title: delicious chicken
directions: Mix all together and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 30 more minutes.

title: shrimp sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Start with 3/4 cup half & half.
Mix well; continue to add half & half until you reach the consistency you desire.

title: pickled beets
directions: Wash beets.
Cook until tender; save juice.
Put beets in cold water.
Take off skin; cut into chunks.
Take some of the juice beets were cooked in and add 1 cup vinegar, 1 cup water and 1 cup sugar.
Mix together with beets.
Depending on how many beets you have to do, you have to keep adding 1 cup of everything (1 cup juice, 1 cup water, 1 cup vinegar and 1 cup sugar).
Heat until boiling.
Put into hot jars.
Enjoy!

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease pan.
Brown ground beef and onion in skillet; drain.
Stir in taco mix.
Pour in pan. Sprinkle with chilies.
Set aside.
Beat milk, baking mix and eggs until smooth, 15 seconds in blender or 1 minute with a hand mixer. Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 35 minutes.
Top with tomatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until cheese is golden brown and a knife inserted in the center comes out clean, 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sweet and sour beef stew
directions: Coat meat with seasoned flour; brown meat and onion in hot oil. Combine ketchup, brown sugar, vinegar, water and Worcestershire sauce. Stir into browned meat. Cover and cook over low heat for 45 minutes; stirring occasionally. Add carrots and more water, if needed. Cook another 45 minutes. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: houston baked beans
directions: Saute bacon and onion.
Combine all ingredients and bake uncovered at 350° for one hour.

title: chewy cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter over medium heat. Remove from heat and beat in eggs, one at a time. Add vanilla, blend in flour and stir in nuts. Pour into greased 13 x 9 inch pan and bake at 325° oven for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let set several hours or overnight. Serve with raw vegetables.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Cover beans with water and soak overnight.
Drain and cook beans in 2 quarts of water for 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients and cook slowly 3 to 4 hours or until beans are soft, stirring occasionally.
Serve over rice, if desired.

title: diabetic oatmeal date nut cookies
directions: Blend oleo and sugars well.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well. Combine dry ingredients.
Add to oleo-sugar mixture.
Add oatmeal, nuts and dates.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 to 17 minutes.

title: punch bowl dessert
directions: Bake cake on a cookie sheet until done.
Cool and cut into 1-inch squares.
Make pudding as box says.
Layer medium punch bowl with cake, candy, pudding and Cool Whip.
Repeat layers until gone. Top with a large amount of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle some crushed Skor bars on top.

title: crab-asparagus soup
directions: Cook potatoes and asparagus; set aside.
Melt margarine in pan and stir in flour, mixing until smooth.
Remove from heat and gradually add chicken broth.
Add pepper and return to heat, stirring until blended and thickened.
Slowly, add milk.
Stir in crab, potatoes and asparagus.
Heat thoroughly.
Do not boil!

title: club chicken
directions: Melt butter or margarine; blend in flour and gradually add milk and broth.
Cook and stir over low heat until thickened.
Add salt, chicken, rice and vegetables.
Pour into greased 2-quart 7 1/2 x 11-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with toasted almonds.

title: quessadilla quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 425 degrees.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan or quiche dish.
Drain juice from the can of Rotel and pour into the bottom of the pan.
Sprinkle cheese on top of this.
Beat milk, Bisquick, and eggs until mixed thoroughly; pour over the Rotel chilies and cheese.

title: south texas beans and rice
directions: Sort and wash beans.
Combine beans, water, ham hock, onion, garlic and salt in a large pot.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Remove ham hock and shred ham from bone; return to bean mixture.
Simmer until done.

title: sombrero appetizer
directions: Brown meat and put in bowl. Add the rest of the ingredients. Microwave on High for 3 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Top with diced tomatoes, sliced black olives and jalapeno peppers. Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: yummy squash
directions: Cook squash and onion in salted water; drain well.
Mash and add mayonnaise, cheese, egg, salt and pepper.
Spoon into oven dish.
Top with bread crumbs, which have been tossed with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: beef stew
directions: Put beef in casserole.
Pour soups over beef.
Add salt and pepper.
Cover and cook in oven for 2 hours at 350°.

title: applesauce jello
directions: Make Jell-O according to package using 2 cups hot and 1 3/4 cups cold water.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan (glass if you have it because it's pretty).
Add applesauce; mix well.
Add ice cream scoops and let melt.
When soft, swirl through Jell-O mixture.

title: hamburger and zucchini
directions: Wash the squash in cold water.
Put in a pot with enough water to cover; bring to a boil.
(Do not cover pan while boiling zucchini, as that would make it lose its green color.)
Drain squash and set aside to cool.
Place the ham and bacon in skillet and fry until bacon is golden color.
Add the onion and fry until it is clear and glazed.
Add the hamburger and fry until its red color has disappeared.
Remove from heat and stir in the salt, pepper, pimento and parsley.
Cut the cooled squash in half and arrange in the bottom of greased baking dish.
Place hamburger mixture over the zucchini.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: pineapple filling
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Drain pineapple and save juice.
Add pineapple and 2 tablespoons pineapple juice.
Stir.
Add cubed bread and mix well.
Place in greased 2-quart dish.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 50 minutes. Delicious with baked ham.

title: blueberry pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan.
Use mixer to cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each egg is added.
Add vanilla and beat until fluffy. Dredge berries with 1/4 cup of flour and set aside.
Sift remaining flour with baking powder and salt.
Fold into cake batter until well blended.
Gently stir in berries.
Bake for approximately 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Place pan on rack and cool in pan for 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Remove tops and seeds from peppers; cut in half.
In skillet, brown beef and cook onion until tender.
Stir in 1 cup soup, rice and seasonings.
Spoon meat mixture into peppers.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Dilute remaining soup and pour over peppers. Cover and bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until peppers are done. Remove cover and top with cheese strips.
Bake about 5 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar, soda, flour, salt and cinnamon.
Add oil, eggs and carrots.
Mix all by hand.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.
Let cool.

title: cucumber-onion salad(4 to 6 servings)
directions: Place cucumber and onion slices in salad bowl.
Combine salad oil, vinegar, sugar and pepper.
Pour over cucumber and onion; marinate 1 to 2 hours.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Beat together the sugar, shortening, egg and vanilla until fluffy.
Sift together the flour, salt and baking soda; mix in alternately with milk, stirring smooth after each addition.
Stir in rolled oats, nuts and chocolate.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheets and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: lemon peel ice cream
directions: Combine ingredients and freeze according to ice cream freezer directions.
Usually 6 cups of ice to 1 cup rock salt.
Makes 1 1/2 gallon freezer.

title: chewy chocolate-chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Beat together butter, brown sugar and sugar on high speed for 3 minutes. Add eggs and vanilla. Add flour mixture with butter mixture. Stir in chips. Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: baked bean stuffed peppers
directions: Remove seeds and stems from peppers.
Parboil peppers for 5 minutes.
Drain and cool.
Brown and cook ground beef.
Drain grease from beef.
Stir in beans and 1/2 of the French fried onion rings, catsup and mustard.
Spoon into peppers.
Place in a greased shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Then put remaining onion rings on top.
Bake another 10 minutes or until onions are hot and crisp.
(I never seem to have the onion rings on hand so just cook some chopped onion with the hamburger. I put buttered bread crumbs on top.
I cook in the microwave.)

title: homemade pimento cheese
directions: Heat the cheese and the milk on low heat.
Cut up cheese so it will melt quicker.
Stir often.
Be sure not to get too thick before setting it off to cool.
Stir until smooth.
Add the pepper; cut it into fine pieces.
Pour all the juice in the cans over the cheese.

title: filet of pork tenderloin
directions: Cut pork tenderloin into filets about an inch thick.
Place in large shallow dish.
Cover filets with the lemon pepper (top and bottom).
Set aside for an hour or more.
In heavy skillet, brown filets for 5 to 6 minutes per side.
Remove meat from skillet, add all other ingredients and bring to simmer.
Return filets to sauce and cook until well done over medium heat (about 10 minutes per side).

title: fudge frosting
directions: Combine sugar, water and chocolate in a saucepan. Stir until mixture comes to a boil. Boil for 3 minutes, stirring occasionally. Remove from stove and stir in the butter and vanilla. Then gradually blend in enough sifted powdered sugar until a good spreading consistency is reached.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Beat the eggs and add milk and crumbs.
Add corn, onions, seasoning and melted butter.
Mix together well and pour in a greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: hawaiian punch
directions: Mix all juices except ginger ale and sherbet.
Add these just before serving.
Pink punch is prettier.
Serves 40.

title: chicken with rice(serves 6)
directions: Cut chicken into strips and season with salt and pepper.
Wrap chicken with 1 to 2 pieces of bacon.

title: nana's pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add pumpkin and eggs.
Combine all dry ingredients; add along with water and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add nuts and raisins.
Put into 4 small greased pans (or 2 regular size for moister bread).
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes. Freezes well.
Warm and slice to serve.
Spread with cream cheese, if desired.

title: garlic broccoli
directions: Cook garlic in oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat, stirring constantly, until tender.
Add broccoli and next 4 ingredients.
Cover and cook 5 minutes or until crisp-tender. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Wash and slice zucchini.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Mix soup, onion, yogurt, carrots and cooked zucchini.
Melt margarine.
Add to it the stuffing mix.
Place three-quarters of stuffing in bottom of buttered casserole.
Pour zucchini mixture over stuffing mix.
Top with remaining stuffing mix.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Chop cabbage.
Melt butter.
Add flour, sugar, salt, pepper and onion.
Add vinegar and beaten egg, stirring well.
Pour over cabbage and toss.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, mustard and vinegar in a small bowl.
Pour over potatoes in a large bowl, adding eggs, pickles and onions. Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well and chill.

title: lemon-pecan cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and beat 4 minutes.
Pour half the batter in greased tube pan; sprinkle half the cinnamon-sugar mixture and pecans over batter.
Pour remaining batter in pan and sprinkle with remaining cinnamon-sugar mixture and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: delicious cookies
directions: Mix cream, sugar and butter together and add well beaten eggs. Sift flour and baking powder together.
Beat in the butter and egg mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Make into small balls.
Place on baking sheet.
Press down flat with a fork and sprinkle with sugar lightly.
Bake in moderate oven.

title: beef and barley soup
directions: In a large 3 1/2-quart kettle, heat oil over medium-high heat. Brown beef.
Add onions, carrots, celery, tomatoes, water and bouillon; bring to boil.
Cover and simmer for about 2 hours or until beef is tender.
Add barley; simmer another 50 or 60 minutes or until barley is done.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: microwave muffin pizza
directions: Place sauce on muffin.
Add cheese slices and meat.
Place on microwave dish and cook on High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.;
Makes 1 after school snack.

title: honey crusted ham
directions: Bake ham according
to	directions.
Mix
together
all ingredients.
Thirty minutes before
ham is done, spread glaze over top and sides of ham.	Continue to bake.

title: prune spice bread
directions: Soak prunes overnight, saving 2 cups water to use later.
Cut prunes into bits and cook prunes, liquid, sugar and oleo.
Cool. Sift flour, salt, spices and baking soda.
Add beaten eggs and sifted dry ingredients to cooled mix.
Pour into 2 greased 5 x 9-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° , one hour.
Yields 1 pound size loaf.

title: raisin apple bread
directions: Combine both flours and set aside.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Scald milk.
Add honey and salt to milk and gradually pour into beaten egg.
Add dissolved yeast.
Stir in wheat germ, raisins, apples and 3 cups flour.
Knead in remaining flour.

title: mushroom sauteed meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients except flour, soup and milk; shape into balls.
Roll into flour.
Brown in skillet.
Place in a large baking dish.
Dilute soup with milk or water.
Pour over meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ham dip
directions: Cream the cheese and cut ham into small pieces. Cut up black olives and green onions. Mix together. Add mayonnaise to your desired consistency. Serve with potato chips or Triscuits.

title: pineapple ham loaf
directions: Combine ham, pork, crumbs, eggs, milk and mustard.
Spray Pam on bottom and sides of heavy skillet.
Pat brown sugar over bottom. Arrange pineapple slices over sugar and put a cherry in center of each pineapple.
Cover and put over low to medium heat for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to low and cook 1 hour.

title: spicy spinach and artichoke dip
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan or skillet over medium heat. Add onion and cook until soft, about 5 minutes. Stir in spinach, artichokes, cream cheese, sour cream 3/4 cup of Monterey Jack cheese, 3/4 cup of Parmesan cheese, tabasco sauce and salt. Stir until well blended and heated through. Pour mixture into casserole dish and top with remaining cheeses. Bake at 350 degrees until cheese starts to brown, about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: ortega 7-layer dip
directions: Combine refried beans and taco seasoning mix in small bowl. Spread bean mixture in 8 inch square dish.
Top with sour cream, guacamole, cheese, salsa, chiles and green onions.
Can be prepared up to 2 hours ahead and chilled.
Serve with chips.

title: cupcake cheese cakes
directions: Preheat oven at 375°.
Mix ingredients until fluffy.
Line cupcake tins with paper baking cups.
Place a vanilla wafer in bottom of each.
Fill cups 2/3 full with cheese mixture.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Cool and top with cherry pie filling.
Chill cheese cakes.

title: sticky buns
directions: Pour boiling water over sugar, salt and Crisco; cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast, which has been dissolved in 1/2 cup lukewarm water.
Add egg and flour and mix well.
Rub surface with Crisco. Cover tightly and store in refrigerator until ready to use.
Will keep about a week.

title: muckie's baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Cook next day until medium soft (about 20 minutes).
Dice up bacon and fry crisp.

title: mustard-grilled pork chops with two-tomato salsa
directions: Combine plum tomatoes, sun-dried tomatoes, basil and cayenne pepper; set aside.
In small bowl, combine mustard, honey and garlic.
Rub mustard mixture over all surfaces of chops.
Place chops on kettle-style grill directly over medium-hot coals; lower grill hood and grill for 3 to 4 minutes.
Turn chops and grill 3 to 4 minutes or until just done.
Serve with tomato salsa.

title: pea salad
directions: Heat vinegar and sugar.
Pour over and mix with vegetables. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: mock peanut brittle
directions: Bring corn syrup and sugar to a boil.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Stir until peanut butter is melted.
Pour over corn flakes and stir until corn flakes are well coated. Press into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut and enjoy.

title: mahogany chiffon cake
directions: Combine boiling water and cocoa; cool.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Make a well in flour mixture; add oil, egg yolks, cocoa mixture and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
In a large bowl, beat egg whites and cream of tartar until very stiff.
Pour egg yolk mixture gradually over beaten whites, gently folding with rubber scraper until blended.
Pour into ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 70 minutes.
Invert on funnel; hang until cool.

title: indian fry bread
directions: Combine flour, salt and baking powder. Cut in shortening.
Add water.
Mix and knead until well mixed.
Using deep skillet or wok, fill halfway with fat. Heat until hot.
Roll balls of dough flat using rolling pin or hands until large as a small pie or saucer.
Put dough into hot fat.
Fry until golden brown on both sides.
Total cooking time is just a minute or two.

title: tropical meat salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together.
Serve in a lettuce lined serving dish or in a half pineapple shell.
Garnish with olives if ham is used or chopped walnuts if chicken is used.
Yields 6 servings.

title: mexican dipfort collins, colorado
directions: Brown sausage and ground beef and onion.
Put all ingredients into crock pot and melt.
Garlic, salt and pepper to taste.

title: creamy spinach dip
directions: Mix everything together except spinach.
Add spinach; mix well.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours or overnight.
Stir before serving.

title: finnish rye cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Stir in rye and all-purpose flours.
Mix in egg.
Work dough to 1/8-inch thickness on light floured cloth covered board. Cut into 2-inch circles.
Place cookies 1 inch apart on greased baking sheets.
Cut hole slightly off center with small bottle cap or thimble.
Prick entire cookie with a fork.
Bake until light brown, 5 to 7 minutes.
Cool on wire racks.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: cheese bake
directions: Peel wax off cheese and cover with foil.
Freeze for at least 2 hours.
Take 2 triangles of dough and press the perforations so that there are no holes pinching and pressing should do it. Cover one side of the cheese with dough.
Repeat with remaining 2 triangles and cover other side of cheese, making sure there are no openings.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
If any cheese leaks out, just let it cool slightly and push cheese under with spatula.
Serve and cut into wedges.

title: rice and beef porcupines
directions: Mix together ground beef, onion, rice, pepper salt.
Make into small balls and brown in a sauce pan.
Drain off fat and add tomato soup and water.
Cover and simmer about 50 minutes.

title: peachy pork chop barbecue
directions: Trim fat from pork chops.
Place in baking dish.
Top with peach halves.
Blend peach syrup and cornstarch.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour over the pork chops and peaches.
Cover lightly with foil and bake at 350° in oven until tender.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: quick chicken and dressing
directions: Boil fryer, debone and cut in large pieces.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Mix soups and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Dot with margarine.
Spread stuffing mix over top and pour chicken broth over all.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes or until slightly browned and bubbly.

title: snowy day soup
directions: Brown beef. Drain. Add all ingredients. Salt and pepper to taste. Simmer for 1 to 2 hours.

title: mushroom pie
directions: Slowly saute mushrooms and onions in butter or oleo.
Sprinkle little flour over it.
Add wine and mix well.
Let simmer until it cooks down.
Place onions and mushrooms in pastry shell.
Spread sour cream over top.
Cover with crust and bake at 400° for 35 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: marinated salad
directions: Drain all vegetables.
Add marinade and chill.

title: mexican salad
directions: Prepare lettuce as for tossed salad.
Drain and wash chilled beans.
Add diced tomatoes, onion, cheese and dressing.
Chill 30 minutes to 1 hour before serving.
Add crushed Fritos and mix well immediately before serving.
Serves 12.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Heat butter in skillet; add celery. Cook until celery is tender; Stir in bread and cracker crumbs. Stir in parsley.
Put layer of crumbs on bottom of baking dish. Add half the oysters; sprinkle with salt and pepper. Por half the oyster liquid and cream over the layers.
Repeat.
End with layer of crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: rice jambalaya
directions: Brown sausage and onions.
Add pepper and celery;
cook slowly for 1
hour.
Add
rice, soup mix and water; cook until rice is done.
Add
water
chestnuts last 1/2 hour of cooking. Use large pan
to
cook.
One-half
of this recipe makes a big casserole.

title: cucumber pickles(makes 7 quarts)
directions: Rinse and scald jars.
Fill with cucumbers, leaving 1/4-inch headspace at top.
After filling with cucumbers, put 1 each clove garlic in each jar, 1 each dill seed, 1 1/2 teaspoons each jar and 1 hot pepper.

title: shrimp opelousas
directions: Cook noodles as directed.
Saute onion and bell pepper in margarine.
Add shrimp and slightly saute them with onion and bell pepper.
Add soup and cheese stuff.
Add cayenne pepper to taste. Mix noodles and shrimp mixture together in casserole pan.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add chicken soup and liquid from mushrooms.
In mixing bowl, mix chicken, rice, milk, 1/2 of mushrooms, pimento, salt and pepper.
Add soup mixture.
Blend well and pour into greased baking dish.
Top with cheese and rest of mushrooms.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rum cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions except substitute water in cake mix with half milk and half rum.
Bake as directed in tube pan.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Mix together soups; fill each can with sweet milk and mix. Grate cheese.
Layer your casserole with flat and round corn tortilla chips found in the frozen food section of the grocery store.
Pour 1/2 of your soup mixture in the dish.
Sprinkle pieces of chicken over the soup.
Place pepper over chicken according to your taste.
Sprinkle cheese heavily on top.
Start over with your layers:
corn tortilla chips, balance of your soup mixture, balance of your chicken, as many jalapeno peppers as you want, balance of cheese on top and bake at 350° until cheese is bubbly, about 15 minutes.

title: house "stinker"
directions: Simmer all together in a pot and the aroma of autumn will fill your home.

title: super soup
directions: Stir together soup and cooked rice.
