This is a quick, easy favorite dish of mine.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender and blend until smooth. Makes 1 cup.

title: southwestern beef and rice
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet; drain.
Stir in everything but the rice and cheese.
Bring to a boil.
Add rice; reduce heat. Simmer for 15 minutes or until rice is tender.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda, cream of tartar, sugar and salt.
Make a well in the middle of the dry ingredients and add the beaten egg, milk and melted shortening.
Mix to combine. Lightly fold in blueberries.
Bake in muffin tin at 400°
for 18 to 20 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Melt apple jelly.
Cool slightly and add remaining ingredients except cream cheese.
Mix well; pour over 8 ounce block of cream cheese.
Serve with crackers.

title: spiced peaches with currant jelly(serve as condiment with meats.)
directions: Combine peach syrup with brown sugar, vinegar, cinnamon sticks, allspice and cloves.
Bring to boil and simmer 10 minutes.

title: stain remover
directions: Mix and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and soak garment 1/2 hour.
Wring out and wash as usual.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients; stir in next 4 ingredients. Mix well, place over boiling water and cook about 10 minutes or until mixture bubbles.
Remove from heat and cover completely. Must not be warm at all.
Can be chilled in refrigerator.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Beat in sugar.
Fold into pumpkin mixture.
Blend well.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Serve with whipped cream or honey.

title: sombrero spread
directions: Brown meat and 1/2 cup onions in skillet.
Stir in catsup, chili powder and salt.
Mash beans and add to mixture.
Heat through.
Garnish with cheese, olives and 1/2 cup onions.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: pork roast with beans
directions: Cook pork roast and garlic in 3 quarts water until meat is tender
and falls apart.
While meat is cooking, soak beans in enough
water
to
cover
beans.
When meat is done, remove from liquid.
Add
beans
and
chili
blend to liquid and cook until beans
are done.
Add chopped pork last hour of cooking.

title: tomato pepper chili sauce
directions: Heat all ingredients, except NutraSweet to boiling in large saucepan.
Reduce heat to low and simmer, uncovered, until mixture is thick sauce consistency, about 20 minutes.
Cool and stir in NutraSweet.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening, eggs until fluffy. In another bowl, add nutmeg, salt, flour; stir baking soda and vinegar into milk. Then add to dry ingredients with creamed mixture, stirring briskly until well mixed, add vanilla. Drop by teaspoonful on a greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375°
for 10 minutes. Sprinkle top with red or green colored sugar to decorate.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine last 3 ingredients.
Then add to the rest of ingredients.
(Optional:
Add 2 tablespoons finely chopped onions or a dash of onion powder.)

title: holiday salad
directions: Drain first three ingredients.
Mix together all ingredients. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
This tastes just as good the next day.

title: quick shrimp
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add shrimp and onion.
Cook and stir 3 to 4 minutes or until shrimp are light pink.
Add basil; mix well.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Yields 4 servings.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and mix well.
Put into a buttered baking pan. Mix remaining ingredients together and put on top of sweet potato mixture. Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: corn oysters
directions: In a small bowl, beat egg whites. In medium bowl, beat egg yolks.
Add corn, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper, onion, green pepper and Tabasco sauce. Stir in flour and baking powder. Fold in egg whites. Heat salad oil in large skillet.
Drop corn mixture by tablespoon in oil. Brown each side until done.
Makes about 12.

title: cathy's honey-mustard chicken
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix in honey, Dijon mustard and curry powder; add chicken pieces, turning to coat.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°, turning once midway through baking.

title: detergent painting
directions: Beat with eggbeater until it gets smooth, shiny and stiff. Let the children pile mixture onto boxes, bags or cardboard.
It will stick and pile up.

title: braised broccoli
directions: Remove tough ends of broccoli; cut broccoli into thick lengthwise slices.
Heat oil in skillet; saute scallions and broccoli.
Cover; cook 5 minutes over low heat.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: mexican wastebasket soup
directions: Combine all in large pot and simmer an hour.
Correct seasoning.
Do not drain vegetables; use this water as your liquid.
If too thick, add more water.
Serve over cubed Monterey Jack cheese in bottom of the bowl.
Serve with flour tortillas or cornbread.
Makes 15 (1 cup) servings.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Mix all together with a little cherry juice.
This not only adds color but prevents apples from turning brown.

title: banana milk shake
directions: Peel bananas, slice them into a large bowl.
Beat with blender until smooth and creamy.
Add milk, sugar, vanilla and nutmeg. Serve in tall glasses.

title: coconut cream pies
directions: Cook vanilla pudding by directions.
Remove from heat.
Add can of coconut (leave enough to sprinkle on top).
Pour into baked pie shells.

title: corned beef sandwich filling
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Makes enough filling for 4 sandwiches.

title: creamy chicken bake
directions: Place chicken breasts in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with cheese.
Combine soup and milk; spread over cheese.
Toss melted butter with stuffing mix and sprinkle over top of chicken.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix cheese, mayonnaise, mushroom soup, mushrooms with juice, pimento with juice, sugar and curry powder.
Add cooked, drained and rinsed macaroni.
Put into casserole dish.
Top with crumbled Ritz crackers and 1 stick margarine, cut in small pats.

title: easy no-bake pumpkin pie
directions: Mix milk and pumpkin. Beat in pudding and spices. Fold in whipped topping. Spoon into baked graham cracker crust. Chill in refrigerator.
Top with additional whipped topping.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in skins until done.
Drain, peel and cut into small cubes.
Add bacon, cheese, mayonnaise, onions and salt.
You may need to add extra mayonnaise to coat potatoes.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for about 30 minutes, or until cheese is bubbling.

title: cheap charlie stew
directions: Brown the meat with the flour.
Drain.
Put meat in crock-pot. Add water, wine, stew seasoning and the frozen vegetables for seasoning.
Mix.
Cook on high until gravy is bubbling.
Add frozen stew vegetables.
Cook on low setting for at least 4 hours. It's so good, you won't have any problem with leftovers.
tags: frozen stew vegetables from freezer case of your local supermarket

title: orange molded jello
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add sherbet and mix well.
Add mandarin oranges and cherries.
Fold in heavy cream mixture.
Pour into oiled jello mold.
Chill overnight.
(You can also mix jello flavors, sherbet and fruits.)

title: chili taco casserole
directions: Crumble chips up.
Layer bottom of 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Pour chili over this.
Put another layer of chips, then pour picante sauce over this. Add final layer of chips. Bake in a 350° oven for about 30 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: oyster rice
directions: Cook onion, garlic and bell pepper.
Cook slowly in a little wesson oil for about 10 minutes.
Add ground beef, sausage, salt and pepper.
Continue cooking slowly, stirring often until it begins to brown.
Add drained oysters and let cook for 20 minutes or until most of the water from oyster is gone.
Drain, then add rice to mixture.
Blend well.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in casserole dish.
Top with 2 slices of bacon.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: gingerbread
directions: Combine egg, sugar, molasses, butter and water; mix well.
In a large mixing bowl, stir together flour, baking soda, ginger and salt.
Add molasses mixture.
Beat until well mixed.
Pour into a greased 8-inch square baking pan or loaf pan.
Bake in 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Serve warm with whipped topping.
Makes 9 servings.

title: spinach dip
directions: Drain spinach through colander until no water remains (press using food handler gloves).
Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Chill.
Serve with cut up vegetables, crackers, party size breads or bagel chips.
Kids love it!

title: lazy woman's pie
directions: Arrange the following ingredients in layers in a long, flat casserole.
Arrange in order listed.
Do not stir.
Place the cherry pie filling, crushed pineapple, butter (melted) and yellow cake mix.
Bake for about 1 hour or less, until bubbly, in a 325° oven.

title: golden citrus punch
directions: In large punch bowl, combine juices, water and sugar; stir until sugar dissolves.
Just before serving; add club soda and ice.
Makes 3 3/4 quarts.

title: apple walnut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Mix and sift flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and mace; add gradually.
Stir in vanilla, apples and walnuts.
Batter will be stiff.
Spoon into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Let cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove to rack.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients together with hands until combined.
Form into small balls the size of a walnut.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheets at 350° for 20 minutes.
Can be frozen and reheated.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Melt butter and add brown sugar.
Pour into bottom of Bundt pan.
Pour in nuts.
Melt butter; add sugar and cinnamon.
Dip frozen dinner rolls into mixture and arrange in Bundt pan.
Pour remaining sugar mixture over rolls.
Let rise.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven at 325°.
Beat first 3 ingredients until creamy. Add next 7 ingredients and beat until smooth.
Add last three ingredients.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pan for approximately 45 minutes (check with toothpick).

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Cut rhubarb in fine pieces and lay on bottom of pie crust. Then add sugar, salt, flour, milk, egg yolks and butter, beaten over the rhubarb pieces in pie crust.
Bake at 350°.
When custard is set, cover it with the egg whites and sugar, beaten.
Bake to a delicate brown.

title: broiled venison steak
directions: If venison is strong, marinate in salad oil and lemon juice for 2 hours.
Before cooking, brush generously with oil; place on preheated broiler rack and broil 7 to 10 minutes on each side at 550°.
Season with salt and paprika and serve on a hot platter garnished with mushrooms, parsley and watercress.
Serves 4.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients. Measure juice, rind and shortening. Add hot water to make 3/4 cup liquid. Add this and egg to dry ingredients. Mix well but do not beat. Add cranberries and nuts. Pour into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan, greased on bottom only. Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: snowflake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, butter, egg and flavoring well, stirring together; blend dry ingredients into shortening mixture.
Chill one hour. Heat oven to 400°.
Roll dough 1/8-inch thick on floured board; cut small stars.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet for 6 to 8 minutes or lightly browned.
Cool.
Put two cookies together with melted sweet chocolate.
Add dab of chocolate and sprinkle of chopped pistachio nuts on top.

title: stuffed jalapeno peppers
directions: Mix all ingredients together except bread crumbs.
Stuff peppers with mixture.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 300 degrees for 40-46 minutes.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients into a batter and fry in hot cooking oil until golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake pastry shell 8 minutes; remove from oven.
Reduce temperature to 350°.
Cut 6 slices of American cheese into pieces; set aside.

title: sopaipillas(mexico)
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Cool scalded milk to room temperature. Combine yeast with milk.
Make a well in center of dry ingredients.
Add liquid.
Work into a dough.
Knead dough 15 to 20 times.
Let rest for about 10 minutes.

title: hot cabbage wieners
directions: Cut and quarter cabbage.
Put in pot and cover 3/4 of the way with water.
Salt to taste.
Cook until half done.
Add hot dogs, peppers and fennel.
Cook until tender.
Serve.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except crackers in large bowl.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Crumble crackers mixed with some melted margarine over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until done (drain).
Slice thin.
Add bouillon cubes to one cup boiling water; let dissolve.
In a bowl, mix oil, vinegar, parsley and onion.
Put a layer of sliced potatoes in a separate bowl; spoon on some of the mixture from the other bowl. Continue until all potatoes and mixture are used.
Add salt and pepper.

title: baked chicken
directions: Mix the Bisquick and the paprika in a bag.
Shake the chicken in the bag and place in a shallow baking pan.
Cook at 425° for 50 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix and cook at 325°.

title: fruit pizza cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Divide into half and press into pizza pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 450°. Let the cake completely cool.
Top with Cool Whip and fruits of your choice.

title: finger jello
directions: Add Knox gelatine to boiling water; set aside.
Add jello, cold water and sugar to saucepan.
Heat until boils.
Stir until dissolved.
Take off heat when it boils.
Add another cup of cold water.
Mix together with unflavored gelatine.
Pour into 2 (13 x 9-inch) pans.
Cool 2 to 3 hours.
Cut into cubes or use cookie cutters for shapes.
Better than Jigglers.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Put all ingredients into crock-pot on low, stirring occasionally, until broccoli is tender, approximately 6 hours.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together and serve with choice of fruit.

title: slow boat to china
directions: Add onions and celery to meat.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Cook together.
In a 2-quart casserole, mix rice, soy sauce, soup and water.
Mix well and add hamburger mixture to this.
Bake at 300° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: mixed vegetable salad(a burmese vegetable tray, known as assay-tana)
directions: Deep-fry onions and sliced garlic (separately), until golden. Drain and let cool.
Lightly crush the onions.
Reserve 2 Tbsp. of oil in which the garlic was fried.
Set aside.
Pour vinegar and water in an open pot; stir in salt, turmeric, and msg and let mixture boil.
Boil and strain all the veggies, one variety at a time, until tender-crisp.
(Boil tomato as the very last vegetable.)
Place all the vegetables on a platter.
Sprinkle with toasted sesame seeds, crushed onions, fried garlic and 2 Tbsp. reserved oil.
Add more salt per taste.
Mix well before serving. Serve at room temperature.

title: arroz con buo
directions: First, you take the corn oil.
Place it in a saucepot to heat. Then you take the chopped garlic and diced onion (keep on low flame).
Saute until they brown slightly.
Then you add in the package of Goya Sazon.
Stir and wait about 12 minutes, then add 1 tablespoon of fresh parsley and 1 can of tomato sauce (Goya).
Let simmer for about 5 minutes in the same pot.
Cook 1 pound chicken breast sauteed until brown with other ingredients, then add 2 tablespoons of Goya seasoning, then add 2 cups of water.
Let cook for about 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is done.
Serve over a white bed of rice.
Enjoy.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients (except bacon) together and place in baking dish.
Cover with strips of bacon and bake at 350° until bacon is crisp.

title: sparkling harvest cider
directions: In punch bowl, combine cider, lemon juice and sugar.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Chill.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.
Garnish as desired.
Serve over ice.
Yield: 3 quarts.

title: good chocolate pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Add both milks.
Cool, slowly stirring often and well until thickens.
Add slightly beaten egg yolks.
Cook about 1 minute.
Add butter and vanilla.
Cook about 2 to 3 minutes more, until smooth and thick.
Cool well.
Add to baked pie shell.

title: corn bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients, then add liquids.
Grease an 8-inch square pan or muffin pan and bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and Spry.
Add sugars and eggs.
Add flour, cream of tartar, soda and vanilla.
Roll in small balls and flatten on cookie sheet with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Mix together and cook in heavy pot for 6 to 8 hours.
Cook slowly and stir often.
One hour before finished, add loose hamburg or meat balls.

title: party o's
directions: Heat oven to 275°.
Combine cereal, pretzel sticks and nuts in ungreased oblong pan (13 x 9 x 2-inches). Heat butter in 1-quart saucepan until melted.
Remove from heat, stir in Worcestershire sauce, paprika and garlic salt.
Pour over cereal mixture, tossing until thoroughly covered.
Bake 30 minutes, stirring constantly.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes
about
5 minutes and drain.
Mix most of margarine
with
potatoes.
Then
mix with sour cream, onions, cream of chicken soup, Cheddar cheese, salt and pepper.
Place in large casserole dish.
Mix remainder of margarine with corn flakes which
have
been
crushed.
Place
on
top
of
potato mixture. Cook in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: animelles
directions: Pour boiling water over the rest of the ingredients and stir until all the salt has dissolved and allow to cool.

title: sensational double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar with wire whip until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping and spread over crust.
Pour 1 cup milk in bowl and add pudding.
Beat with whip until well blended for 1 to 2 minutes.
Let stand 3 minutes.
Stir in pumpkin and spices.
Mix well and spread over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: cherry bar cookies
directions: Spread 2/3 batter in lightly greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Spread 1 large can cherry pie filling on top.
Drop remaining batter by teaspoons or pipe with cake decorator on top of pie filling. (Filling will not be covered).
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cranberry cookies
directions: Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Cream margarine (room temperature).
Add flour, salt and vanilla and mix well.
Stir in
nuts.
Bake on an ungreased pan in a moderate oven at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Roll in confectioners sugar while still warm.

title: soy marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Makes enough marinade for 2 pounds of meat.
Marinate
meat in a nonmetallic container.
Marinate in refrigerator
for
hours
or 2 hours at room temperature before cooking.

title: tasty pretzels
directions: Melt oleo in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put onion soup in melted butter.
Stir well.
Put broken pretzel pieces in soup and butter mix.
Stir well with a turner.
Bake at 200° for a metal pan or 175° for a glass dish for 2 hours.
Stir every 20 minutes.

title: squash relish
directions: Grind the first 3 ingredients; mix with salt.
Refrigerate overnight.
Drain and rinse twice.
Add the remaining ingredients to the first preparation; cook for 30 minutes, stirring often. Put in hot jars and seal.

title: macaroni and cheese deluxe
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese according to package directions. While macaroni is cooking, brown ground beef; drain.
Add onion and seasonings.
Add the can of soup and 1/2 cup milk to meat and onion.
Cook for 3 to 5 minutes.
Grease casserole dish; place macaroni and cheese on bottom of dish.
Pour 1/2 meat and soup mixture over macaroni and cheese; repeat.
Top with cheese slices and buttered noodles.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix and serve.
Marshmallows will soften and mellow if salad is mixed ahead.

title: corn and green bean casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in a large bowl and spread into a large casserole baking dish.
Mix last 2 ingredients well and spread over casserole.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until bubbling.

title: sweetheart fudge pie
directions: Cream the butter.
Gradually add brown sugar, beating at medium speed of an electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add melted chocolate, coffee granules and rum extract; mix well.
Stir in flour and 1 cup chopped walnuts.
Pour mixture into pastry shell. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Cool completely.
Chill.
Garnish, if desired.
Yields one 9-inch pie.

title: triple chocolate cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine cake mix, melted butter or margarine and egg in a large bowl.
Stir in all 3 chocolates and pecans.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 11 minutes.
Cool 1 minute on baking sheet.
Remove to cooling rack.

title: stroganoff superb
directions: Brown meat slowly in oleo.
Add onion, mushrooms and seasonings.
Cook until tender.
Add cream cheese and milk. Continue cooking, stirring until cheese melts.
Serve over noodles.

title: lorri's chile relleno casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Beat half and half with eggs and flour until smooth.
Split open chiles, rinse out seeds and drain on paper towels.
Mix cheeses, reserve 1/2 cup of cheese for topping.
Make alternate layers of remaining cheeses, chiles and egg mixture in casserole dish.
Pour tomato sauce over top and sprinkle with reserved cheese.
Bake 1 1/4 hours or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: swiss steak
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Sift together.
Put in deep dish.
Coat steaks on both sides and pound in with side of saucer. Cut steak in serving size pieces.
Brown in oil in Dutch oven. Do not crowd.

title: french cherry pie
directions: Cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla together.
Whip cream and fold in carefully.
Pour into shell.
Spread evenly.
Cover with cherry pie filling.
Chill thoroughly.

title: blueberry dump cake
directions: Layer ingredients as listed in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown!
Great when served with ice cream.

title: praise the lord soup
directions: Simmer all together for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serve in soup bowls and top with sour cream, chopped olives, green pepper, onions and Cheddar cheese.

title: frankfurter rice bake
directions: Save 1/2 cup of cheese for top.
Cut hot dogs in small pieces and combine rest of ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix.
Place into casserole dish.
Sprinkle rest of cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: crazy crust apple pie
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt, sugar, egg, shortening and water.
Mix and spread over bottom of pan.
Put apple filling, lemon juice and cinnamon in center of dough.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 425°.

title: never enough salad
directions: Wash, drain and cut up the lettuce.
Add rest of ingredients to taste.
Top with croutons.

title: brownie banana split pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix brownie mix as directed on package. Place parchment paper on 13 or 15-inch baking stone.
Pour mixture on paper and spread into circle, leaving 3/4-inch all around.
Do not bake without parchment.
May also be baked on pizza pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until set.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Spread over brownie crust.
Top with fruit and nuts.
Drizzle syrup over pizza.
Chill.
Cut into wedges.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: *Shortening and eggs must be at room temperature!

title: lasagna
directions: Simmer browned hamburger, tomatoes and sauce for 45 minutes. Cook noodles.
Layer noodles, hamburger sauce, 1/2 cup cottage cheese, 1/2 Mozzarella; layer again. Top with Parmesan cheese. Bake 30 minutes at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: chow mein casserole
directions: Brown the meat.
Add onions and celery; cook until vegetables are transparent.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Pour into a greased casserole, top with crushed noodles and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: crispy bun sticks
directions: Cut each bun half lengthwise (to make a total of 12 pieces). Place pieces on baking sheet.
Brush each bun stick lightly with salad dressing on all sides, using about 1 teaspoon for each piece. Bake at 375° until lightly browned, 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 12 bun sticks.

title: mom's pumpkin pie
directions: Heat butter, pumpkin and brown sugar until butter melts (set aside).
Beat flour, sugar and eggs hard.
Mix with pumpkin mixture.
Then add milk, water, vanilla, salt, pepper and cinnamon (on top).
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then 375°.

title: betty's potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in large casserole.
Chill for at least 6 hours or overnight.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: cucumber and orange salad
directions: Peel, halve and seed cucumber.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices. Working over a bowl to collect juices, peel 2 oranges with a paring knife, cutting right down to the flesh to remove all white pith. Cut sections away from membrane.
Measure 3 tablespoons juice.
If necessary, squeeze more juice from the third orange.
Combine cucumber, orange sections, juice and 1/8 teaspoon salt.
Toss to coat.

title: hamburger and rice
directions: Cook hamburger and add rest of ingredients.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour, covered.
The last 15 minutes, uncover and top with chow mein noodles.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix well; chill.
Very attractive salad; great for holiday buffets.

title: buttermilk fruit salad
directions: Mix pudding mix and buttermilk.
Beat with electric beater until thick.
Add Cool Whip and mix well.
Add fruit.
Mix well. Can add nuts, if desired.
Stir well and chill.

title: dilly casserole bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast over warm water. Stir to dissolve. Heat cottage cheese to lukewarm. Combine in mixing bowl with sugar, onion, butter, dill seed, salt, soda, egg and yeast.
Add flour, a little at a time, to make a stiff batter, beating well after each addition. Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled, 50 to 60 minutes.
Stir down with 25 vigorous strokes.

Turn into well-greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Cover and let rise in warm place 30 to 40 minutes or until almost doubled. Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes until rich brown and sounds hollow when tapped.
Cover with foil the last 15 minutes to prevent excessive browning, if necessary. Remove from pan and cool on wire rack. Makes 1 loaf.

title: ham and cheese crescent pockets
directions: Heat oven to 375 degrees. Separate dough into 4 rectangles; firmly press perforation to seal. On ungreased cookie sheet press each crescent roll to form 7 x 5 rectangle. Place one ham slice and one cheese slice on each rectangle. For each rectangle, fold dough in half over filling. Press edges to seal. Bake 10 to 13 minutes or until down.

title: sweet-sour chicken
directions: Brown chicken in butter in large skillet.
Cover; simmer 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove chicken; set aside.
Drain pineapple; reserve syrup.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in skillet.
Gradually stir in vinegar, soy sauce and reserved syrup.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add pineapple, green pepper, onion, mushrooms and reserved chicken.
Cover and simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all the ingredients except shrimp together well with spoon or mixer.
Add clean, dry, crumbled shrimp and stir into other ingredients.
Serve with or on crackers of your choice.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: In a large skillet, saut onion and green pepper in butter until tender. Add tomatoes, mushrooms, olives and oregano. Add cooked ground beef. Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes. Place half of spaghetti in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish sprayed with Pam. Top with half of the

meat mixture. Sprinkle with 1 cup of Cheddar cheese. Repeat layers. Mix the soup with water until smooth and pour over the casserole. Sprinkle with the Parmesan cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Combine jello with 2 cups boiling water.
Add 1 cup cold water.
Add crushed pineapple, strawberries and nuts. Put half of mixture in dish.
Top with layer of sliced bananas.
Refrigerate until slightly set.
Spread sour cream over mixture.
Top with remaining of fruit mixture and refrigerate.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown meat in skillet; drain well.
Saute onion and pepper; add to meat mixture.
Add soup and mix well.
Pour into a Pyrex dish.
Layer with cheese.
Arrange Tater Tots on top.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until cheese melts and Tater Tots brown.

title: breakfast scones
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Work in butter with fingers.
Add eggs and enough cold water to make a soft dough. Turn onto lightly floured board and pat out, keeping sheet 1-inch thick.
Cut into rounds or squares.
Fold over double and brush with milk.

title: wonderful old fashioned pound cake
directions: Cream salt, sugar, shortening and margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well.
Add flour, milk and water a little at a time.
Mix well, then mix in flavoring.
Pour in greased and floured tube cake pan.
Place cake in cold oven.
Turn oven temperature to 325° and bake cake for 1 1/2 hours.
Do not open door until done!

title: spaghetti sauce recipe(from nerone, italy)
directions: In a large saucepan, add some extra virgin olive oil on a low to medium heat. When warmed, add the chopped bacon and cook until very well done. Next, add the carrots and tomato paste and stir frequently. You will have a very thick preparation, but keep going. Add the bay leaf, onion and crushed rosemary and stir frequently. Now add the chopped celery and continue to cook, stirring frequently. When thoroughly warmed, add the Pomi tomatoes and the basil leaves because you will need the moisture content to start the melding of these ingredients. Lower the heat and cover.

title: cocktail meat balls or frankfurters
directions: Mix beef, bread crumbs, egg and salt; shape into 50 small meat balls (1/2-inch).
Place in shallow baking pan (13 x 9 x 2-inches).
Broil until browned; turn once.
Spoon off fat.

title: party ham rolls
directions: Mix mustard, butter and poppy seed.
Cut rolls in half; spread mixture on each cut side.
Place a small amount of ham and Swiss cheese on bottom of each roll.
Cover with top half of roll. Place rolls back in the foil pan that they came from and wrap with foil.
Bake at 300° for 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese melts. Yield: 3 1/2 dozen.

title: phyllo sausage egg bake
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon margarine in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add pepper, onion and mushrooms.
Cook until tender. Remove from skillet.
In same skillet, brown sausage until no longer pink; drain.
Add mushroom mixture to sausage.
In medium bowl, beat eggs slightly; stir in cheese and mushroom-sausage mixture.
In another bowl, combine broccoli, Ricotta cheese and parsley flakes.
Heat oven to 350°.
Unroll phyllo sheets; cover with plastic wrap.
Place 1 sheet in ungreased 13 x 9-inch (3-quart) baking dish, folding to fit.

Brush with melted butter. Continue layering and brushing with butter 4 additional sheets. Spread half of mushroom-sausage mixture evenly over phyllo dough. Layer and brush with butter 5 more phyllo sheets.
Spread with all of the broccoli mixture.
Layer and brush with butter 5 more phyllo sheets.
Spread with remaining mushroom-sausage mixture. Layer and brush with butter 5 remaining phyllo sheets.
Score top of phyllo dough in diamond shape.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until puffed and golden brown.
Makes 9 to 12 servings.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate a day before serving.

title: soup appetizer
directions: Heat all together. Serve in little cups with dab of butter on top as an appetizer. Good to serve with little cheese crackers.

title: lemon sponge pie(in memory of betty marie covington)
directions: Cream butter, add sugar and egg yolks.
Beat well.
Add flour, salt, lemon juice, grated rind, and milk.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites and pour into unbaked pie shell.

title: donna's cheese ball
directions: Chop beef and onions up fine.
Add cream cheese and 1/2 Cheddar cheese.
Mix in Accent and garlic salt.
Roll in remaining cheese.
Serve with crackers.

title: chicken fried steak
directions: Pound steak to 1/4-inch.
Cut into pieces.
Stir together egg and milk; combine cracker crumbs, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Dip meat into egg mixture, then in cracker crumbs.
In skillet, brown meat in hot oil, turning once.
Cover and cook over low heat for 45 to 60 minutes or until tender.

title: smokestack restaurant baked beans
directions: Combine and bake (uncovered) for 60-75 minutes (350°) or cook on low in crock pot for 6-8 hours.
(Remove lid last hour.)

title: barbecue
directions: Brown beef and onion together.
Mix all together and cook on low heat in slow cooker for 2 to 3 hours for best flavor.

title: lowfat spanish rice with smoked sausage
directions: Combine the bell pepper, onion, and broth.
Cook until peppers and onions are tender.
Add sausage, rice, tomato sauce, water, salt, and black pepper.
Cover and cook over low heat for about 8 to 10 minutes or until the rice has absorbed the liquid. Taste and adjust seasoning, if needed.
Makes 6 generous servings. with about 1 gram of fat per serving.

title: nanny's ripe tomato pickles
directions: Add salt to chopped vegetables.
Mix and let drain 2 hours. Boil remaining ingredients.
Add chopped ingredients.
Cook until thick.
Put in sterile jars and seal.

title: mexican pinwheels
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread over shells.
Roll and wrap tight in Saran Wrap.
Refrigerate several hours.
Slice 1/2 to 1-inch thick.
Dip in salsa.

title: three-colored macaroni salad
directions: Cook
macaroni	according to directions.
Drain and add cold water
and drain again.
Add the rest of the ingredients. Add salami, pepperoni, broccoli or any other meats or vegetables you prefer.

title: raspberry dessert
directions: Bring the applesauce to a boil.
Add the jello.
Carefully fold in the berries.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour pineapple into cake mix.
Pour into 13 x 9 cake pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes until top is brown.
Cut into 12 servings.

title: my sister cindy lou's sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Mix in sifted dry ingredients.
Roll dough on floured surface to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut in fancy shapes to appeal to children.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: italian cream cake
directions: In a
small
bowl,
add buttermilk and soda; let stand. Beat egg whites until stiff.
Cream margarine, shortening and sugar; add
egg
yolks,
one at a time, to sugar mixture.
Add flour
and buttermilk
alternately.
Toast pecans and coconut and add
to flour
mixture
along
with vanilla.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes in 3 (8-inch) greased and floured cake
pans. Turn
out of pans and cool on wire racks. Frost with Italian Cream Frosting.

title: curried pork with vegetables
directions: Cut garlic, pepper, onions and celery into small pieces; saute in butter or margarine.
In a separate pan, saute the pork or chicken, cut into strips.
When the vegetables are tender and the meat is browned, add both together.
Add the seasonings, along with the almonds and simmer for about 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve with rice or pasta.
Steamed or candied carrots would compliment well.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar until smooth.
Add eggs, mixing until blended.
Add pecans and water.
Mix well.
Add vinegar last. Pour into pie shell and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: green bean salad
directions: Cook green beans until tender, adding salt to taste.
Drain. Mix beans, onion and pimento.
Mix together salad oil and lemon juice.
Add to vegetables.
Top with crisp bacon (crumbled). Serve warm.

title: rice with carrots
directions: Soak the rice in hot water for 5 to 10 minutes and rinse well. Fry in the oil for 5 minutes with the dark red chile pepper and the garlic.
Add the finely chopped carrots and one whole washed carrot.
Add the chicken broth and parsley; salt to taste.
Simmer for 5 to 10 minutes at low heat.
Put in a container with the other carrots and rest of the chile pepper.
Mix in tuna.
Enjoy yourself and lick your fingers happily.

title: chicken and stuffing casserole
directions: About 1 1/2 hours before serving, in 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat, in hot salad oil, cook half of chicken pieces with 1/2 teaspoon salt until chicken is golden.
Remove to medium bowl.
In drippings, brown remaining chicken with 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Remove to bowl.

title: manhattan clam chowder
directions: Place first 6 ingredients and seasonings in a large pot.
Add water until pot is 2/3 full. Over medium heat, cook until celery and carrots are almost soft, about 20 minutes.
Add potatoes* and continue cooking about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: angel food candy
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and vinegar in large saucepan.
Cook until 300° on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat and stir in 1 tablespoon baking soda.
The reason you use a large pan is it foams up when you put in baking soda.
Pour into buttered cake pan.
When cool, break apart and dip in milk chocolate.

title: peanut butter eggs
directions: Mix powdered sugar, peanut butter and vanilla with mixer until very smooth.
Then melt the Hershey's Kisses until smooth.
Shape peanut butter mixture into an egg shape, then dip one side into Hershey's syrup.
Leave to harden, then turn over and repeat on other side and leave to harden.

title: marinated chuck roast
directions: Pierce roast all over on both sides.
Place in casserole. Combine oil, catsup, wine vinegar, salt, pepper and garlic; pour over roast.
Cover and marinate 12 to 18 hours.

title: doughnuts supreme
directions: Split doughnut.
Put slice of cheese between.
Add brown sugar on top and in doughnut hole.
Put cherry half (or whole) in center.
Put in oven or microwave until cheese and sugar melts.

title: marinated garden salad
directions: Quarter large potatoes; halve smaller ones.
Cut beans in half (you should have about 2 cups).
In a 4 1/2-quart Dutch oven, cook potatoes, beans and carrots in lightly salted boiling water for 15 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Drain in large strainer.
Transfer the vegetable mixture to serving bowl; pour dressing over vegetables and let stand for 10 minutes to cool.
Chill overnight or for several hours.
Season with pepper if desired.
Makes 12 servings.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef, add taco sauce, kidney beans and simmer 15 minutes.
Toss together all other ingredients except tortilla chips.
Add beef mixture.
Toss again.
Crunch chips all over. Serve with extra taco sauce.

title: fig cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add cooking oil.
Beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, alternating with milk.
Add figs and vanilla. Bake at 350° in a Bundt pan for about 1 hour.
Grease and flour pan.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onions.
Put cooked noodles in a casserole.
Add pizza sauce, tomato sauce, mushroom soup, salt and pepper.
Mix together; add beef on top.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake until bubbly at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: missouri 7-up cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter, then add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour alternating with 7-Up.
Add flavoring and bake in a Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cauliflower kugel *
directions: Wash cauliflower and separate into large florets.
Bring water to a boil.
Add salt and cauliflower and simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes until tender.
Drain and mash.
Preheat oven to 350°. Saute onions in oil.
Cook until soft and lightly browned. Combine the onions with the cauliflower; add pepper, eggs and wheat germ.
Place in greased 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle top with cornflake crumbs.
Bake 45 minutes.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: beef and noodle soup
directions: Brown beef in large skillet.
Stir.
Add water, onion and basil.
Simmer until meat is tender.
Add soup, milk and noodles.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix well.
In mixing bowl, beat eggs, then pour in hot water (hot water will cook eggs if not beaten well).
Pour into pie shell and bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes.
It will shake; it's usually done.

title: delicious ham salad
directions: Mix ingredients well. Good for sandwiches.

title: chili mexican casserole
directions: Start with butter tortillas.
Cover with meat, beans and chili mixture.
Layer with cheese.
Repeat layer again.
After layers are done, pour tomato sauce on top and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for at least 1 hour.

title: crustless cheese cake
directions: Beat above ingredients together until smooth.
Pour into buttered 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until puffy or brown around edge.
Cool at room temperature for about 20 minutes.
(It could sink slightly during this period.)

title: chicken okra gumbo
directions: Brown chicken; remove from pot.
Add to this pot the okra, onions and garlic.
Sprinkle flour over all.
Cook over low flame, stirring constantly (okra burns easily); cook until oil comes over the top.
Add browned chicken and one quart of water; let simmer until the consistency of thick soup.
Serve with rice.
Just as good with shrimp or crab.

title: shrimp artichoke casserole
directions: In bottom of a well-greased 1 1/2-quart casserole, place artichoke hearts and cover with shrimp.
In 1/2 stick butter, saute the mushrooms 6 to 8 minutes.
Pour over shrimp.
Melt remaining 1/2 stick butter. Add flour and cook over low heat 3 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Gradually add cream and milk, cooking until thick. Add salt, pepper, sherry and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir until smooth.
Pour over casserole. Top with cheese and paprika.
Bake 25 minutes until light brown and bubbly.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Sift flour in large bowl.
Make up like biscuits.
Make dough real hard.
Pinch off in real small pieces.
Flatten out on cookie sheet and bake until brown.

title: german zucchini
directions: Stir-fry zucchini, onions and green pepper in oil until transparent.
Mix lemon juice, brown sugar and catsup and pour onto vegetables.
Simmer until tender and crisp.

title: warm or cold potato salad
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Salt to taste.
Boil until well done. Drain.
Mix celery, onion, pickle, olives, eggs and dill weed with the mayonnaise.
Pepper to taste.
Serve immediately.
This is best while still warm but is also good refrigerated as any other potato salad.
Use only fresh-cooked potatoes.

title: new macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare macaroni to package directions. Drain macaroni and return to pot.

title: carrot pumpkin bars with orange icing
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease a 15 x 10 x 1 inch pan; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, stir together the flour, baking powder, orange peel, baking soda, and salt.
Set the flour mixture aside.
In a medium bowl combine eggs and brown sugar. Stir in pumpkin, oil, milk, and vanilla.
Then stir in carrots and chopped walnuts or pecans.
Add egg mixture to flour mixture, stirring with a wooden spoon until combined.
Spread batter into the prepared pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until a wooden toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on a wire rack.
Spread with Orange Icing.
Cut into triangles or bars.

title: light never-fail pie crust
directions: Cut margarine and flour until crumbly.
Add egg, vinegar and ice water; mix well.
Form into ball.
Divide into 3 portions and roll out.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes for baked shell.

title: grandma lawson's lemon-lime jello salad
directions: Make Jell-O by dissolving both Jell-O packages in 2 cups boiling water.
(Note:
use juice drained from pineapple plus enough water to make 2 cups.)
Add remaining ingredients and mix. Chill until set.

title: finger jello
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Mix Knox gelatine and cold water together.
Mix both together and set in refrigerator.
Great for kids!!!!!!

title: grandma's tea cakes
directions: Mix up like biscuits.
Cook until brown.

title: easy deep dish pizza
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Lightly grease jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch or cookie sheet.
Mix baking mix and water until soft dough forms.
Gently smooth dough into ball on floured surface. Knead 20 times.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a large bowl, blend cake mix, cinnamon, cloves, zucchini, buttermilk, oil and eggs at low speed until moistened.
Beat 2 minutes at high speed.
Pour in prepared pan.
Sprinkle with nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: door county appetizer
directions: Brown beef and pork.
Add oregano and cheese.
Stir over low heat until melted.
Spread over cocktail rye slices.
Bake at 400° to 425° for 10 minutes or until bubbly.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: In a shallow buttered baking dish (9 x 9 x 2-inches), place 1/4-inch layer of cracker crumbs.

Moisten well with 3/4 cup of medium white sauce. Add a layer of grated American cheese (1/2 cup), a layer of finely chopped, cooked ham (1 cup), then sprinkle with a small jar of pimento and a layer of grated hard-cooked eggs (2).
Sprinkle with pepper. Repeat to fill dish. Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° about 25 minutes or until bubbly hot and crusty.

title: homemade cinnamon rolls
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix everything except cinnamon and brown sugar; let rise for 1 hour.
Roll out.
Mix brown sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle on top.
Roll up tightly, then cut about 1 1/2-inch apart.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes.
For icing, just buy plain vanilla cake icing.

title: no buttermilk or eggs cake
directions: Blend all wet ingredients. Add dry ingredients. Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: beef enchiladas
directions: Toppings:
Use sliced black olives, green onions, green peppers, etc.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt oleo in baking dish. Mix all other ingredients well. Bake 45 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: pineapple supreme cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions in 10 x 18-inch pan. Let cool.
Beat cream cheese until soft; add pudding and milk. Mix and put on top of cooled cake.
Sprinkle drained pineapple over pudding, then cover with Cool Whip.
Top with nuts, coconut and/or cherries.

title: club cracker cookie bar
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with whole club crackers.
Combine sugars, margarine, milk and 1 cup graham crackers and cook 5 minutes.
Cool to warm.
Pour over crackers.
Cover with another layer of crackers.
Melt together peanut butter and chocolate chips.
Spread over crackers.
Refrigerate.

title: pineapple delite cake
directions: Drain pineapple.
Use juice in cake mix instead of water. Finish up with water for the amount of water cake calls for.
Bake in two layer cake pan at 350° until done.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Shape into loaf.
Place in Sweet 'N Sour Meat Loaf Sauce.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Melt and cool chocolate in mixer bowl.
Beat well.
Add egg yolks, condensed milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Stir in half and half and whipping cream.
Pour into ice cream container and freeze according to freezer instructions.

title: peachy pork picante
directions: Coat pork cubes with taco seasoning.
Heat oil in large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.
Add pork; cook until brown, stirring occasionally.
Add salsa and preserves to pan; lower heat.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: baked beans supreme
directions: Brown onion and ground chuck.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake in casserole for 1 hour at 350°.

title: toe to's cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Mix wet ingredients. Pour wet into dry. Beat eggs. Add sugar, cooled Crisco, warm milk, vanilla, whiskey, honey and orange juice. Mix dry; add nuts. Add wet to dry ingredients. Form into balls. Grease pan. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Put 2 to 3 handfuls of cooled cookies in bowl. Pour frosting mix with hands or rubber spatula in folding action.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain the pineapple and save the juice.
Mix the pudding with the pineapple juice and set aside.
Drain all the fruit. Mix with the pudding mixture.
Serve.
(You can use banana pudding.
I also use strawberries and white grapes when in season.)

title: gazpacho
directions: Combine tomato juice, garlic, cinnamon sticks, cumin, sugar, salt, pepper, Tabasco and vinegar.
Bring to a rolling boil (5 minutes); strain out garlic and cinnamon sticks.
Turn off heat; leave on burner.
Add onions and peppers (3 or 4 minutes), then add 1 1/2 juice cans of ice cubes.
Stir until cooled down.
When almost melted, add cucumber and zucchini; stir, then add tomatoes.

title: chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chopped nuts in bottom of pan.
Mix German chocolate cake as directed.
Pour over nuts.
Melt margarine.
Cream with cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Dab over top of cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: red tomato catsup
directions: Boil down juice with onions about one third.
Mix in sugar and cornstarch.
Add rest almost at the last.
Seal in jars.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat well. Stir in molasses. Add dry ingredients; mix thoroughly. Chill dough. Roll on floured cloth, 1/4-inch thickness. Sprinkle with sugar. Roll to make sugar thick. Cut with floured cutter.
Bake on lightly greased sheet at 350° for 10 minutes.
A raisin may be placed in center of cookie if desired.

title: baked macaroni and tomatoes
directions: Cook macaroni following package directions; drain and reserve for later use.
In large skillet, saute onion in margarine just until tender.
Add tomatoes, parsley flakes, salt and pepper; simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Stir in contents of cheese packet.
Heat slowly, stirring constantly, until mixture is thoroughly blended.
Gently stir in reserved macaroni.
Pour into greased, shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 minutes; remove from oven.
Top with cheese slices.
Return casserole to oven for 5 minutes, or until cheese is melted.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on package in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
When cake is done and still hot, poke holes in cake and pour cream of coconut over the cake.
Let cool.
Spread Cool Whip over cake and sprinkle coconut on top.

title: orange smoothee
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Whip.
Serve immediately. These are so good!

title: crispy crisps
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Thaw pastry.
Roll one sheet at a time into an 18 x 10-inch size pan.
In a cup beat 1 egg; add salt and water and beat.
Brush pastry with egg mixture.
Sprinkle your choice of remaining ingredients over pastry.
Cut crosswise into 1/4-inch strips.
Place on large cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
When cool, store in airtight container.

title: almond chip drops
directions: Beat butter and sugar in a large bowl until light.
Add egg, beating well.
Mix in the almond extract and vanilla, then the flour until well blended.
Stir in chocolate chips and almonds. Drop dough by teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: deviled drumsticks
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray large baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Coat each drumstick in the mustard-salt-pepper mixture.
Roll in cheese-breadcrumb mixture.
Place in baking dish.
Drizzle with olive oil.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Beat milk and peanut butter until smooth.
Add biscuit mix and vanilla; mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes at 375°.

title: watergate cake
directions: Beat well and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Use 1/2 pound of country butter in place of oil.
This will make good cake.

title: broccoli and macaroni salad
directions: Boil water.
Add salt.
Add macaroni until cooked.
Boil broccoli with a little salt added; drain.
Put broccoli, oil and garlic in same pot.
Bring to a boil, then simmer 5 minutes.
Add to macaroni and mix together.
You may want to add more garlic powder to your own taste.

title: quick chicken tetrazzini
directions: In a medium pan, saute onions and mushrooms until tender. Reduce heat and add soup, water, cheese and sherry.
Stir occasionally until cheese melts.
Add pimento, parsley, chicken and spaghetti.
Bring to serving temperature.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in mixer except 1/4 cup shredded cheese. Spread in pan.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: key lime pie
directions: Beat the egg yolks until lemon colored.
Blend in the condensed milk and slowly add lime juice and salt; mix well.
Add the cream of tartar to the egg whites and beat until foamy. Continue beating, adding sugar, one tablespoon at a time, until peaks form.
Fold 6 tablespoons of the meringue into the filling mixture and pour into a baked pie shell.
Top with the remaining meringue, sealing the edges carefully.
Bake at 330° until golden brown.

title: 24 hour slaw(serves 20 people)
directions: Alternate layers of cabbage and onion with onions on top. Combine sugar, vinegar, salt, celery seed, mustard and pepper in saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Oil should be added last after saucepan is removed from stove.
Drip hot mixture over cabbage. Do not stir.
Leave in refrigerator for 24 hours before serving.

title: cream of olive soup
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan; blend in flour and cook for 2 minutes over medium heat.
Whisk in chicken stock and bring to boil and add pepper.
Stir in olives and cream; bring back to simmer. Taste and adjust salt, if needed.
Stir in sherry and onions and serve.
Very unusual and very good.

title: easy chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix about 1/2 of the cake mix (dry), the margarine, vanilla and eggs in large bowl until smooth.
Stir in remaining cake mix, the chocolate chips and nuts.

title: vegetable dip
directions: In blender, mix onion and cheese, then add mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Add egg, then salt, pepper and parsley.
Chill 15 minutes.

title: aunt mary's salad
directions: Mix the milk, Cool Whip and lemon juice well.
Add drained fruit cocktail and pineapple chunks.

title: low-fat low cholesterol eggnog
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender until smooth and frothy. Serve in chilled glasses.
Garnish with sprinkle of nutmeg. Makes 2 servings.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Cool cornbread and
mix
chopped vegetables in crumbled cornbread.	Mix in small bowl.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: You will need 24 cupcake liners.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding, sugar and milk together about 2 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip; set aside.
Lightly grease bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan with oil.
Line bottom of pan with crackers.
Pour 1/2 pudding mixture over crackers.
Put another layer of crackers with remaining pudding.
Finish with another layer of crackers.
Ice with frosting and then refrigerate.

title: cheese cake topped brownies
directions: Prepare brownie mix as package directions. Spread into greased 13 x 9 baking pan. In large mixing bowl; beat cream cheese, butter and cornstarch until fluffy. Gradually beat in milk; add eggs and vanilla, beat until smooth. Pour cheese cake mixture evenly over brownie batter.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream sugar and margarine or butter.
Add eggs, vanilla, buttermilk, salt and flour; mix thoroughly.
Pour into a deep pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: cherry delight cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients well and bake at 350°.

title: beef italiano
directions: Trim fat from roast; place in roasting pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (no lid!).
Spoon off fat; add onion and cook for 30 minutes.
Combine garlic powder, Italian seasoning, tomato soup and water; pour over meat.
Cover and bake for 1 more hour.
Add potatoes and carrots.
Bake 1 more hour.

title: jewish coffee cake(quick bread)
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time. Sift together baking powder, salt and flour. Add sifted mixture alternately with milk to shortening mixture.

title: spaghetti pizza style
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Add milk and egg; mix together.
Pour in cake pan.
Spread your cheese, then pepperoni on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve with salad and garlic bread.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together the sour
cream,
vermouth
and
soup; set aside. Grease 9 x 13-inch
casserole.
Place
ham
in a layer along bottom, then a layer
of
chicken,
and
then a layer of Swiss cheese.
Pour soup mixture
over all and sprinkle with 1 cup Pepperidge Farm seasoned
stuffing
mix over top.
Drizzle 1/4 cup melted butter over
all.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 1 hour.

title: blizzard
directions: Put ice cream in a bowl; mix until soft.
Insert the cookies and chop, then put in the blender and press mix; hold for 10 seconds.

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: Saute all vegetables, but tomatoes, in margarine.
Brown sliced sausages; drain well, then add it and the ham to vegetables.
Add chicken broth, water, tomatoes and seasonings. Bring to a boil and add rice.
Cover and simmer on low heat for 10 minutes.
Add shrimp and heat just enough for the shrimp to heat. Serve with a tossed salad and fresh French bread.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: scalloped scallops
directions: Wash and pick over scallops.
Melt butter. Add crackers and crumbs. Layer crumbs in buttered dish. Cover with scallops and half of the milk. Season with salt and pepper.
Repeat layer of crumbs, scallops and milk. Cover with crumbs. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: vegetable stuffed potato
directions: Bake potato in microwave for 10 minutes.
Cook vegetables in a skillet with butter.
Add vegetables to split potato and sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: peppered beef
directions: Spread pepper on waxed paper.
Place meat on top of paper and roll back and forth to cover roast with pepper.
Press pepper firmly into beef until it coats all sides.
Combine soy sauce, lemon juice, barbecue sauce and garlic to make marinade.
Marinate roast in refrigerator overnight.
Remove roast from marinade and roast at 325° for 2 hours for rare beef, basting with marinade. Allow meat to cool 1 hour before slicing.
Slice paper thin for sandwiches.
Reheat marinade and serve over meat, if desired. Makes 20 dollar size sandwiches.

title: pork tenderloin gourmet
directions: Dredge meat with 1/2 of the flour, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon paprika.
Brown in butter.
Brown onion and pepper.
Add remaining flour and mushrooms.
Add milk, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add lemon, salt and pepper.
Cover and bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Break up cake into square pan.
Prepare strawberry Jell-O with 2 cups boiling water.
Add 1 cup cold water.
Add thawed strawberries.
Pour over cake and stir.
Refrigerate.
When congealed, put on Cool Whip.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Marinate shelled and deveined shrimp in mixture of ingredients. Preheat broiler to 500°.
Put shrimp and marinade in broiler pan. Have the pan 4-inches from heat.
Broil for 5 minutes.
Turn shrimp.
Broil 5 minutes on this side.

title: light'n lean chicken
directions: Spray large nonstick skillet with nonstick spray.
Heat to medium and add chicken.
Season with 1/4 teaspoonful pepper.
Cook about 10 minutes, turning once, or until browned evenly.
Reduce temperature and add garlic.
Continue cooking 10 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken to serving plate.
Add broth and wine to garlic cloves.
Bring to a boil and continue boiling 5 minutes.
Reduce heat.
Combine milk and seasonings, add to cooking juices in pan.
Heat and stir until slightly thickened. Return chicken to pan and sprinkle with chives.
Baste chicken with cooking juices.
Heat through.
Very good with rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: spaghetti bake
directions: Place spaghetti in the bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Beat together milk and egg.
Pour over the spaghetti.
Drain browned hamburger and add oregano, onion flakes, salt, pepper and garlic to taste.
Place seasoned hamburger over spaghetti.
Place mushrooms on top of the meat and then spread spaghetti sauce over the mushrooms.
Put a thin layer of cheese on sauce, then layer pepperoni and another layer of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour 15 minutes covered with foil.
Remove foil and bake another 15 minutes.
Best to let stand 5 minutes before cutting. Can be made and refrigerated 24 hours before baking.

title: pear relish
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook until tender.

title: stuffed artichokes
directions: Trim and wash artichokes.
Bang on top to open chokes. Sprinkle in each choke 1 tablespoon of chopped Italian parsley, 1 clove chopped garlic, 2 tablespoons grated cheese, 2 tablespoons bread crumbs.
Close chokes (roll in hands) and place in pot.
Put enough water in pot to steam chokes (about halfway up choke). Drizzle with olive oil and sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste. Let chokes cook about 1 hour or until leaves come out easily.

title: egg rolls
directions: Chop bamboo shoots, cabbage, watercress and shrimp.
Cook cabbage and drain well.
Add browned sausage and rest of ingredients.
Allow to cool.
Roll in skins according to directions on the package.
Drop egg roll into hot oil and cook until nicely browned (about 1/2 to 1 minute each).
Great when served with duck sauce.
The following Sweet and Sour Sauce is also good.

title: sausage and cheese pie
directions: Separate crescent dough into 2 large rectangles.
Place in ungreased casserole.
Press over bottom and halfway up sides to form crust.
Seal perforations.
Slice sausages and arrange over crust.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.

title: microwave tostada dip
directions: Layer chips, chili and cheese in a 9 x 12-inch dish. Microwave for 8 minutes.

title: fudge pudding cake
directions: Combine flour, 1/2 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Add milk, oil and vanilla.
Stir until smooth. Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Combine 3/4 cup sugar, 1/4 cup cocoa and boiling water.
Pour over the batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Best cooked up last minute and served warm.
Yum!

title: pistachio cake
directions: Combine all ingredients well.
Pour into well-greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: buns, doughnuts or dutch cakes
directions: Dough will be fairly stiff, but not dry.
Place container in a warm place to raise to at least double the size.
Always cover container with a double cloth to keep warm.
Letting it rise again after poking it down won't hurt it.
Yields approximately 7 dozen doughnuts.

title: president paul's cheeseburgers
directions: So you take this meat and divide it up into 8 sections (about the same size).
You pat it until each one is thick and round. Then you shake seasoned salt and Tabasco on each one.
You put them on a covered grill and cook for about 8 minutes.
Start with about 2 minutes on each side.
When they are almost done (about a minute to go), put on Swiss cheese and cover again.
Slice tomato and onion and serve in a bun.
Ketchup and mustard optional.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Cheddar cheese.
Mix until well blended.
Add all other ingredients (except pecans).
Mix well.
Chill.
Shape into a ball and roll in pecans.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Combine first 6 ingredients; stir well.
Spoon into a greased 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine cereal and butter. Sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer ingredients in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch Pyrex dish, starting with lettuce.
Spread mayonnaise on top.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: moist and delicious corn bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well.
Add cornbread mix.
Pour into greased muffin tins or square baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hamburger chop suey
directions: Serve over your favorite rice.

title: chili relleno
directions: Put 1/2 the chiles on the bottom of a greased casserole dish. Top with Cheddar cheese.
Add the rest of the chilies.
Top with Jack cheese.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Combine egg yolks, evaporated milk, flour, salt and pepper.
Fold together with egg whites and pour over chiles and cheese.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Pour tomato sauce on top and bake another 30 minutes.

title: brenda's broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in bread loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes (depending on your oven temperature).

title: daddy's favorite chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes (top of cookies will look pale).
Combine all ingredients.
Add nuts and chocolate.
Drop from a teaspoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet.

title: surprisin' carrot cake
directions: Grease and flour 2 (9 inch) round baking pans. In bowl stir together first 5 ingredients; set aside. In large bowl with mixer at medium speed beat next 4 ingredients until well blended. Gradually beat in flour mixture until well mixed. With spoon stir in carrots and walnuts. Turn into prepared pans. Bake in 350° oven 30 to 35 minutes. Remove; cool. Fill and frost with 2 c. whipped cream or sour cream frosting.

title: old fashioned gingerbread
directions: Cream butter. Gradually add sugar, mixing well. Add egg and molasses, mixing well. Combine dry ingredients. Add to the creamed mixture alternately with hot water, beginning and ending with the flour mixture and beating well after each addition. Pour batter into a lightly greased and floured 9-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in the center comes out clean. Yield: 9 servings.

title: artichoke appetizer
directions: Chop artichokes.
Mix well and combine all ingredients. Spread in flat dish.
Bake, uncovered, 20 minutes at 350°.

title: artichoke cheese squares
directions: Drain artichoke hearts, reserving about 2 tablespoons marinade. Saute onion in reserved marinade; drain. Combine onion with artichokes and remaining ingredients, stirring after each addition. Pour into a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes. Cool thoroughly and cut into 1-inch squares. Reheat before serving. Yield: 64 (1-inch) appetizer squares.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies; put half on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese and margarine until smooth.
Mix in powdered sugar; fold in Cool Whip.
In separate bowl, mix together pudding, milk and vanilla.
Fold cream cheese mixture into pudding mixture.
Pour over crumbs and sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.
Chill for 2 or 3 hours.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Bring milk and sugar to a rolling boil.
Boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add chocolate and let melt.
Beat until smooth.
Remove from heat and add other ingredients.
Good over ice cream and cake.

title: robust italian salad
directions: Cut salami in half; then slice into 1/4-inch slices.
Pour dressing over combined salami, vegetables and tomatoes.
Toss lightly.
Cover.
Marinate several hours in refrigerator.
Cut cheese into chunks; then add just before serving.
Toss lightly.

title: squash dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until browned.

title: taco pizza
directions: Brown ground beef; add taco seasoning according to directions. Prepare 1 recipe of Bisquick biscuits and spread out on slightly greased pizza pan.
Spread refried beans and ground beef mixture over Bisquick.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until edges are browned.
Top with cheese and return to oven until melted. Cut and top with lettuce, tomato, sour cream and taco sauce.

title: no work chicken
directions: Mix the last 4 ingredients together; pour over chicken breasts.
Cover for 6 hours or overnight.
Turn chicken over. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Baste and cook 15 minutes more.

title: cheese roll spread
directions: Let stand until room
temperature
or
until
it can be mixed. Chill overnight or until it can hold its shape.
Shape in roll and then roll in ground nuts.
Keeps well.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Line bottom of pie shell with banana slices.
Pour in cooked pudding; let set.
May be topped with meringue or Cool Whip.

title: shipwreck casserole
directions: Drizzle oil over bottom of 13 x 11 x 2-inch casserole. Place onions in bottom of casserole. Layer beef on top of onions, rice on top of beef, celery on top of rice, potatoes on top of celery, pepper on top of potatoes and beans on top of pepper. Pour V-8 juice over top of all. Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: mary jane's candy
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Line cookie sheet with foil. Place crackers in single layer on cookie sheet. Melt butter with sugar, stirring constantly until foamy. Pour over crackers. Bake 7 to 8 minutes until brown. Sprinkle with chips. Bake 1 minute. Spread over crackers; refrigerate. When cool, break into pieces to remove from foil.

title: easy cherry cheese cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs as directed on box of Jell-O; pack firmly into a glass casserole dish.
Mix cheese cake mix as directed for 2 cheese cakes.
Pour over graham cracker mixture. Place in refrigerator for 1 hour.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift flour.
Add baking powder, baking soda and salt; sift again.
Cream shortening.
Add sugar.
Continue beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; mix until smooth.
Slowly alternate dry ingredients and mashed bananas, stirring just enough to combine thoroughly.
Do not beat.
Put into greased loaf pan, 9 1/2 x 5 1/2-inch.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: 5 layer hot dish
directions: Put into layers.
In the first layer, put the potatoes in the bottom of the pan.
Add the rice on top of the potatoes for the second layer.
For third layer, put the onions on top of the rice. The hamburger is put on top of the onions followed by the tomato soup and water.
Add salt and pepper to suit taste.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: crock-pot chicken
directions: Put chicken in crock-pot.
Pour dressing over chicken.
Cook on low for 8 hours.
Turn off.
Refrigerate.
Eat hot or cold.

title: pineapple salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve with coconut shrimp.

title: mexican dish
directions: Saute ground beef, bell pepper and onion until beef is lightly browned.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, salt, pepper, garlic salt, kidney beans and rice.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat together the first 3 ingredients, then add the flour, soda and cinnamon.
Add the apples, nuts and raisins.
Batter will be stiff.
Stir well from bottom. Spoon into a 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Pam works fine. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots in salt water until tender.
Drain.
In pan place carrots and rest of ingredients.
Cook and stir until carrots are covered with glaze completely.

title: escalloped potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes.
Cut wieners into 1/2-inch slices.
Arrange in layers of potatoes, wieners, celery and onion in a baking dish. Melt margarine.
Blend in flour, mustard and salt. Cook until sauce boils, stirring constantly.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until potatoes are tender.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together; place in a 1-quart ovenproof casserole. Bake at 325°, uncovered, for 2 to 2 1/4 hours or until rice is tender, occasionally stirring the surface skin into the pudding as it forms. Serve warm or cold. If served cold, stir in enough skim milk to thin the pudding to desired consistency. Yields 6 servings. Contains approximately 90 calories per serving.

title: cauliflower dip
directions: Mix well.
Use raw cauliflower and dip in the mixture.

title: southern cheese straws
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix together flour, cheese, salt and cayenne pepper.
Cut in butter with two forks or pastry blender until mixture looks like cornmeal.
Add beaten egg and stir. Knead until you can form a ball.
Place on floured board and roll thin.
Cut in finger size strips.
Bake on a lightly greased cookie sheet for 5 to 8 minutes, until lightly browned.
Makes 15 to 20.

title: fruit roll-ups
directions: Boil butter, sugar and water for 5 minutes. Spray 13 x 9-inch pan with Pam. Put filling in tortillas; roll up and place seam side down into pan. Pour hot mixture over and bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: seafood pasta salad
directions: Cook spaghetti noodles according to package directions. Drain.
Put in large salad bowl.
Add Dressing, cucumbers, crab meat, shrimp, broccoli, cherry tomatoes and seasoning or dressing mix.
Toss, chill and serve.

title: texas pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs lightly.
Add sugar, butter, syrup, vanilla, salt, flour and pecans; mix.
Pour into pie shell; bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until center is soft, but not quite set.

title: spaetzle
directions: Bring saucepan of salted water to a boil, reduce the heat and maintain a simmer.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg, molasses, vinegar and sour cream.
Add dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: triple chocolate pound cake
directions: Combine first five ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed with an electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Stir 12 ounce package morsels into batter.
Pour batter into a 10-inch Bundt pan that has been greased and lightly floured.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until a toothpick inserted comes out clean. Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Invert on a cooling rack and cool completely.

title: brownies
directions: Sift the flour, salt and baking powder 3 times.
Set aside. Cream butter and gradually add sugar.
Cream until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, and mix well.
Blend in melted chocolate and vanilla extract.
Add flour mixture and beat well.
Fold in chopped nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from oven; top with marshmallows or marshmallow cream.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into large pan.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: belle fowler's dump cake
directions: Pour in pan in order given.
Do not mix, except add dry cake mix on top.
Bake in large pan 1 hour at 325°.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream together the first 3 ingredients.
Add flour, eggs and flavoring.
Mix for 2 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli corn casserole
directions: In a bowl, combine 1/4 cup of cornflake crumbs and 1/3 cup bread crumbs.
Drizzle with 2 tablespoons butter and toss to coat; set aside.
In a large bowl, combine the corn, broccoli, eggs, onion, salt, pepper and remaining cornflakes, bread crumbs and butter.
Transfer to a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with reserved crumb mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes or until heated through.

title: baked seafood
directions: Arrange 2 pounds shrimp or crab or combination of seafood in a 2-quart baking dish.
Make sauce of ingredients.
Sprinkle 1/2 of sauce over seafood in baking dish.

title: winter slaw
directions: Mix vegetables together in crock.
Mix vinegar, sugar, mustard and celery seed together; pour over vegetables.
Mix thoroughly.
Cover lightly.
(Do not put on weight.)
Will keep in a cool place a long time.

title: cheddar biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. In bowl, add flour, baking powder, salt and sugar. Add cheese and butter. Mix until crumbly. Add milk. Mix until mixture forms a dough. Turn onto a lightly floured surface. Shape into a ball. Pat to 1/2-inch thickness. Cut with 2-inch biscuit cutter. Place biscuits on an ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes or until biscuits are golden. Makes 15 biscuits.

title: foolproof fudge
directions: In heavy pan over low heat, melt chips with condensed milk and salt. Remove from heat. Stir in nuts and vanilla. Spread evenly over buttered pan. Chill until firm.

title: confetti cottage cheese
directions: Mix vegetables into cottage cheese.
Scoop with an ice cream scoop onto the lettuce leaf.
Serve with a slice of Carrot-Raisin Bread.

title: oriental shrimp salad
directions: Cook rice and let cool.
Combine rice, shrimp, bean sprouts, water chestnuts, celery, green pepper, pimiento and green onions. Chill 1 hour.

title: big boy strawberry pie
directions: Mix water, sugar, cornstarch & jello. Put in saucepan, bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cook till clear.
Drain the berries well; place in baked pie shell. Pour warm jello mixture over top.
Chill till set.	Top with Cool Whip.

title: gussied-up melba toast
directions: Combine all ingredients except bread.
Spread butter mixture thinly on bread slices.
Cut into quarters on the diagonal.
Do not remove crusts.
Place buttered pieces on cookie sheet and dry in slow oven until completely crisp (check in center).
Oven temperature should be as low as possible.
It will take about 1 1/2 hours to dry at 250° (the slower, the better).
May also be dried at Low power in microwave (times vary).
Refrigerate or freeze in airtight container.
Toast may be warmed for a few minutes at 150° just before serving.
Refrigerate or freeze any remaining butter mixture.

title: seafood dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve with vegetables or crackers.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: In large skillet, cook and stir ground beef and onion in margarine until onion is tender.
Stir in flour, salt, garlic, pepper and mushrooms; cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soup; simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream; heat through.
Serve over noodles.
Sprinkle with snipped parsley if desired.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix well; cook in double boiler until thick.
Layer with wafers and bananas.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut Crisco, using a pastry cutter, into
flour and salt until small crumbs form.	Add milk; mix with a fork
to form a ball.
Do not knead the pastry; it will get tough.
