Put pastry on wax paper. Cover with another piece of wax paper; roll out to
form
an 11-inch
circle.
Remove 1 piece
of
wax
paper carefully.
Flip into a 9-inch pan.	Remove other piece of wax paper.
Carefully fit into pan;
flute the
top
into
desired design.
Using fork, make holes in crust to
release steam and prevent bubbles.	Bake at 400° for 10 minutes,
or until light brown.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Mix well.
Knead a few times in the bowl and then put in greased pan or make rolls.
(Also put rolls in greased pan.)
Let rise 20 to 30 minutes.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes in 425° oven.

title: chocolate ecstasy
directions: Bake cake.
Break up into bowl and pour kahlua over top while hot.
Make pudding and set aside.
Layer:
cake, pudding, Cool Whip, candy.
Let set overnight.
Enjoy.
Makes enough to serve 10 to 12 people.

title: sweet potatoes kerrville
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in ovenproof dish that has been treated with cooking spray.
Cook for 20 minutes in oven at 350°.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Add melted butter to sugar and cream well.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat after each.
Stir in flour, vanilla and pecans.
Mix well.
Fill bottom of pie shell with the chocolate chips and cover with filling.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Better served warm.
Freezes well.
Serves 8.

title: 10 sticky buns
directions: Cut margarine into 4 parts and put 1 part in each muffin tin cup.
Grease cups with rest of margarine.
Then put 1 tablespoon of dark brown sugar and 1 tablespoon of honey or corn syrup in each muffin cup; then add chopped nuts, raisins and/or chocolate chips.
Then use 1 can of refrigerator biscuits and put 1 biscuit on top of each mixture in cup.
Bake in oven at medium heat for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients, then add spinach.
Cook shells according to package.
Slightly cover bottom of baking dish with spaghetti sauce.
Stuff shells with mixture and place in baking dish.
Pour spaghetti sauce over shells.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together and place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add the topping.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: indoor smores
directions: Measure cereal into a large bowl.
Butter a 13 x 9 x 2-inch rectangular pan.
Melt marshmallows, corn syrup, margarine and chocolate chips in a 3-quart saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour over cereal in a large bowl.
Mix quickly until completely coated with chocolate.
Stir in 1 cup marshmallows.
Make squares by pressing mixture evenly in buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with buttered back of spoon.
Let stand at least 1 hour or refrigerate if a firmer bar is desired.
Cut into squares.
Makes 24 squares.

title: favorite lazy lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Cook noodles.
Butter large shallow casserole.
Layer 1/2 noodles on bottom.
Spread 1/2 cottage cheese over noodles.
Sprinkle 1/2 browned hamburger over cottage cheese.
Put 1/2 Mozzarella over hamburger and top all with 1/2 sauce.
Repeat layers.
I like to end with the sliced cheese on top.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes in a 375° oven.
Let rest 15 minutes before serving.
Serves 8.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Chop artichoke hearts and mix all ingredients together. Sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Serve with Tostitos.

title: pennsylvania dutch pork roast
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place pork in roasting pan, fat side up; sprinkle with 1 teaspoon salt and the pepper.
Roast 1 hour. Pour apple cider and chicken broth into pan; add thyme and potatoes.
Bake, covered with foil, for 1 hour.
Scatter celery around pork and baste vegetables with pan drippings.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 teaspoon of salt and bake, covered, for 30 minutes.
Scatter apples around pork and bake, covered, 10 minutes, or until meat thermometer registers 170° in center of roast.
Transfer pork and vegetable mixture to serving platter; keep warm.

title: christmas fruit salad
directions: Mix fruit cocktail with all fruit chopped fine.
Mix in strawberry jello and Eagle Brand milk.
Stir well and add Cool Whip.
Chill and serve.

title: swedish meatballs with rice
directions: Combine beef, bread crumbs, egg, onion, salt and paprika. Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Brown the meatballs in a skillet with the melted margarine.
Combine the mushroom soup and water, pouring over meatballs.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Serve on top of cooked rice.

title: good slaw
directions: Add sugar to cranberries.
Leave in fridge overnight.
Dissolve jello in hot water.
Mix remaining ingredients with refrigerated fruit next a.m.
Let set before serving.
Makes 2 molds.
Keeps in fridge 3 days.
Freezes well.

title: corn chowder
directions: Dice onions and potatoes.
Let onions and potatoes cook together until tender, then add corn and milk.
A little butter may be used, too.

title: green grape salad
directions: Combine cream cheese, sour cream and powdered sugar.
Mix well.
Add vanilla.
Fold in grapes.
Cover and chill.
Sprinkle with brown sugar before serving.

title: pumpkin bread(one loaf)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Sift first 8 ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients and mix in order.
Spoon batter into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake for 75 to 90 minutes at 325° until bread pulls away from sides of pan and a toothpick comes out clean.

title: pizza quiche
directions: Chill pie shell 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Sprinkle bottom of pie shell with cheeses, onion, pepperoni and green pepper.
In a medium bowl, combine half and half, eggs, flour, seasonings and 4 tablespoons of the tomato sauce.
Pour egg mixture into the pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes; reduce oven heat to 325° and bake 30 minutes longer.
Remove from the oven and spread remaining tomato sauce over the quiche.
Let stand at least 10 minutes before cutting into wedges.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: summer slush
directions: Pour orange juice into a glass and top up with ginger ale and mineral water.
Decorate with a cherry and orange slice skewered to a cocktail stick.
Add an ice cube to serve.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown beef and add onion and garlic.
Cook until tender. Drain, then add other ingredients.
Cook for 3 hours or 7 hours in a crock-pot.
Add other vegetables, if desired.

title: artichoke-tomato salad with herb dressing
directions: Cook artichoke hearts according to package directions.
Put artichoke hearts, cut side up, in single layer in a shallow dish.

title: chocolate-bar easter cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine chocolate, butter and water in a mixing bowl.
Stir until chocolate is melted.
In a separate bowl combine flour, brown sugar, baking soda and salt.
Gradually add chocolate mixture, beating for several minutes with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended.
Add eggs, sour cream and vanilla, continuing to beat on medium speed for 1 minute. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool.
Top with your favorite chocolate frosting.

title: quick canape
directions: Mix and serve warm as dip accompanied by tortilla chips.

title: glorifying  icing for brownies
directions: Mix first four ingredients until smooth. When brownies are done and while they are still hot, cover them with Marshmallow Creme. Then spread with icing mixture of the first four ingredients.
(This will take some effort, but the icing will cover the brownies.)
This stuff really "glorifies" brownies.

title: pork chops
directions: Place chops in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with barbecue sauce. Slice onion and or green pepper on top.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: pico de gallo
directions: Chop very ripe tomatoes, small white or purple onion, small clove of garlic, olive oil and red wine vinegar.
Chop up cilantro or parsley to taste.
Add 1 fresh hot pepper (I use seeds and all, eliminate seeds for non-pepper bellies).

title: fruit punch
directions: Add half of sugar-water mixture to last 5 ingredients.
Add ice water to make 2 gallons.
Add rest of sugar-water mixture to get desired sweetness.

title: peanut banana shake
directions: Put everything except ice cubes in a blender.
Blend on slow speed.
Add crushed ice cubes.
Blend on slow speed again until smooth.
Serve in tall glasses.

title: egg white cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy; sprinkle salt and cream of tartar over them.
Continue beating until stiff but not dry. Gradually beat in sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, adding vanilla with the last of the sugar.
Shape by spoon or pastry bag into mounds on a baking sheet covered with unglazed paper.
Bake in slow oven
about 40 minutes or until very delicately browned and dry on top.
Remove carefully from paper while warm.

title: apple chicken salad
directions: For marinade, in small bowl combine apple juice concentrate, salad oil, soy sauce, vinegar and savory.
Place chicken breast in plastic bag in a shallow dish. Pour marinade over chicken. Refrigerate about 4 hours, turning once.
Remove meat, reserve marinade.
Grill chicken for 20 to 25 minutes, or until tender, turning once.
Remove from heat.
Cut chicken into strips.
Cover and chill 2 to 24 hours.

title: macaroni and tomatoes
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Add to cooked macaroni. Add water and can of tomatoes (crushed).
Cook over low heat until water is almost gone (15 minutes).

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook vegetables in chicken broth for 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese; mix well.
Place in a large flat
baking dish.
Cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: sausage balls in cranberry sauce
directions: Combine sausage, eggs, bread crumbs, salt and poultry seasoning.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: jane's spinach supreme
directions: Cook spinach; drain well.
Mix drained spinach, cream cheese and 1/2 melted butter.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Place in 1-quart casserole.
Mix stuffing and remaining butter; place on top of spinach.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown the beef and onion together. Add the taco seasoning. Mix all
together and heat.
Mix all the ingredients and put in a crock-pot to keep warm.
Pour over tortilla chips and top with Monterey Jack and Colby cheese, shredded up.

title: made right mushroom burgers
directions: Combine ground beef, celery and onion in 1 1/2-quart casserole. Cook on Full power for 4 to 5 1/2 minutes or until beef is no longer pink.
Stir halfway through cooking time.
Drain.
Stir in soup, mushrooms, catsup and chili powder.
Heat on Full power for 7 to 9 minutes or until heated through.
Stir halfway through heating time.
Spoon into split hamburger buns.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients as listed and turn into 2 prepared pie shells.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then turn oven down to 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Spread pineapple evenly in a 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Then spread pie filling over pineapple.
Next, sprinkle dry cake mix over all.
Cut stick of margarine into thin slices and distribute over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potato doughnuts
directions: Heat milk until skin forms on top, but do not boil milk.
Add sugar, shortening, salt and mashed potatoes.
Cool mixture until warm.
Soften yeast in lukewarm water.
Let stand for five minutes, then add potato and milk mixture with eggs that have been beaten until light.
Add vanilla to this mixture.
Add flour to this mixture, a little each time, working to a nice dough with a spoon. Put mixture into a greased bowl.
Cover and let stand and rise until it holds the impression of finger when touched lightly.
Turn out on flourdd board and roll out 1/4 inch thick.
Cut out with a doughnut cutter.
Place on floured wax paper.
Let rise until double in size.
Fry in shortening at 350° until golden brown. Makes 5 or 6 dozen doughnuts.

title: salt substitute
directions: Combine. Spoon into clean shaker jar. Add a few grains of rice to prevent caking.
Good on chicken, beef, fish and baked potatoes.

title: italian bread
directions: Mix garlic, olive oil, salt and pepper; pour over each half of bread.
Sprinkle onion and tomato over halves; cover with cheese. Bake at 500° until edges of bread are brown and cheese melts.
Cut in 1-inch slices.

title: gingerbread men
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Stir in egg and molasses.
Sift flour with remaining ingredients and fold into batter.
Chill dough for 2 hours.
Divide dough in 4 portions.
Roll portion on floured board; cut with gingerbread man cutter.
Bake on greased cookie sheet for 10 minutes at 375°.
Cool on racks.
Makes 24 cookies.

title: eggs baked with bacon
directions: Crumble bacon. Brush pan with bacon grease or butter.
Crack up eggs into pan. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and chives.
Sprinkle crumbled bacon over eggs and then sprinkle with the bread crumbs. Pour milk over eggs. Bake at 350° for 13 to 15 minutes or until eggs are set.

title: chicken wings
directions: Mix the first five ingredients.
Add chicken and marinate for 24 hours.
Then bake until chicken is cooked at 325°.

title: nutcracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add cream of tartar.
Beat in sugar until stiff peaks form.
Fold in crackers, nuts and vanilla. Pour into a
greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake 40 minutes at 325°.

title: snowball cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water and then add boiling water; cool.
Mix pineapple with juice, sugar, salt and lemon juice into gelatin; wait for it to begin to jell.
Add cubes of cake and a portion of gelatin mixture until all is used.
Place in mold and refrigerate overnight.
Ice with package of Dream Whip and spread with coconut.

title: squash patties
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form into patties.
Fry in pan in oil until brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towels.
Batter will keep 1 week in refrigerator.

title: apple pie filling
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients with salt.
Stir in 10 cups water; cook until thick.
Add lemon juice.
Pack apples into hot jars. Add filling alternately with apples.
Leave 1/2-inch head space. Process in a boiling water bath: 15 minutes for pints, 20 minutes for quarts.
Makes 6 quarts.

title: corned beef baked dish
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in casserole and top with crumbs. Bake 45 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix sour cream, sugar and coconut.
(This is the filling you spread between layers.)
Reserve 1 cup of this mixture for icing. Spread filling between layers.
Mix the 1 cup filling with 1 1/2 cups Cool Whip and ice entire cake.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and margarine. Beat in powdered sugar until smooth. Add vanilla and stir in pecans. Frost between layers, sides and top of cooled cake.

title: two pea soup
directions: In a kettle, cook the onion, celery, the carrots and the garlic in the butter, covered, stirring occasionally, for 10 minutes or until soft.
Add the ham hock, the split peas, the stock, the bay leaf and 2 cups of water.
Bring liquid to boil, skimming froth, and cook soup, covered partially, in a preheated 400° oven for 1 hour.
Transfer ham hock to cutting board; cool slightly and cut meat into small pieces.
Stir meat into soup; season with salt and pepper and discard bay leaf.
Just before serving, stir in thawed peas and cook another 1 to 2 minutes.

title: beef cream cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
While cream cheese is softening, cut beef into small pieces.
Combine softened cream cheese, onion, Worcestershire sauce and chipped beef.
Form into ball.
Before serving, roll in nuts.
(Best if prepared a day in advance.)

title: remoulade sauce
directions: Place all ingredients in blender, except green onions.
Blend 5 or 6 seconds; stop.
Stir down.
Blend another 5 or 6 seconds; stop.
Add green onions and blend for 2 seconds.
Do not overblend.
Chill 24 hours.
Yields approximately 3 cups sauce.

title: german nut cake
directions: Beat three whole eggs and five egg yolks and sugar together for six minutes.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.
Beat five egg whites until stiff and fold carefully into cake batter.
Put in two 9-inch pans and bake 40 to 45 minutes at 325°.

title: marinated asparagus
directions: Blanch asparagus until tender. Put in cold water to stop cooking action and drain. Mix the remaining items together except egg yolk. Pour over asparagus. Add chopped egg yolk over top and serve.

title: deviled eggs(serves 6)
directions: Halve eggs lengthwise.
Remove yolks and mash with pastry blender or fork.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Refill egg whites.

title: mom's favorite
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cream butter, sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Add beaten egg yolks and beat thoroughly.
Add sifted dry ingredients and milk alternately in small amounts, beating well after each addition.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry and fold into batter.
Pour into greased pans and bake at 375° about 30 minutes.
Makes three 9-inch layers.

title: triple chocolate peanut clusters
directions: Melt chocolates in electric skillet on lowest setting or in double boiler, stirring constantly.
Cool 5 minutes.
Stir in peanuts.
Drop mixture by tablespoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let cool completely.
Wrap in plastic and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Yield:
7 dozen.

title: sour cream sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients; cover and chill.
Serve over fresh fruit.
Yields 1 cup.

title: sumi salad
directions: Heat oil and toast seed and almonds until light brown.
Mix in with onions, cabbage and crumbled noodles.

title: gingerbread
directions: Sift together the first 6 ingredients.
In a large electric mixer bowl at medium speed, mix the butter and sugar.
Add the egg; continue beating.
Add the molasses.
Mix both mixtures alternately, adding 1 cup of hot water and beating just until smooth.
Grease a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan; line the bottom with wax paper.
Turn mixture into pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: blueberry four layer dessert
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Cut in margarine to resemble coarse meal.
Stir in 1/2 cup pecans.
Press mixture into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: snow-top chocolate cookies
directions: Place chocolate and shortening in small saucepan and cook and stir over low heat until melted.
Cool 15 minutes.
Combine eggs, sugar, baking powder, vanilla and salt in a large bowl.
Add chocolate mixture.
Gradually add the flour, stirring until thoroughly combined.
Cover and chill for 2 hours or until easy to handle.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll in powdered sugar to coat generously.
Place 2-inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake in a 375° oven about 10 minutes or until edges are just set.
Transfer to rack to cool.
Makes 60 cookies.

title: brownie pie
directions: Melt butter and cocoa.
Add remaining ingredients.
Blend all together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: butterscotch sauce
directions: Place Karo syrup, sugar and butter in a saucepan and bring to a boil over low heat.
Add cream.
Remove from heat and serve.

title: crab spread
directions: Heat soup and cheese until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: french mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water 30 minutes. Drain and mash. Add milk, margarine, seasonings and baking powder.
Beat until fluffy. Add onion.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: ken's chicken and sausage jambalaya
directions: In a 4-quart Dutch oven (Number 8), brown sausage; remove sausage and discard grease.
Then brown pork and chicken; remove from pot.
Saute onions, celery and bell pepper until limp.
Return sausage, pork and chicken to pot and add water.
Add Tony's Seasoning and continue to simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Continue adding all other seasonings to taste (should be a little hotter and saltier than normal).
Add remaining ingredients (rice, parsley and green onions), stirring gently until all ingredients are mixed and rice begins to swell (10 to 12 minutes).
Lower burner to simmer, cover and cook approximately 20 minutes.
Turn burner off and let stand for an additional 20 minutes.
Remove lid, turn rice over with spoon and serve.
(Makes 6 to 8 servings.)

title: corn salad
directions: Thaw corn in refrigerator or in bowl of water.
Put in a bowl and add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill.

title: creamed corn casserole
directions: Mix flour and sugar together first, then add remaining ingredients.
Pour in casserole and bake for 30 minutes or until thickened in a 350° oven.

title: cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Add sweetened condensed milk; blend thoroughly.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour in crust.
Chill 3 hours.
Top with favorite pie filling.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cream the cream cheese and powdered sugar; spread dough on cookie sheet.
Layer fruit.
Can be topped with coconut and nuts. On frozen fruit, thaw and drain off as much liquid as possible before adding to the crust.

title: cheese broccoli casserole
directions: Pour boiling water over frozen broccoli.
Drain.
Re-cover with boiling water and cool 5 minutes.
Drain.
Saut onion in 2 tablespoons butter until tender, but not brown.
Stir in soup, cheese, broccoli, oleo and rice.
Butter a casserole dish and pour mixture into it.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot through.

title: celestial snow cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat for 4 minutes. Pour into 3 greased pans and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: zucchini squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onions which has been quartered and sliced in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Drain well.
Combine soup, sour cream, shredded carrots, squash and onion.
In a fry pan melt margarine and combine with stuffing mix which has been moistened well with 1 1/2 c. hot water add 2 chicken bouillon cubes dissolved.
Toss until thoroughly heated.
Spread 1/2 stuffing mixture in bottom of baking pan.
Spoon in squash mixture over stuffing mixture.
Top with remaining stuffing mixture.
Bake in 350 degree oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
This freezes very well. Bake before you freeze it.

title: apricot jam bars
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, sugar and oats.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Pat 2/3 of mixture into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Spread jam evenly over top.
Cover with reserved crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: cherry crisp
directions: Combine flour and butter.
Blend. Add sugar, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Pour pie filling into baking pan.
Sprinkle flour mixture over cherries. Bake for 30 minutes in a preheated oven at 350°.
Serve with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: waikiki chicken
directions: Coat chicken in seasoned flour and brown in oil.
Drain off excess oil.
Combine pineapple, barbecue sauce, cornstarch and ginger.
Pour over chicken in skillet. Cover and simmer 30 minutes.

title: blueberry cheese cake
directions: Mix grahan crackers, sugar and margarine well.
Pack in bottom of an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla until smooth and creamy.
Pour over cracker mixture and bake for 25 to 35 minutes at 325°.
Cool.
Pour blueberry pie filling over baked mixture.
Make a day or two ahead.
(Improves with age.) Refrigerate.

title: escarole bean and ham soup
directions: Saute garlic cloves and small sliced onion in 2 tablespoons butter.
Add ham, chopped or cut in strips and slide around in saute butter.
Pile on top of this almost 1 head escarole, washed and shredded.
Cover and steam until limp.
Add chicken both and let simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Add drained cannellini beans (white kidney) and heat.
Serve with Italian bread.

title: no cook banana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding according to package directions.
Mix in sour cream and add 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Using a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, layer with vanilla wafers, then bananas and pudding mixture.
Cover top with remainder of Cool Whip.

title: quiche fondue
directions: Alternate bread and cheese making 2 layers.
Beat eggs lightly.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Pour over bread and cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes slightly. Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Pour into large rectangular baking dish. Sprinkle with paprika and parsley. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Do not open oven during baking.

title: cream cheese cake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
With an electric mixer blend the following:
the box of Pillsbury Lovin' Lites or Betty Crocker light cake mix, 1 Egg Beater (1/4 cup), Butter Buds and vanilla. Pour into cake pan that has been sprayed with Pam.

title: jennie's gingerbread
directions: Mix together all ingredients and pat out as you would biscuits.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: candied yams
directions: Mix all ingredients together; add a layer of marshmallows on top.
Cook in preheated oven at 375°
for about 30 to 45 minutes until brown on top.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Boil cranberries, sugar and water together until berries pop. Squish through an applesauce press.
Add jello, lemon juice, celery and nuts to cranberries.
Mold and chill.

title: instant cappuccino
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Store in airtight container.
When ready to use mix 2 tablespoons per coffee cup of hot water.
Top with whipped cream, sprinkle with nutmeg or chocolate shavings.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Combine cream of chicken soup, ketchup and Worcestershire sauce in small bowl.
Mix well.
Use baking dish large enough to hold single layer of chops.
Spread small amount of soup mixture on bottom of dish.
Place chops in dish and cut slices of onion over chops.
Spoon rest of soup mixture over top to cover, using all.
Cover tightly and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: sausage poppers
directions: In mini muffin pan, place biscuits or crescent rolls until bottom and sides are covered (for the crust). Brown sausage. Mix sausage and cream cheese together until mixed well. Spoon sausage into the muffin pan. Bake until crust is golden brown.

title: no fuss rice pudding
directions: Combine ingredients in saucepan.
Cook until boils.
Let set for 15 minutes.

title: killer dip
directions: Finely chop and dice all above ingredients (for best results, chop by hand).
Put in medium bowl.
Add olive oil and red wine vinegar.
Stir and chill.
Serve with tortilla chips or pita bread triangles.
Simple, spicy and scrumptious!

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer in order given and refrigerate overnight.

title: hamburger barley soup
directions: *Save until the end.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Grease large pan.
Put dry rice, mushroom soup and chicken soup in pan and stir in mix.
Place chicken pieces on top and sprinkle with dry onion soup mix.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: cranberry chicken(serves 4)
directions: Bake chicken in oven at 350° until it begins to brown.
Mix all remaining ingredients, then pour over the chicken.
Continue baking until chicken is done.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and dry jello together.
Add drained oranges. Mix well.
Add cottage cheese.
Chill and serve.

title: spiced nuts
directions: In oblong baking dish, heat butter at High 1 minute or until melted.
Stir in curry and Worcestershire.
Add almonds and coat thoroughly.
Heat at High 4 to 5 minutes.
Stir twice.
Yields 2 cups.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cook broccoli halfway and drain.
Add all remaining ingredients except cracker crumbs.
Mix together and pour into an ungreased casserole dish.
Spread cracker crumbs on top and bake 30 minutes.

title: roast loin of pork
directions: Put pork loin roast in a roasting pan. Combine first 7 ingredients and rub over the roast. Bake in preheated 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours. Mix the applesauce, brown sugar, cinnamon and ground cloves. After the pork roast has been in the oven for the 1 1/2 hours, spread this applesauce mixture on top and sides of the roast and continue cooking for 2 hours longer or until tender.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Mix the jello with the boiling water.
Add the cranberry sauce; fold in the sour cream.
Refrigerate.
May be used in mold.

title: low cal salad
directions: Dissolve gel in 1 T chicken broth.
Heat remaining broth and add dissolved gel, let cool 5 min. Mix with chili sauce.
Add veggies, salt & pepper and cheese.
Pour into mold and chill til serving time.
Unmold over lettuce and sprinkle with dressing. Serve at once.

title: spaghetti with chicken
directions: Cover bottom of pan with olive oil.
Skin thighs and brown in oil.
Add copious amounts of garlic, basil and hot pepper.
Add slightly less oregano and Italian seasoning.
Just as the garlic starts to brown, add the tomato sauce (large can) and stir.
Simmer lightly over low heat for 45 minutes.

title: "hole in ones"(breakfast)
directions: Take the slice of bread and cut a hole in the middle (we've used many things for cutting the hole, including cookie cutters for special holiday breakfasts).

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients, then add the rest.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin custard pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and
spices.
Add to egg and mix well. Blend in pumpkin.
Add
milk
gradually.
Bake in oven at 425° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° for 50 minutes.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Add to the apple mixture the oil, chopped nuts, eggs and vanilla.
Mix flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt to the apple mixture.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan which has been greased and lightly dusted with flour.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: power cookies
directions: Cream sugars and oleo; add eggs and vanilla to sugar and mix well.
Sift dry ingredients together (flour, salt and soda).
Mix dry ingredients with egg mixture, mixing well.
Form rolls and chill.
After chilling, form balls and bake 8 minutes or until lightly browned.
Bake at 350°.

title: microwave stuffed potato shells
directions: Scrub
potatoes.
Pierce
with fork.
Microwave at High for 5 to	7
1/2 minutes; turn at 3 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes to	complete
cooking.
Place
bacon
on
bacon rack, microwave on High
for	30
to 60 seconds.
It will be crisp. Crumble
bacon and set aside.
Slice each potato lengthwise in half.
Then crosswise.	Carefully
scoop out centers, leaving 1/4-inch	of potato
next
to skin.
Arrange skins on serving plate.
Sprinkle with
salt and pepper.
Spread thin layer of sour
cream
in each shell.
Sprinkle with cheese, green onion and
crumbled
bacon. Microwave
at
Medium
for	2
1/2 to 4 minutes or until cheese melts.
Rotate at half cooking time.

title: old time dressing
directions: Boil chicken until good and tender.
Debone.
Let broth stay in cooker on top of stove.
Add all 7 ingredients and chicken pieces.
Let cook for about 5 minutes.
Put in ovenproof dish and bake for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: vegetarian chili
directions: In a large pan, saute zucchini, onions, peppers and garlic in oil until tender. Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce, beans and seasonings. Bring to a boil over medium heat. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Garnish with sour cream and grated cheese. Yield: 16 servings.

title: stuffed prunes
directions: Remove seeds from prunes; keep prunes whole.
Combine cream cheese and walnuts; mix thoroughly.
Stuff cream cheese mixture into prunes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix together with a wire whisk and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes 1 deep dish or 3 regular crusts.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute the mushrooms and the butter with lemon juice. Toss them with the cooked spaghetti and chicken.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Set aside.
Melt the butter and stir in the flour and spices.
Add broth and stir until the sauce thickens, then add milk.
Pour the sauce over the noodles. Sprinkle with Parmesan and paprika.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until browned and bubbly.

title: hawaiian dessert
directions: Pour cherry pie filling into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread evenly.
Add pineapple; cover with half of coconut.
Spread cake mix over top.
Sprinkle remaining coconut and pecans on top.
Pour butter over top evenly.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: * barbecue meatballs *
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and shape into 12 meatballs. Brown in oil in skillet; remove excess fat.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over meatballs.
Simmer over low heat 10 to 15 minutes, turning frequently, until meatballs are well glazed. Serve over rice or noodles as desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: donna's spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend well.
Cover and refrigerate several hours to blend flavors.
Serve with crisp vegetables.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together well. (Can be done in blender). Add one cup water to 2 cups of mixture or to taste.

title: pasta with shrimp and peas
directions: Bring large pot of water to boil.
Heat butter in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add garlic and shrimp; sprinkle with 1/4 teaspoon salt and cook, stirring until shrimp are pink, 2 minutes.
With slotted spoon, transfer shrimp to bowl.
Add clam juice to skillet and bring to boil; boil 3 minutes.
Stir in cream, peas, 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper; return to boil and boil for 2 minutes.
Meanwhile, add 1 tablespoon salt and pasta to boiling water.
Cook just until pasta is tender, 3 to 4 minutes. Drain.
Stir shrimp and lemon peel into sauce.
Toss with pasta.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and butter.
Bring to a rolling boil. Stirring constantly, cook 5 minutes more.
Add baking soda and cream of tartar.
Pour and mix over popcorn in a large soup pot. After mixed well, place in a large roaster pan, cookie sheet or shallow pan and bake in 200° oven for 1 hour.
Pour on waxed paper and separate to cool.
Store in sealed Tupperware to keep crisp.

title: chess pie
directions: Put in uncooked pie shell and cook at 350° for an hour.

title: creamy seaside casserole
directions: Prepare shells and cheese as directed on package.
Saute onions and pepper in margarine.
Add to shells and cheese with remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole; cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: chess pie
directions: Melt butter. Pour over lightly beaten eggs and sugar; mix well and add cornmeal, vanilla and cream. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake in oven at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes or test with toothpick inserted in center comes
out clean.

title: sourdough cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Put into pan and bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix
zucchini,	sugar,	oil and eggs.
Sift flour, salt and baking
powder
times.
Add
to zucchini mixture.
Add vanilla, cinnamon and chopped pecans.
Mix well.
Pour into 2 well-greased and
floured
loaf pans.
Cook in a 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes, until center is done.

title: "philly" cherry pie
directions: Prepare Dream Whip as directed on package.
Set aside.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla. Add Dream Whip mixture to cream cheese mixture.
Put in crust and refrigerate to cool.
Top with cherry pie filling just before serving.

title: chicken and broccoli(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Layer 1 package of cooked broccoli in a casserole dish.
After having picked the chicken from the bone, mix with the can of cream of chicken soup and mayonnaise.
Pour over the broccoli and bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: cole slaw
directions: Bring oil, sugar, vinegar and mustard seed to a rolling boil. Pour over cabbage, pepper, onion and carrots.
Cover and keep in refrigerator.
Will keep for 4 to 6 weeks in refrigerator.

title: kool-aid pie
directions: Place milk in small bowl and chill several hours.
When thoroughly chilled, beat on medium speed until double in volume, then gradually add sugar, Kool-Aid and coloring.
Place in crust and freeze for several hours.

title: barbecue roast beef
directions: Cook favorite pot roast until tender.
Shred into tiny pieces, eliminating the fat.
Add barbecue sauce to coat meat.
Mixture should be thick, not runny.
Serve on hamburger buns while warm.

title: philly cheese bell
directions: Combine cold pack cheese food and softened cream cheese, mixing until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Mold into bell shapes using two cold pack containers lined with plastic wrap or coated with margarine.
Chill until firm; unmold.
Garnish with chopped parsley and pimento strips, if desired.
Serve with Triscuits. 2 bells.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Melt oleo and mix with crackers and sugar.
Press mixture in 9 x 12-inch dish and bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Add cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar.
Beat well and add to crackers.
Put pie filling on top.
Refrigerate.

title: green salsa
directions: Remove husks from tomatillos.
Wash well and wipe dry.
Place tomatillos in a heavy saute pot or skillet over medium heat.
Cook, shaking pan, for about 5 minutes or until skin begins to burst. Immediately remove from heat.
Cut tomatillos into pieces.
Combine tomatillos with remaining ingredients in a food processor fitted with a metal blade.
Process, using quick on-and-off turns, until just chopped.
Do not puree.
Taste and adjust seasonings.
If salsa is bitter, add maple syrup, 1 teaspoon at a time, until desired flavor is achieved.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: blender custard pie
directions: In blender, process all until well mixed.
Pour into buttered pie plate; cook 25 to 30 minutes at 400°.
Check center with knife.
When knife comes out clean, pie is done.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cook rice, add all other ingredients.
Do not drain corn. You may also want to save a small amount of cheese to put on top. Bake at 350° until top is brown, approximately 20 minutes.

title: frozen sweetcorn
directions: Combine all ingredients in sauce pan.
Bring to a boil, boil 3 minutes.
Cool.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and butter; add sugars, vanilla and mix.
Add 1 egg at a time and mix well.
Sift flour and baking powder together and alternate milk and flour to flour mixture.

title: stained glass treats
directions: Melt oleo and chocolate in top of double boiler.
Take off heat.
Add nuts.
When cooled sufficiently (too hot will melt marshmallows and they will run together), stir in marshmallows. Cut 3 or 4 pieces of wax paper approximately 12 to 18 inches long. Sprinkle with coconut.
Cannot use much because it will fall off anyway.
Drop mixture onto the paper to form logs.
Roll up in the wax paper and chill.
Slice.

title: chocolate chip squares
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Cream together butter and brown sugar.
Add egg and mix well.
Add dry ingredients.
Lastly, stir in coconut and chocolate bits.
Mix well with hands.
Spread in the middle of a 1/4-inch deep cookie sheet or jelly roll pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cut in squares while warm.
Recipe may be doubled.
These cookies freeze well.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook meat in butter, stirring until done.
Drain off fat.
Put into mixing bowl and add onion, beans, olives, tomato, avocado and lettuce.
Mix well. Add cheese, corn chips, taco sauce and dressing.
Toss thoroughly and serve.

title: cheese enchiladas
directions: Dip tortillas, one at a time, in hot oil to soften and drain on paper towel.
Sprinkle onion, cheese and peppers on tortillas and roll up.
Place, lapped side down, in shallow baking dish and cover with the enchilada sauce.
Top with grated cheese and bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: easy swiss steak
directions: Sprinkle tenderizer on both sides of steak. Set aside.
Melt shortening in skillet over medium heat.
Add steak.
Cook over medium heat until both sides are browned.
Stir in remaining ingredients and cover.
Reduce heat to low.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: microwave veggies
directions: On an oval microwavable platter, put head of cauliflower in center of dish; arrange broccoli and carrots around cauliflower nicely.
Put 4 teaspoons of margarine or butter on top of vegetables; salt and pepper to taste.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap; poke 2 holes in top.
Microwave 17 to 19 minutes on High.

title: bob moore's secret barbecue
directions: Marinate the meat a day or two, then cook it on the grill.

title: cookies(from cake mix)
directions: Mix ingredients well, using a teaspoon.
Drop spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool and watch them disappear.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: heavenly baked potatoes
directions: Mix together and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with crushed corn flakes or potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: german fried potatoes
directions: Fry bacon and drain.
Fry potatoes in bacon grease with onions.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Serve with bacon sprinkled on top.

title: witches bread
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, oil, water and pumpkin until mixture is well mixed.
Add flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Half fill four greased coffee cans with mixture.
Bake at 350° for one hour, cool.
Serve plain, buttered or frosted.
Yields 20 servings.

title: shrimp chowder
directions: Saute celery and onion in margarine.
Add cream cheese and milk; stir over low heat until cream cheese is melted.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Dissolve lemon and orange Jell-O with hot water.
Add cold water.
Drain pineapple and add to the Jell-O.
Stir in enough miniature marshmallows to cover the top of the Jell-O.
Let this set in the refrigerator until firm.

title: tuna roll
directions: Drain tuna.
Blend tuna and cream cheese well.
Refrigerate until firm enough to roll.
Can be made into a ball or roll.
Roll in chopped pecans.
Serve with snack crackers.
Can also be used as a sandwich spread.

title: icebox cookies and date turtles
directions: Cream until smooth. Add 3 3/4 cups flour. Save 1/4 cup flour for rolling batter into sausages. Refrigerate at least 4 hours (better if overnight). Cut the sausages thin and place on cookie sheet, leaving plenty of space between them. Bake in medium heat to hot oven 7 to 10 minutes. Watch carefully as it burns easily.

title: pecan pralines
directions: In a saucepan cook sugar, milk, salt and Karo until thick, stirring constantly.
Cook to the soft ball stage, testing in cold water.
Add butter and vanilla and beat until thick.
Add chopped pecans.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: layered vegetable salad
directions: Layer evenly in large glass bowl, the lettuce, bell pepper, grated carrots, onions, frozen peas and boiled eggs.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar, salt, garlic powder and pepper in a separate bowl.
Spread mayonnaise mixture over layered vegetables.
Top with cheddar cheese and bacon bits.
Garnish with tomato wedges. Can be made up to 24 hours in advance.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Melt Hershey bars and bitter chocolate on stove or in microwave (about 2 minutes).
Keep checking.
Add corn flakes and nuts.
Drop on a greased pan.
Cool.
Keep in the refrigerator.

title: arroz con pollo
directions: Heat
oil, brown chicken, add onion and garlic, fry for a few minutes, then add tomato sauce and the saffron which has been dissolved
in the chicken broth.
Salt and pepper, cover and
cook for 20 minutes, add rice and stir well.
Cover again and
simmer for
minutes or until all liquid has been absorbed and chicken is tender.	Serves 4 to 6.

title: sourdough bread starter
directions: Combine in large plastic or glass container such as 1/2 gallon ice cream container.
Let stand at room temperature with lid ajar for 48 hours or until it has a pleasant sour odor.
Store in refrigerator.
Feed every 2-5-7 days with 1 cup warm water, 1/3 cup sugar and 1/4 cup potato flakes.
Stir and let stand at room temperature 9 to 12 hours.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients while heating.
When mixture has simmered for several minutes, it is ready to baste on your favorite meat as it grills.

title: chicken teriyaki
directions: Mix first six ingredients until smooth.
Pour over chicken, cover and marinate in refrigerator for several hours or overnight, turning occasionally.
Place chicken and marinade in slow cooker. Cook at low heat 6 to 8 hours.
To thicken, mix flour and water, stir in and cook on high 15 minutes.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: prego hearty lasagna
directions: Mix Ricotta, Mozzarella and eggs.
Brown beef, stirring to separate meat.
Pour off fat.
Stir in Prego sauce.

title: chocolate or fruit delight
directions: Soften margarine or butter.
Mix all the ingredients and press into the bottom of a baking dish.
Bake until light brown.
Cool.

title: potato soup
directions: Cover potatoes and onions with water. Boil until tender, but DO NOT DRAIN. Fry bacon. Add to potatoes with a little of the bacon grease. Add whipping cream. Add milk if needed to make soupy consistency.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook noodles; drain and rinse.
Stir in Italian dressing. Stir in Salad Supreme.
Add cucumbers and tomatoes.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: snicker bar fudge
directions: Line a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan with foil; set aside.
In microwave safe bowl, melt margarine or butter.
Stir in cocoa, brown sugar and milk.
Cook, uncovered, on high for 2 to 2 1/2 minutes or until mixture comes to a boil, stirring once.
Stir again.
Cook for 1 minute more.
Stir in powdered sugar and vanilla.
Spread into foil lined pan.

title: pizza with monterey jack and garden vegetables
directions: About 1 hour before serving, prepare Sicilian Pizza Dough.

title: easy homemade biscuits
directions: Grease an 8-inch skillet with oil.
Mix ingredients with spoon until very stiff, but pasty.
Drop spoonful into dry flour and turn over.
Roll each dough ball between hands until smooth, round. Place in skillet, mash down and turn over, greasing both sides. Bake in 350° oven until light brown.

title: tomatoes with basil(pomodori al basilico)
directions: Cut washed tomatoes into 1/4-inch slices.
Arrange on a large platter, slightly
overlapping.
Drizzle
oil
on top of tomatoes and sprinkle
with
salt
and pepper.
Chop basil and place on top of
tomatoes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
Great with Italian bread, if desired.

title: sourdough pancakes
directions: Add together.
Pour on hot greased griddle.
Cook until lightly browned.

title: cranberry cocktail
directions: Mix together cranberry cocktail and ginger ale.
Add lemon juice.
Makes 12 (1/2 cup servings).

title: pumpkin gingersnap pie
directions: Beat milk and pie filling; mix in large bowl with wire whisk for 1 minute.
Blend in topping and remaining ingredients; spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm; let stand at room temperature for 10 minutes before serving.

title: buttery almond cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and confectioners sugar.
Add flour and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in almonds.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 13 to 16 minutes or until bottoms are golden brown and cookies are set.
Cool for 1 to 2 minutes before removing to wire racks to cool completely.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: brown mountain cake
directions: Cream butter, gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add flour alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour.
Combine water, cocoa, and soda, stirring well; add to flour mixture, beating well.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 38 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool completely on wire racks.
Spread Caramel Frosting between layers, on top and sides of cake.
Sprinkle with grated chocolate and garnish with pecan halves, if desired.

title: winifred's meat loaf
directions: Mix well and bake.
One half more of everything for a family of 14 and it will then make 2 large loaves.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Scramble hamburg.
Boil (noodles) shells until firm.
Cook broccoli.
Put a layer of sauce in bottom of a baking dish.
Mix hamburg and broccoli together.
Stuff shells.
Put shells in pan over sauce.
Spread more sauce over stuffed shells.
Cover with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake, until cheese has melted, at 350° about 20 minutes.
Take out of oven and serve.

title: ranch salad
directions: Combine vegetables, bacon and cheese in a large salad bowl. Combine dressings and pour over salad.
Toss to mix.
Chill. Serves 16 to 20.

title: microwave chicken chilli
directions: In 2-quart casserole, combine onion, green pepper and garlic; cover and cook on High for 2 to 4 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cover.
Reduce power to 70% and cook 25 to 30 minutes.
Stir twice.
Makes 6 cups, 1 serving each contains only 187 calories, 1 gram fat, 13 g cholesterol and 75 NA.

title: cauliflower and broccoli casserole
directions: Stir soup and cheese together.
Mix with cauliflower and broccoli.
Top with a layer of cooked carrots.
Sprinkle onion rings on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Fresh cooked vegetable may be substituted.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mom's apple crisp (microwave)
directions: Peel and core the apples and pace in the bottom of a microwave safe bowl or dish. In a mixing bowl, mix remaining ingredients and pour over the top of the apples. Then place a few apples on top and microwave for 10 to 12 minutes and serve hot with ice cream.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients well.
Gradually add just enough of the milk to make a paste.
Add well beaten egg yolks.
Add remainder of the milk.
Cook slowly, stirring constantly, to prevent sticking.
When thickened, remove from heat and add vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue.

title: sweet potatoes in orange sauce
directions: Slice sweet potatoes in half lengthwise and place, cut side down, on a well-greased cookie sheet or shallow baking dish. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over sweet potatoes. Bake 1 hour at 250°.

title: onion and egg spread
directions: Mix eggs, sour cream, dip mix and curry powder together; mix well.
Spread on single bread slices; cut into fancy shapes with cutter.
Makes 2 cups spread.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and eggs one at a time.
Add dry ingredients and flavoring.
Roll thin; cut and bake in a hot oven.

title: unusual banana bread
directions: Beat eggs and flavorings together.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Pour into 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
May be baked in muffin tins if desired.
Serves 2.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together; then add dressing.
Put in loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 or 40 minutes.

title: flan
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In small saucepan, cook the 1/4 cup sugar over medium heat until sugar begins to melt; shake pan occasionally.
When sugar melts, quickly pour caramelized sugar into an 8 x 1 1/2-inch round baking pan, tilting pan to coat bottom.
In mixing bowl, beat eggs.
Stir in skim milk and evaporated skim milk, the 2 tablespoons sugar, vanilla and salt. Pour into caramel coated pan.
Set the round pan in large baking pan set on oven rack. Pour hot water into the large baking pan around the 8-inch round pan to a depth of 1-inch.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until a knife inserted near center comes out clean. Cover and chill thoroughly.
Loosen flan from sides of pan. Carefully invert onto a plate.
Serves 8. Per serving:
87 calories, 2 gm. fat.

title: cornflake macaroons
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and cream to soft ball stage.
Pour over dry ingredients, press into cake pan and let cool and cut or break into pieces.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix pulp.
Beat eggs; add milk and dry ingredients alternately.
Pour into greased pan about 2-inches deep.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: hershey pie
directions: Melt candy in double boiler.
Remove from heat.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crust.
Chill and serve.

title: celery seed salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in a jar with lid or shaker.
Shake well.
Better after 24 hours.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all together, place in a loaf pan; press meat down and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook rice until it is crumbly, not sticking together.
Clean and cut up chicken into bite-sized pieces.
Clean and wash shrimp. Squeeze lemon juice onto shrimp and set aside.
Season chicken with seasoned salt and garlic powder.
In pan heat oil; add chicken.
Cover and cook over low heat for 20 minutes.
Drain juice off shrimp and add to chicken in pan. Cover and cook for another 10 minutes.
Add chopped peppers, scallions, onions and onion soup mix into pan with chicken and shrimp.
Let simmer for five minutes.
Turn off heat.
In large pan mix cooked ingredients thoroughly with cooked rice.
Serves about seven people.

title: tropical lemon meringue soup
directions: Drain syrup from pineapple and add water to measure 2 cups liquid.
Stir cornstarch, salt and 2 tablespoons sugar together in a saucepan.
Blend in liquid.
Bring to a boil, stirring.
Cook until slightly thickened, about 2 minutes.
Beat egg yolks lightly.
Stir a little of the hot mixture into yolks, then combine with remaining soup.
Stir over low heat about a minute or two longer.
Do not allow mixture to boil.
Remove from heat and stir in lemon juice.
Cover and chill.
Shortly before serving, beat egg whites to soft peaks.
Gradually beat in remaining 4 tablespoons sugar.
Fold half the meringue into the chilled cooked mixture.
Add drained pineapple chunks.
Spoon into chilled serving bowls.
Top each serving with a spoonful of the remaining meringue.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: fruit for fried pies
directions: Pare fruit (peaches or apples).
Add sugar and let stand 12 hours.
Add vinegar.
Boil hard until fruit thickens.
When thick, put in jars and seal.
Makes delicious fried pies.

title: adobo chicken
directions: Brown chicken in oil with minced garlic and diced onion.
Add vinegar, soy sauce, tomatoes and water.
Simmer 45 to 60 minutes or until done.
Serve over or with rice.

title: cube steak and mushrooms
directions: Brown the steaks in fat in a skillet and remove from skillet. Saute the onions and mushrooms in the same skillet until tender. Combine the soup, buttermilk and seasonings in a bowl.
Place alternate layers of potatoes, onion mixture, steaks and soup mixture in a greased 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: shrimp and crab spread
directions: Heat soup.
In a large bowl, stir gelatine and water until blended.
Add cream cheese, mayonnaise and hot soup; mix with electric mixer.
Fold in shrimp and crab meat.
Cover and refrigerate until set, approximately 2 hours.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: no bake peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, cocoa and milk; bring to a rolling boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir and drop by teaspoon on wax paper; let cool completely.

title: party punch
directions: Dissolve sugar and Jell-O in 5 cups of boiling water.
Add the pineapple juice.
Add enough cold water to make a gallon. Freeze in two 1/2 gallon containers.
Then 2 hours before serving, stir in 4 cans of lemon-lime pop.

title: seafood chowder
directions: Combine potatoes, onion and celery; add just enough water to cover.
Add seasonings and sprinkle with parsley flakes.
Cook until potatoes are almost tender.
(Don't drain.)
Add 1/2 to 1 stick margarine or butter.
Heat in separate pan one can of canned milk or 2 cups regular milk until hot and then add to potato mixture.
Add fresh seafood and continue cooking until fish flakes and scallops, etc. are done (approximately 10 to 15 minutes).

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 large loaves.

title: stack cake
directions: Mix ingredients together in order given.
Use enough flour to roll dough out.
Bake in thin layers in 350° oven until brown. Stack with applesauce.

title: fried apples
directions: Melt butter.
Add water and apples.
Steam until almost tender.
Add sugar and cinnamon and cook uncovered until done.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Combine dry ingredients together; add to oil mixture and beat at low speed for 1 minute.
Add grated carrots and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in round cake pans.
Bake longer if in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: snickerdoodles(cookies)
directions: Bake at 325° until brown.
(Coconut or nuts may be added or any other kind of flavoring.)

title: chicken rolls
directions: Dip each breast half into melted butter.
Combine bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese; mix well.
Coat chicken pieces on both sides in bread crumb mixture.
Roll up chicken pieces tightly; place in baking dish so pieces are touching.
Sprinkle with extra butter and bread crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: venison (or beef) stroganoff
directions: Brown meat and onions in oil.
Add flour, water and Worcestershire sauce to soup.
Blend with meat mixture.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add sour cream.
Bring to a boil and serve over cooked rice or noodles.

title: aunt susie's apple bread
directions: Bake in 2 greased loaf pans at 350° for 60 to 90 minutes until inserted toothpick comes out clean.
Angel or Bundt pans may be used.
These should not be greased.
Remove from oven.
Cool. Remove from pans.

title: party potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake uncovered for 1 hour at 350°.

title: hot spiced apple cider
directions: Combine all ingredients in large saucepan. Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: christmas punch
directions: Combine Kool-Aid, water and sugar in a large punch bowl.
Stir until Kool-Aid is completely dissolved.
Add pineapple juice and ginger ale.
Stir for 1 minute.
Place lime sherbet, in scoop form, on top of punch.

title: chick pea, tomato and green bell pepper salad
directions: Put the vinegar and oil into a bowl; season and mix to make a quick dressing.
Then add the chick peas, green bell pepper and tomatoes and stir gently so that they are all coated with the dressing.
If you have some fresh herbs, snip some on top before serving with lemon wedges.

title: cheese dip
directions: Melt Velveeta in microwave for 8 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes.
Brown sausage and drain.
Mix sausage and tomatoes with the Velveeta and put the entire mixture into the crock-pot on low to keep warm.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Boil on low heat for 5 minutes.
Add chocolate chips and marshmallow cream.
Add nuts and let stand.

title: chewy squares
directions: Melt butter, add sugar.
Remove from heat and add eggs one at a time, beating well by hand.
Add remainder of the ingredients. Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cabbage roll casserole
directions: Line dish with chopped cabbage.
Fry beef and onion and drain. Add rice to cabbage, pour stewed tomatoes over mixture.
Salt and taste.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ginger candied carrots(serves 6)
directions: Cook carrots in cold water until tender, 25 to 30 minutes. Melt butter in saucepan; add brown sugar, ginger and caraway seed. Drain carrots; return to pot and add butter mixture.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve immediately.

title: coconut pie
directions: Put all into blender at low speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into 9-inch pie crust.
Sprinkle 1 cup coconut over the top.
Bake 40 minutes in 350° oven.
Serve warm or cold.

title: cold artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill in refrigerator for 24 hours before serving.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, salt, cornstarch and water in microwave dish.
Microwave for 1 1/2 minutes on High.
Stir; sometimes it requires more time in the microwave.
Stir; it will thicken.
Add butter and the vanilla.
Microwave for an additional 30 seconds. Serve over ice cream.

title: muffalatta salad
directions: Boil spaghetti for 8 minutes; drain. Add oil. Mix well. Add steak seasoning, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco. Marinate for 2 to 3 hours. When ready to serve, add mayonnaise; mix well. Add pimentos and black olives. If too dry, add more mayonnaise.

title: chris hayden's fudge
directions: Marinate raisins several days in brandy or run.
Then drain to use.
Melt chocolate chips in microwave or on low heat in saucepan. Add milk to melted chocolate and stir well to mix.
Lastly, add raisins and stir well.
Pour into cake tins and cool.
Can be covered with ground pecans.
Also, when cool enough to touch, can be shaped into balls.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Mix the cheeses together good.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Chill.
Roll out in cheese balls or cheese logs.
Roll in pecans.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients, creaming well; gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour to creamed mixture, stirring until combined.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour batter into a well-greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 45 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely.
Yield:
One 10-inch cake.

title: szechwan chicken(kind of hot, but great)
directions: Blend cornstarch and 1 tablespoon soy sauce.
Mix chicken; set aside.
Mix remaining 2 tablespoons soy sauce, sherry, sugar and vinegar; set aside.
Heat oil in uncovered wok at 375°.
When hot, add red pepper flakes.
Stir-fry until black (10 seconds maximum). Add chicken; stir-fry 2 minutes.
Remove chicken with strainer; set aside.
Add onions and ginger root.
Stir-fry 1 minute.
Add chicken; stir-fry 2 minutes.
Add sherry mix; stir-fry 1 minute. Stir in peanuts and serve over hot rice.

title: cranberry surprise loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour bottom only of 9 x 5 x 2 3/4-inch loaf pan (there is too much batter for an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan).
In small bowl, beat cream cheese until light and fluffy. Add 1 egg and blend well; set aside.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In large bowl, mix together flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Stir in juice, margarine and beaten egg.
Fold in cranberries and nuts.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut Crisco, flour and salt together.
Add beaten egg, water and vinegar; blend thoroughly.

title: oppido's surprise meat loaf
directions: Mix all of these ingredients in a large bowl.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Put meat loaf into your favorite loaf pan.
Cook for about 45 minutes.
To check for doneness, insert a knife into the center of the meat loaf and look to see if the hamburger is still raw or not.
If you see any grease develop during cooking, carefully pour it out and put meat loaf back into oven.

title: no bake cookies
directions: In saucepan melt cocoa, butter, sugar and milk.
Boil hard for 1 minute.
Remove from heat; add vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Mix thoroughly, working fast.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper; cool.
Remove from paper.
Eat.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: foolproof bread
directions: Sift together flour and yeast.
Heat milk, oil, water, sugar and salt until warm.
Using electric mixer, add liquid to dry ingredients.
Add eggs.
Blend with mixer until smooth, about 1 minute.
Pour into three well-greased one pound coffee cans. Cover with lids and let rise to 1/2-inch from top of cans.
Remove lids and bake 30 minutes in a 375° oven.
Cool 15 minutes before removing from cans.
Freezes well.

title: old-fashioned baked beans
directions: Brown meat and diced onion.
Drain.
Mix brown sugar, catsup, mustard and Worcestershire sauce and put in crock-pot along with meat and beans.
Cook on low, about 4 hours.

title: no-bake banana pudding
directions: Mix milk and pudding.
Stir until thick.
Add Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip.
In large bowl put a layer of wafers, then a layer of bananas, then a layer of pudding mixture.
Continue layering until pudding is used up.
Be sure to end up with pudding mixture on top.
Chill in refrigerator for 2 to 4 hours.
Can top with Cool Whip as last topping.

title: easter cookies
directions: Mix the margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add the sour cream and vanilla to mixture.
Add the remaining ingredients; chill for 1 hour.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: lyndal's chili
directions: Cook ground beef, onions and drain off grease.
Add tomato juice, tomato paste, kidney beans, salt, pepper, paprika and chili powder.
Simmer in pot for several hours.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Cook margarine, milk, sugar and cocoa just for about 2 minutes until the sugar is dissolved.
Remove from stove.
Add peanut butter; mix well.
Add rolled oats and vanilla.
Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: baked steak
directions: Place in Dutch oven.
Cover and bake in slow oven at 250° for 4 hours.
Serve over rice, mashed potatoes or noodles.
(A crock-pot may be used.)

title: potato soup
directions: Bring chicken broth, potatoes, onion and milk to boil.
Simmer 15 minutes, then add remaining ingredients.

title: fettuccine primavera
directions: Snap off tough ends of asparagus.
Remove scales from spears with a knife or veggie peeler.
Cut asparagus diagonally into 3/4-inch pieces.
Coat a large nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Add margarine.
Place over medium-high heat until margarine melts.
Add asparagus, mushrooms and next 6 ingredients. Saute until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Add wine, salt and pepper.
Cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add fettuccine and cheese.
Toss well.
Serve immediately.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
When you mix your cornbread, add vegetables and 2 eggs to mixture and bake.
Beat 10 eggs well. Crumble cornbread and add eggs, broth and 2 cups of milk, a little at a time until mixed well.
Leave mixture soupy so that it will not be firm when baked.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 450° until top is brown.

title: mexican pinto
directions: Mix all ingredients in a crock pot and fill with water. Cook until tender.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil in iron skillet the first 4 ingredients to 230°.
Add peanuts.
Boil to 320°.
Turn down to 260° and add butter and soda.
Remove from heat and pour into greased cookie sheet and cool.

title: strawberry shortcut cake
directions: Generously grease bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking pan; sprinkle marshmallows evenly over bottom of pan.

title: summer lemon cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Combine next 3 ingredients in a large bowl, mixing well. Stir in gelatin. Add cake mix and beat for 2 minutes. Pour into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes. Remove and pierce with a fork every 2-inches. Mix powdered sugar and lemon juice in a bowl until smooth. Pour over warm cake. Let set 1 day before serving.

title: mints
directions: Blend all ingredients until smooth.
Use your hands.
Cut into different shapes.
May use a pastry bag with no tip or tiny molds. Store in refrigerator.

title: cheese cake
directions: Combine graham crackers crushed with 1/4 cup of melted butter and 1/4 cup of sugar.
Put into a 9-inch pie pan to make a pie shell.
Bake 8 minutes at 350°.

title: dates bars
directions: Pour hot water over dates.
Add butter.
Add sugar and egg. Mix together and add flour, soda, baking powder, vanilla and nuts. Mix well and pour into greased and floured oblong pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
When cool, cut in bars and roll in powdered sugar.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Cook on a greased skillet.

title: strawberries and cream
directions: Stir the cream cheese and powdered sugar together until smooth to make cream.
(You may want to add more powdered sugar to taste.)
Serve with strawberries.

title: shoepeg corn casserole
directions: Drain corn.
Cream the butter and cream cheese.
Add corn and peppers.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot.

title: caramels
directions: Bring ingredients to rolling boil for 12 to 15 minutes. Add 1 cup chopped nuts and pour into buttered pan.
Cool.
Cut for wrapping.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas; add sugar, egg and shortening.
Sift flour with baking soda and salt; add to banana mixture.
Grease loaf pan. Bake in slow oven, 300°, for an hour or until toothpick comes out clean from center of bread.

title: lovely lemon cheese cake(low calorie cheese cake)
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2/3 cup boiling water; let cool.
Spray glass pie pan with Pam.
Press graham cracker crumbs on bottom of sprayed pie pan.
Blend cottage cheese and cream cheese in blender or mixer.
Add Jell-O and beat or blend at medium speed for 20 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip; add to pie pan.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight.
When ready to serve, spoon desired lite pie filling on slice of cheese cake.
Delicious dessert plus being low calorie.

title: quick and easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all 3 ingredients until smooth.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: light pound cake(bake auction)
directions: Put all ingredients into bowl.
Beat with electric mixer for 20 minutes.
Pour into well-greased tube pan or loaf pan.
Place in cold oven; set at 350° and bake for 1 hour.
Insert tester for doneness.

title: corn relish
directions: Combine water, vinegar, all the spices and sugar in 3-quart heavy saucepan.
Stir frequently with a wooden spoon, bringing mixture to a heavy boil.
Add red pepper, celery and onion to this mixture and lastly add the corn.
Return to boil stage.
Cook, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Pack in prepared and sterilized glass jars, sealing tightly.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 1 quart.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook onion in hot fat until yellow; add meat and cook
until brown.
Add seasonings, drained beans and soup.
Pour into
1/2-quart
baking dish.
Spoon mashed potatoes over mixture.
Bake 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: marmalade drumsticks
directions: Spread drumsticks with marmalade. Coat evenly with stuffing crumbs.
Place in single layers in greased shallow baking pan. Drizzle with butter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes, or until done.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions, allow to cool. Mix nuts with instant pudding mix that has been made according to directions.

title: rotini
directions: Boil rotini and add 1/2 tsp salt. Brown ground beef, drain. Add spaghetti sauce, pepper and sugar. In oblong casserole dish, layer 1/2 sauce, rotini, remaining 1/2 sauce, cover with remaining cheese. Bake 15-20 min. at 350°.

title: m&m's cookies
directions: Beat first 5 ingredients well. Add dry ingredients a little at a time, mixing well in between. Stir in M&M's.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 6 dozen.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° until filling is firm in center of pie.

title: cheddar dip
directions: Beat all ingredients.
If necessary, add more milk for desired consistency.
Cover; refrigerate 1 hour.
Stir before serving. Makes about 2 cups.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Cook rice, broccoli, celery, onion and butter in water on stove until tender.
Heat Cheez Whiz and soup together; add rice mixture.
Bake in a casserole dish at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour at 300°.

title: antipasto
directions: Steam green pepper and cauliflower separately until tender. Heat to boiling garlic, tomato paste, vinegar, salt, sugar and oil in a large pot.
Add green pepper, cauliflower, olives, mushrooms and tuna.
Heat through.
Put in jars and refrigerate.
Keeps for about 2 weeks in refrigerator.
Can be frozen.
Serve with saltine crackers.

title: baked sole with mushroom sauce
directions: Coat a large nonstick skillet with cooking spray; add margarine.
Place over medium-high heat until margarine melts. Add onion; saute until tender.
Add flour; cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add mushrooms, water and 1 tablespoon wine.
Cook over medium heat 5 to 7 minutes or until mushrooms are tender, stirring constantly and adding 1 tablespoon water, if necessary, to prevent sticking.
Stir in green onions.
Remove from heat; cover and set aside.

title: david's favorite monster cookies
directions: Cream sugars and margarine.
Add eggs.
Stir in syrup, vanilla, baking soda, peanut butter, oatmeal, chocolate chips and M&M's.
Make huge cookies.

title: vegetable simone
directions: Slice and chop carrots, green pepper, celery, broccoli, cauliflower tops and water chestnuts.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise, parsley flakes, minced onion, dill weed and celery salt and mix with vegetables and refrigerate overnight.
Top with croutons and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or covered in 300° oven for 45 minutes; add cheese 15 minutes before baking is finished.

title: chicken in a pocket
directions: In a bowl combine all ingredients, except pocket bread.
Spoon 1/4 of chicken mixture into pocket of each bread half.
Makes 2 sandwiches.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together except ketchup and brown sugar. Pour mixed ingredients into meat loaf pan; mix the ketchup and brown sugar together and spread over mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° to 400° until done.

title: everyday meat loaf
directions: Soak breadcrumbs in milk. Add meat, eggs, onion, sage, salt and pepper. Mix well. Form in loaf pan.

title: greek meat loaf
directions: Preheat
oven
Mix all ingredients gently and pack into a loaf pan.
Bake about 1 hour.
Pour off accumulated drippings before serving.
Yield:
6 servings; approximate calories per serving is 310.

title: delicious punch
directions: Combine Jell-O and hot water.
Add pineapple juice, water and sugar.
Mix altogether.

title: county fair potato candy
directions: Butter a 7-inch pie plate or similar dish.
Place the mashed potatoes in a bowl and add the sugar, coconut and vanilla.
Stir with a wooden spoon until well mixed.
Transfer the mixture to the buttered pan.
Melt the chocolate and pour it over the top of the candy, spreading it with a buttered spatula.
Place the pan in the refrigerator for 30 minutes.
Before the candy sets and the chocolate hardens, score to make squares.
Keep covered in the refrigerator, the candy will last 10 days if you keep it that long.

title: summer cooler
directions: Combine orange-pineapple juice and ginger ale in pitcher, mix gently.
Pour over crushed ice.
Yields 8 servings.

title: spiced sections
directions: Put sugar, cinnamon, cloves and vinegar into saucepan.
Cook over low heat for at least 10 minutes.
Add mandarins, cook for an additional 15 minutes over low heat.
Cool and refrigerate overnight.
Drain syrup from the mandarins.
Cook syrup until it is thick, add mandarins.
These are excellent served with roast duck or pork.

title: sausage cheese rolls
directions: Half cook sausage and drain; cool.
Add cheese, garlic powder, chili powder, oregano and onion flakes; mix.
Form into quarter size balls.

title: pineapple layer cake
directions: Mix as directed and bake in 4 or 5 layers.

title: almond raspberry bars
directions: Cream butter or margarine and powdered sugar.
Add flour, mixing well, and press into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly brown.
Spread jam over hot layer.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff.
Fold in coconut.
Spread over jam.
Sprinkle with almonds and bake for 20 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: coconut sour cream cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Bake in 2 (8-inch) layer pans. When cool, split layers to make 4 layers.
Combine sugar, sour cream and coconut.
Blend well.
Don't stir vigorously.
Set aside one cup of mixture.
Spread remaining between layers.
Combine cup of mixture with Cool whip and spread on top and sides.
Seal cake in airtight container and refrigerate for 3 days before serving. Can be frozen.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together on medium speed.
Spoon into a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with crackers, chips and pita bread wedges.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix Bisquick, sausage and cheese together.
Roll into nickle size balls.
Bake in oven at 350 degrees for 15 to 20 minutes or until browned.
Makes approximately 110 balls.

title: chicken pie
directions: Heat
soup
and broth together to make gravy.
In separate dish,
mix margarine, pepper, flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
(This
makes
the batter.) Pour gravy over chicken which is
placed
in
bottom of casserole dish.
Spoon batter over
the gravy
and chicken.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: holiday cookies on a stick
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt in a small bowl.
Beat butter, granulated sugar, brown sugar and vanilla in a large mixing bowl until creamy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in 3/4 cup Shapes & Morsels.
Drop dough by level 1/3 cup measure 3 inches apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Shape into mound with floured fingers.
Press down slightly and insert wooden stick into side of each mound.
Bake 14 to 18 minutes or until golden.
Cool on baking sheets on wire racks for 3 minutes. Remove to wire rack to cool completely.
Spread frosting on tops of cookies and sprinkle with remaining Shapes & Morsels.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: Mix together refried beans, green chilies and taco seasoning mix.
Spread on 12-inch round serving platter.
Blend avocados, lemon juice and 1/2 cup taco sauce until smooth (or use ready made guacamole dip and just drizzle with lemon juice).
Spread on top of bean mixture.
Top with a layer of sour cream, then taco sauce. Top with cheese, scallions and onions.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream the butter, shortening, sugar and eggs.
Mix flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
Add to the other ingredients.
Mix well. Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Roll balls into sugar and cinnamon.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix and chill.
Use for vegetable dip.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer ingredients in order listed.
Bake at 350°.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: skillet sticky chicken
directions: In 10-inch skillet, over medium heat, in hot oil, cook chicken pieces until browned on all sides.
Pour off fat.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients; stir into skillet.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 30 minutes or until chicken is tender, stirring occasionally.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In
a bowl, thoroughly combine the sugar, flour and eggs.
Add the melted butter and buttermilk and stir until well mixed.
Stir in the vanilla.
Pour the filling into the chilled pie shell and bake for 10 minutes.
