Without opening the oven door, lower the temperature to 350° and bake for 35 minutes more.
It is important to keep the oven door closed. Transfer the pie to a wire rack to cool to room temperature.
Cut into wedges.

title: meatballs, cocktail hot dogs and sausages in sauce
directions: Combine last 9 ingredients to make sauce.
Make ground beef into meatballs; cook, drain or buy already prepared meatballs.
Add hot dogs or sausages and meatballs to sauce.
Simmer all ingredients in saucepan or put in crock-pot on low or in microwave.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Put rice in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix water and soups together.
Pour half over rice; add chicken and rest of soup mixture.
Bake 2 hours at 350°.

title: cabbage patch stew
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Combine remaining ingredients. Pour in crock-pot and cook on high for 3 to 5 hours.

title: orange-tapioca salad
directions: Mix juice and water with tapioca and jello.
Cook until thick. Cool; add pineapple, oranges and Cool Whip.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Mix first four ingredients together; set aside.
In 9 x 13-inch pan melt butter and sprinkle in the sugar.
Now put in the cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Let set for 10 minutes and then turn it onto a platter.

title: cheese-crab dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, chill and serve with Melba rounds, crackers or cocktail crackers.
Can be made the day before. Serves about 8.

title: lemon vinaigrette dressing
directions: In 1-pint jar with tight fitting lid or cruet, combine all ingredients; shake well.
Chill to blend flavors.
Use as a salad dressing or as a marinade for asparagus, broccoli, poultry or fish.

title: bottled hell-o
directions: Mix 1/2 cup of vinegar and peppers together.
Stir well.
Add remaining vinegar and ketchup.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Pour into sterilized jars or bottles.
Refrigerate.

title: mexican delight
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Cook macaroni and drain.
Add all ingredients.
Pour in casserole dish and top with cheese slices and bake until cheese is slightly melted.

title: pumpkin soup
directions: In a medium saucepan, place onions, leeks, carrots and celery.
Saute over medium heat until vegetables are tender; set aside.
In a soup pot, combine pumpkin, spices and broth.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.
Stir sauteed veggies into pumpkin mixture.
Taste for salt and white pepper.
Garnish with sour cream and green onions or chives.

title: corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large bowl, mix all ingredients. Pour into a greased casserole.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8 easily.

title: spicy dip
directions: Mix together and chill.
The longer it sets, the better.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place bread in pan.
Put cheese on top of bread.

title: easy peach pie
directions: Slice peaches into an 8-inch square dish.
Mix sugar, flour and egg.
Put on top of peaches.
Pour melted margarine on top of that.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes until brown and bubbly. (If not moist enough batter, add an extra egg.)

title: lemon parsley potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in a large saucepan and cover with water. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and cook for 15 to 20 minutes or until tender. Drain. In a small saucepan, melt the butter; stir in parsley and lemon juice. Pour over potatoes; toss to coat. Yield: 8 servings.

title: spaghetti all'amatriciana(spaghetti with bacon, onion and tomato)
directions: Slice the bacon into short pieces 1/4-inch wide.
Cook the pieces in a large skillet, stirring often, until they brown somewhat, but before they turn dark and hard.
Remove them with a slotted spoon and reserve.
Discard all the bacon fat from the skillet.
Cut the onion into thin slices from top to bottom (rather than making the usual rings).
In the skillet, saute the onion in the olive oil until it is translucent and just barely beginning to brown.
Add the tomatoes and puree, breaking the tomatoes apart with the edge of a spatula or a large spoon.
Add the oregano and basil.
Simmer gently for 10 minutes.
Add the bacon.
Add pepper or hot sauce to taste (Red Hot is a quick, tasty way to add zing to red pasta sauces).
Keep the sauce warm.

title: easy dinner chicken casserole
directions: Mix together.
Sprinkle chips on top.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sausage potato chowder
directions: Cut smoked sausage into bite size pieces. Put smoked sausage and onions in soup pot and simmer until onions are tender. Add chicken broth, potatoes, sugar, basil, salt and pepper. Cook until potatoes are fork-tender. Add milk and both cans of corn. Stir well and heat through.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Pour olive oil into 10-quart pot.
Add onions, garlic, carrots, celery and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Cook on low heat until onions are wilted but not brown.
Add cabbage, kale, thyme, bay leaves and rest of salt.
Increase heat; cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add water, tomatoes and chickpeas; bring to boil.
Lower heat; simmer, covered, for 45 minutes.
Add pasta; cook until done.
For thicker soup, reduce water.
Add 1/4 cup Marsala, Port, sherry or vermouth before serving.
Sprinkle parsley (fresh); grate Parmesan cheese over top.

title: baked beef stew
directions: Brown meat in oil; drain off fat.
Add gravy, juice, soup and horseradish.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Place vegetables in casserole. Pour meat mixture over and bake at 350° for 1 3/4 hours.
Serves 6.

title: sauerkraut cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs one at a time, beating well.
Sift all dry ingredients and add to mixture, alternating with 1 cup of water.
Add vanilla. When well mixed, add sauerkraut, well drained and cut fine.
Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan for about 30 minutes.

title: chicken-velveeta soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a stew pot.
Heat to boiling stage, stirring occasionally, then simmer a few minutes and serve.

title: granny's bread pudding
directions: Break up slices of bread or biscuits into the mixture of eggs, milk, sugar and vanilla.
Add melted butter or margarine to mixture.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch pan that has been buttered and sprinkle top with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° until knife comes out clean and the top is nice and brown.

title: microwave chocolate wafer pie crust
directions: Microwave butter in 9-inch pie plate at High for 1 minute. Stir in crumbs.
Press mixture evenly in pie plate.
Chill and fill with your favorite cream filling.

title: meat casserole
directions: Layer twice, ending with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: oatmeal pudding cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking soda.
Combine butter, the sugars and pudding mix in a large mixer bowl; beat until smooth and creamy. Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture, then stir in oats and raisins.
Batter will be stiff.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheets, about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Thaw bread dough (takes about 2 hours), but do not let rise. Grease cookie sheet.
Flatten dough loaf on sheet.
Place pepperoni on dough, then cheese.
Roll together, tuck in edges. No need to grease pan again.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Let cool slightly and slice.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Sift together flour, cocoa, salt, sugar and baking soda, then add oil, vanilla, water and vinegar.
Mix well.
Pour into small muffin tins, filling them 1/3 full.
Top each with a spoonful of filling.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and bananas.
Mix well.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk and nuts.
Turn into 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: smothered cabbage
directions: Wash and cut up cabbage.
Set aside in water.
Put about 1/4 cup of bacon fat in large pot or skillet.
Saute green pepper and onion in fat.
Add cabbage which has been set aside.
(Only use water that remains on cabbage when taken from bowl.)
Cover and cook until desired tenderness.
Season with salt and sugar to taste.
Shake in a little soy sauce.
Stir well during cooking.

title: onion potatoes
directions: Cut as many potatoes as your family will eat into bite-size chunks.
Place in Pam sprayed casserole dish or pan.
Sprinkle generously with onion soup.
Mix and dab with butter all over. Bake at 400° for about 1 hour or until tender.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and spoon into pie crusts. Refrigerate.
Makes 2 pies.

title: aunt josie's cake
directions: Grease and flour pan.
Mix and cook at 325° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: imo lou evans's steamed cornbread
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients.
Add raisins or nuts.
Fill to 2/3 of top of greased cans.
One-pound coffee cans work well. Close lids tightly.
Place on trivet over 1 inch of boiling water. Cover steamer tightly.
Steam 2 hours.
Remove from can.
Cut with a thread.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape into a ball or log.
Roll in finely chopped nuts or minced parsley.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Soften cream cheese and add rest of ingredients.
Spread on tortillas.
Roll each tortilla (burrito style).
Refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, slice the rolls in small slices. Serve with or without salsa.

title: aunt fanny's baked squash
directions: Wash and cut up squash.
Boil until tender; drain thoroughly, then mash.
Add all ingredients except 1/2 of butter to squash. Melt remaining butter; pour mixture in baking dish, then spread melted butter over top and sprinkle with cracker meal.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until brown on top.

title: emergency dinner
directions: Mix the ground beef and celery soup.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with frozen Tater Tots.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken fried rice
directions: In a bowl, beat together the egg whites and whole egg; let sit.
Heat oil in large nonstick skillet over medium heat.
Add vegetables and saute for 20 to 30 seconds.
Add the eggs, saute for an additional 30 seconds. Add rice, chicken and soy sauce. Stir until well mixed.

title: philadelphia cheese ball
directions: Blend all ingredients together and form into a ball.
Can be topped with nuts.

title: uncle dave's noodle bake
directions: In a microsafe dish, combine the onion and butter.
Microwave on High power for 2 minutes.
In another bowl, combine the eggs, sour cream and parsley.
Add onion, cheese and ham.
Add salt, pepper and cayenne pepper.
Place the cooked, drained noodles in a lightly greased microsafe dish.
Pour egg and ham mixture over. Microwave on High power for 3 minutes, covered.
Let rest 2 minutes.
Uncover and microwave again at high power for 3 minutes or until just set.
Let rest a few minutes before serving.

title: crabmeat stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and remove stems from mushrooms.
Mince crabmeat and place in mixing bowl.
Mix ginger with cornstarch, then mix cornstarch with water.
Add scallions, sherry, cornstarch mixture and egg with the crab meat.
Mix well, adding salt and pepper to taste.
Stuff mushrooms in heavy skillet, large enough to hold all 12 mushrooms in one layer.
Add 1/4 cup water, oil and soy sauce. Bring to boiling and cover.
Reduce heat; cook for 10 minutes. Drain and serve hot.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together, then add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fettucini "al marko"
directions: Cook fettucini as directed.
Melt butter and pour over drained pasta.
Pour cream over pasta and mix.
Finally, mix cheeses and toss to coat.
Serve with grated cheeses to taste.
For variation, toss with steamed broccoli crowns.

title: easy noodle skillet meal
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; set aside.
In a large skillet, saute ham in butter until lightly browned.
Add mushrooms; cook for 2 minutes.
Add peas; cook until thoroughly heated.
Add heavy cream; cook until slightly thickened.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add noodles and Parmesan cheese to sauce; toss and serve.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: yellow summer squash casserole
directions: Cut into bite size pieces the squash, pepper and onion. Steam. Stir in eggs, mayonnaise and salt and pepper.

title: apple cobbler
directions: In a shallow casserole dish, combine apples, sugar, 1 tablespoon Bisquick and cinnamon.
In a medium bowl, mix the 2/3 cup Bisquick with brown sugar.
Cut in the butter.
Stir in milk. Drop by spoonful onto apples.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 to 7 minutes.
(Substitute apples with peaches for variation.)

title: mexican stuffed mushrooms
directions: Total Cooking Time: 5 1/2 to 7 minutes in microwave.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus; melt butter and blend in flour.
Add milk gradually.
Cook slow until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add cheese and salt.
Pour over asparagus in a 1 1/2 quart casserole; sprinkle with crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake in 325° oven for about 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour in 9-inch unbaked pie shell. Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: easy seafood salad
directions: Combine shrimp, crab, pimiento, onion and peas in a serving bowl.
In shaker container, mix remaining ingredients and pour dressing over salad.
Toss and serve.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve.
Best if served the same day as made.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons margarine; blend in flour, salt and pepper. Add milk all at once; cook, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Arrange half the cooked asparagus and all the egg slices in bottom of 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Add half the white sauce.
Top with remaining asparagus and sauce.
Toss crumbs with margarine; sprinkle atop sauce.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until heated through.
Serves 6.

title: sweet potato pies
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until done, about 45 minutes.
Blend together for 15 minutes until strings from potatoes are gone. Pour into ready pie crust and bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 4 to 5 pies.

title: cranberry whipped cream salad
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve syrup. Add enough hot boiling water to syrup to make 1 cup liquid. Dissolve jello in hot liquid. Stir in cranberry sauce and orange peel. Chill until partially set. Fold in mandarin oranges and pineapple. Whip the cream and fold into fruit mixture.
Pour into a 6-cup mold. Chill until set. Unmold.
Garnish with green grapes and cranberries, rolled in some egg whites and lime and raspberry jello.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Blend butter and peanut butter until smooth. Add eggs and vanilla, then sugar.
Blend well.
Blend in flour. Roll out in small balls.
Put on cookie sheet and press with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes, until brown.

title: crunchy creamed chicken
directions: Saute green pepper and onion in butter until tender.
Stir in soup, milk and seasoned salt.
Add nuts, chicken and carrots. Heat thoroughly.
Add parsley.
Just before serving, put a few cashew nuts in center of creamed chicken.
Serve with rice or noodles.
Yields 6 servings.

title: congo squares
directions: Melt butter.
Add brown sugar; stir.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Add flour, nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: so-easy sugar cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large bowl combine 3/4 cup sugar, shortening, oil, milk, almond extract and egg; mix well.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Spread evenly in ungreased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan; sprinkle with 1 tablespoon sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cool 5 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: oatmeal fudge bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar, 3/4 cup margarine, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in Bisquick and oats until smooth.
Heat chips, milk, 2 tablespoons margarine and salt in saucepan, stir until smooth.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Press 2/3 mixture in 15 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1-inch pan.
Spread chocolate mixture over top, drop remaining mixture over chocolate by tablespoonfuls.
Bake 30 minutes.
Cool well.
Cut into bars.

title: minestrone soup
directions: In large pot heat oil.
Add onion, parsley and celery.
Cook until veggies are soft.
Add tomato paste, bouillon, carrots, water, cabbage, salt, pepper and sage.
Bring to boil, then simmer 1 hour.
Add kidney beans, zucchini, green beans and macaroni. Cook 10 to 15 minutes or until macaroni is done.

title: banana nut muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 12 muffin pan cups or use paper liners.
Beat together butter and sugar at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat in bananas until smooth.
Mix together flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Alternately stir flour mixture and buttermilk into egg mixture until dry ingredients are just moistened.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Do not overmix batter; it should not be completely smooth.
Spoon batter in muffin cups, filling 2/3 full.
Bake until lightly browned, 15 to 18 minutes. Serve warm.

title: grampy's molasses squares
directions: Cream together sugar, eggs, shortening, molasses and then milk. Add vanilla and lemon.
Sift dry ingredients; add to liquids.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Cook at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: seafoam salad
directions: Drain pears and mash. Dissolve lime jello in 1 cup hot pear juice. Beat cream cheese with 2 tablespoons milk.
Gradually beat in hot jello. Chill until partially set.
Drain pears again and fold into jello mixture.
Next fold in the Cool Whip. Chill. Sprinkle nuts on top, if desired.

title: frozen yogurt pie
directions: Fold thawed Cool Whip and yogurt together.
Pour into crust; freeze until firm.

title: company carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender, about 15 to 20 minutes. Cook, covered, in small amount of boiling salted water. Drain carrots, reserving 1/4 cup liquid. Place carrots in 8 x 12 shallow baking dish. Combine cooking liquid, mayo, onion, horseradish, salt and pepper. When ready to serve, pour sauce over carrots. Sprinkle crumbs on top. Dot with butter, parsley and paprika. Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Great served with beef tenderloin.

title: cream of lima soup
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, combine broth, beans, the 1/3 cup green onion, butter, curry powder, tarragon and pepper.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Cool slightly.
Pour mixture into a blender container.
Cover and carefully blend until smooth.
Return to saucepan.
Stir in cream and heat through.
Sprinkle each serving with green onion tops if desired.

title: chicken squash casserole
directions: Cook and cut chicken into pieces.
Prepare stuffing mix. Blend soup and sour cream together.
Layer ingredients as follows: slices of squash, chicken pieces, soup mixture then stuffing. Bake uncovered for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: homemade salami
directions: Mix well with mixer.
Shape into 2 loaves.
Wrap and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Unwrap and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Prick with fork when done to let all juices escape.
When done, it still looks reddish, but it is done.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and peanut butter; mix well.
Beat in eggs and dry ingredients.
Shape into balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet; flatten with tines of fork.
Bake at 350° about 15 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread on bread. Garnish with olives for decorations.

title: cheese cake
directions: Blend together until smooth the cream cheese, sugar, sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker pie crust.
Chill 4 hours before serving.

title: easy chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil the
hen in seasoned water.
Cool.
Debone and cut into bite
size pieces.	Saute 10 minutes.
Add parsley flakes and chicken.
Cover and let set for 10 minutes.
Add the cream of chicken
soup
and	sour
cream.
Break spaghetti into bite size pieces and cook as directed on package or in the leftover chicken stock.
Drain and cool.
Combine with chicken mixture and
place in	buttered
casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake, uncovered, in a 300° oven until hot.

title: uncooked oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients except oats.
Boil for 1 minute.
Add mixture to uncooked oats and drop onto waxed paper.

title: vi's homemade christmas (and the rest of the year) kahlua
directions: In a large pot, dissolve sugar in coffee.
Bring to boil.
Stir frequently while keeping at a rolling boil.
Boil until slightly thickened and liquid is down to approximately 4 to 5 cups (I usually give up after about 1/2 hour, but I use less sugar so it doesn't thicken as well).
Cool to room temperature.
Add vodka and vanilla.
Mix. Pour into dark bottles and ferment for 3 months. Enjoy over ice or mixed with milk.
I must admit I've never actually made it to three months myself, but it sure tastes good as moonshine!

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together and serve with fresh fruit.

title: turkey-broccoli breakfast casserole
directions: In a bowl, mix broccoli, turkey, onion, cheese, salt and pepper.
Put into a baking dish, sprayed with Pam.
In a small bowl, beat eggs and milk.
Pour over the dry ingredients so they are just covered.
Place dish, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until eggs are set and the top is golden.
Serve hot with sourdough toast.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: You also need toothpicks.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Butter bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line pan with graham crackers.
Mix pudding according to directions.
Blend in whipped topping.
Pour half of mixture over graham crackers, then place second layer of crackers over pudding.
Pour on remainder of pudding and top with more graham crackers.
Frost with chocolate icing.
Keep refrigerated.

title: ham and cheese pinwheels
directions: Combine cream cheese, marble cheese, onions, paprika, parsley and caraway seasoning.
Spread thin layer onto 1 slice of ham. Roll tightly.
Repeat until all ham slices are rolled. Refrigerate, seam side down, at least 1 hour.
Slice rolls angularly about 1/2-inch thick.
Serve with crackers of your choice.

title: marinara sauce
directions: Saute onion and garlic in the olive oil until onion softens. Add tomatoes and simmer for 90 minutes.
Add bouillon cubes and bacon and simmer 15 minutes.
Serve alone on pasta, or with Parmesan cheese in baked ziti.

title: quick and zesty vegetable soup
directions: Brown meat with onion. Drain. Salt and pepper to taste.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil. Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until noodles are tender.

title: cherry nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat and add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with cherry juice to batter.
Add cherries, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into 9 x 5-inch greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: pecan shorts
directions: Cream butter, sugar, vanilla and water.
Add flour and pecans. Chill 2 hours or overnight.
Roll out in hands to form rectangular pieces.
Bake at 350° about 15 minutes.
Cool slightly and shake in powdered sugar while still warm.

title: cassoulet(french pork and bean casserole)
directions: Brown pork and sausage in skillet.
Add onion and garlic and cook until tender.
Pour off fat; add remaining ingredients to skillet and mix well.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole and bake at 375°
for 1 hour.
Remove bay leaf and serve.

title: spice carrot muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, brown sugar, pumpkin pie spice, soda and salt.
In separate large bowl, combine remaining ingredients, except granulated sugar.
Mix well.
Add carrot mixture to flour mixture.
Line muffin tins with paper baking cups.
Spoon mixture into muffin cups.
Sprinkle tops with granulated sugar.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes until toothpick comes out clean.
Makes 24 medium sized muffins.

title: pineapple brunch casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain pineapple.
Reserve 2 tablespoons juice and pineapple for garnish.
Combine biscuit mix, milk, eggs, butter, mustard, onion powder and nutmeg in blender or large mixing bowl until smooth.
Stir in ham, shredded cheese, onions and pineapple.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until set.
Garnish.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, butter, and cheese; shape into ball. Roll in onions and bacon bits. Pour preserves over the top. Serve with crackers.

title: rieska
directions: Dough is very soft. Put a lot of flour on cookie sheet. Knead until it holds together.
Put in oval shape and prick with fork. Bake 1/2 hour at 375° to 400° or until brown on bottom.

title: taco dip
directions: Blend all ingredients until smooth.
Spread on bottom of 2 round pizza pans or 1 large serving platter.
Sprinkle with finely chopped onion, lettuce, green peppers, tomatoes and black olives. Top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Serve with Doritos chips.

title: chili beans
directions: Crumble hamburger up in pan with chopped onion and green pepper.
Cook until hamburger, onion and green pepper are done (drain if hamburger is real greasy).
Stir in tomato soup and kidney beans.
Make a paste with flour, salt and chili powder; pour in pan with other ingredients.
Cook on low heat for 45 minutes; stir so it will not stick.

title: rabbit pie
directions: Dress and wash the rabbits.
Cut into serving pieces.
In a large stock pot, cover the rabbits with boiling water.
Add the onion, bacon, salt and pepper.
Cover tightly and simmer until tender.
Remove the rabbits from the broth and place in a baking dish.
Thicken the broth with flour, using 2 tablespoons for each cup of liquid.
Pour the thickened broth over the rabbits. Prepare the biscuit dough and pat into a 1/4-inch thick sheet. Place the dough over the baking dish, cutting slits to allow the steam to escape.
Bake in a 450°
oven for 30 minutes.

title: new basic biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix the flour, baking powder, sugar and salt together in a large bowl.
Cut the butter into small pieces and cut it into the flour, using 2 knives, a pastry blender or your fingertips until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add the half and half and stir gently until the mixture forms a mass. Gather it into a ball.
Transfer the dough to a lightly floured surface.
Knead it for about 30 seconds, then pat it out to form a 3/4-inch thick rectangle.

title: mexican salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Fritos and Catalina dressing, in advance.
Just before serving, add Fritos and Catalina dressing. Sprinkle with Bac*Os (adds flavor to salad).

title: plain cookies
directions: Melt oleo.
Beat eggs.
Add sugar, then add cooled, melted oleo.
Gradually add flour until very stiff dough.
Pinch dough the size of English walnuts and place on greased cookie sheet. Take a bowl of sugar and dip a round potato masher in it, then mash dough balls nearly flat.
Bake at 375° until slightly browned.
Makes 6 to 9 dozen.

title: south louisiana red beans *
directions: Cook beans in water with salt, bacon drippings and meat for 1 1/2 to 2 hours in heavy pot (or crock-pot on low heat for 8 to 10 hours).
Add onion, garlic and bay leaf (for crock-pot, add at the beginning).
If beans become dry, add small amount of hot water. Serve on mounds of rice; also good with tossed salad and French bread.
Serves 4.

title: hamburgs in onion soup
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Make into patties.
Brown patties on both sides and put in a casserole.
Cover with one can of onion soup and one can of water.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: creamy frozen fruit salad
directions: Combine sugar, salt and flour in saucepan.
Add fruit syrup, egg and vinegar. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Cool.
Add fruit and nuts.
Chill evaporated milk in freezer until soft ice crystals form, 10 to 15 minutes.
Whip until stiff, about 1 minute.
Add lemon juice.
Whip 1 more minute (until very stiff).
Fold into fruit mixture.
Spoon into lightly greased 6 1/2-cup mold.
Freeze firm, 5 to 6 hours.
Makes 12 servings.

title: holiday fruit cake
directions: Empty cake mix into bowl.
Add applesauce, eggs, salt and extract.
Beat three minutes until smooth and creamy.

title: banana sour cream pie
directions: Beat all ingredients until well-blended.
Pour into pie crust and chill at least 3 hours.

title: grits casserole
directions: Cook grits in water 4 minutes.
Mix eggs in milk. Add grated cheese and margarine.
Pour into grits.
Put in casserole dish. Cook 30 minutes at 325°.

title: hot german potato salad(microwaved)
directions: Microwave potatoes on High for 10 minutes.
Cool, peel and slice.

title: mile high lemon pie
directions: Prepare 9-inch baked pie shell as directed on package.
In saucepan, mix egg yolks, 1 cup sugar, gelatin, water, lemon peel, lemon juice and salt.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly just until mixture boils.
Chill in refrigerator, stirring occasionally, until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from spoon.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until foamy.
Beat in 1 cup sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Continue beating until stiff and glossy.
Fold in lemon mixture.
Pile into baked pie shell. Chill several hours or until set.

title: souper meat and potato pie
directions: Combine ground beef, salt, pepper, parsley flakes, dill, chopped onion, eggs and 1/2 can mushroom soup and add enough bread crumbs for binding.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Cover with mashed potatoes, shredded cheese and sprinkle with paprika.
Place in oven and bake until cheese is melted.

title: blackberry cake
directions: In a large bowl cream eggs, sugar and oleo well and set aside. Mix dry ingredients together and add all other ingredients.
Add to the creamed mixture.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) cake pans that have been lined with wax paper.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: fabulous flako pie(quickie quiche)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10-inch pie plate (Crisco works great).
Combine cheese, chicken, broccoli and onion in blender container or in bowl of electric mixer.
Mix at high speed until smooth.
Pour over ingredients in pie plate.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until knife comes out clean. Cool 5 minutes before serving. Garnish with tomato wedges, if desired. Makes 8 servings.

title: vegetable beef and biscuit bake
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, cook beef until brown.
Drain fat.
Stir in both soups, water, vegetables and Worcestershire sauce.
Spoon into 3-quart baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Remove dish from oven.
Stir well.
Arrange biscuits on hot mixture.
Top with cheese. Bake until biscuits are golden brown, approximately 10 minutes.

title: fun cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt. Set aside.
Cream together butter and sugar until light and fluffy; beat in egg and vanilla.
Blend in flour mixture slowly. Stir in M&M's and nuts.
Drop heaping teaspoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 11 minutes, until brown.
Cool on cookie sheet.
Makes about 5 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: melissa's taco salad
directions: Prepare beef according to seasoning mix directions.
Add beans and 3/4 cup taco sauce.
On large platter, arrange 1/2 the lettuce. Add beef and bean mixture.
Top with remaining lettuce, olives, onion, tomatoes, cheese and chips.
Serve with remaining taco sauce and sour cream.
Serves 6. Nice with Green Giant Mexican.

title: halloween party mix
directions: In a large bowl, combine the pretzels, crackers and peanuts. In a large saucepan, combine sugar, butter and corn syrup. Bring to a boil for 5 min. Remove from heat; stir in vanilla,

baking soda (mixture will foam). Pour over pretzel mixture and stir until coated. Pour into a greased 15 by 10 by 1 inch baking pan. Bake at 250 degrees for 45 min., stirring every 10 to 15 min. Break apart while still warm. Toss
with M&M's and candy corn. Cool completely. Store in air tight containers.

title: beer cheese soup
directions: All soup packages available at Hickory Farms.

title: carrot and raisin salad
directions: Toss together carrots, raisins and crushed pineapple.
Mix together reserved juice, Miracle Whip and powdered sugar.
Pour over carrot mixture and stir well. To plump up the raisins, make one day before serving.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: super supper dish
directions: Shape hamburger into small meat balls.
Sprinkle with salt and brown in frying pan; drain off excess fat.
Add sliced onion and brown slightly.
Add mushroom soup, combined with water.
Cover; cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until meat balls are done.
When ready to serve, cover with mashed potatoes (instant potatoes may be used, prepared according to instructions); spread with a little butter or margarine and brown under broiler.

title: devon's cabbage rolls
directions: Boil whole head cabbage just until leaves begin to fall or peel off.
Remove cabbage; let water drain off and separate leaves. Retain water in pot for next use.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Put a tablespoon or more of mixture in each leaf and roll up, securing with a toothpick or string.
Drop cabbage rolls into pot of water and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 hour or until done.

title: broccoli-chicken bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 9 x 13-inch pan place chicken. Cover chicken with broccoli.
In bowl stir soups together with milk.
Pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over mixture. Bake 30 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt last 3 ingredients.
Pour over Rice Chex.
Shake in a brown bag which has powdered sugar.
Cool for 30 minutes in fridge.

title: stromboli
directions: Roll hot roll mix out like a pizza and top lightly with 1/2 cup spaghetti sauce.
Add a layer of salami, ham and Mozzarella cheese.
Roll up like jelly roll and place seam side down on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: bananas foster
directions: Melt the butter in a sauce or frypan.
Add the brown sugar. Stir to dissolve.
Add the rum.
Cook a few minutes to make a syrup.
Peel the bananas; cut in half lengthwise and quarter.
Add bananas to syrup and poach until soft.
Serve over ice cream.

title: fudgsicles
directions: Put child's favorite ice cream in thermos.
Depending on outside temperature, child will have soft ice cream or milk shake for lunch.

title: raw vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Place broccoli in 1 ounce boiling water and turn off heat. Let stand until completely thawed.
Saute onions and celery in butter.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: granny's basic chocolate icing
directions: Combine sugar and chocolate together, then add milk, margarine and vanilla.
Pour into a saucepan; cook until thick.

title: chicken artichoke casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender with bay leaf, salt and pepper. Remove meat from bones and cut in bite size pieces.
Saute mushrooms and green onions in margarine and garlic salt.
Place chicken and artichokes in casserole and add mushrooms and onions. Fold in mayonnaise, sour cream, sherry and 1/2 cup of Parmesan cheese.
Mix well; top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 20 minutes or until cheese browns.

title: barbecued quail(chicken)
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Place quail in shallow dish and bake at 300° until tender.
Baste often with sauce.

title: herb rolls
directions: Blend butter, parsley, dill and onion in a 9-inch pie pan. Cut biscuits in quarters; swish each one in melted mixture. Arrange pieces touching in pie pan.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until brown.
Let stand a short time.
